INSERT INTO `wp_2_posts` VALUES (2,1,'2015-04-20 12:20:13','2015-04-20 12:20:13','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','publish','open','open','','sample-page','','','2015-04-20 12:20:13','2015-04-20 12:20:13','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(5,1,'2015-04-20 12:37:31','2015-04-20 12:37:31','','Media','','private','closed','closed','','media','','','2015-04-20 12:37:31','2015-04-20 12:37:31','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?option-tree=media',0,'option-tree','',0),(6,1,'2015-04-20 12:41:58','2015-04-20 12:41:58','','wtn-logo-long-01','','inherit','open','open','','wtn-logo-long-01','','','2015-04-20 12:41:58','2015-04-20 12:41:58','',5,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/wtn-logo-long-01.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(7,1,'2015-04-20 12:42:05','2015-04-20 12:42:05','http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/cropped-wtn-logo-long-01.png','cropped-wtn-logo-long-01.png','','inherit','open','open','','cropped-wtn-logo-long-01-png','','','2015-04-20 12:42:05','2015-04-20 12:42:05','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/cropped-wtn-logo-long-01.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(8,1,'2015-04-20 13:41:42','2015-04-20 13:41:42','','wtn-theme-logo-normal-01','','inherit','open','open','','wtn-theme-logo-normal-01','','','2015-04-20 13:41:42','2015-04-20 13:41:42','',5,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/wtn-theme-logo-normal-01.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(9,1,'2015-04-20 13:41:45','2015-04-20 13:41:45','','wtn-theme-logo-retina-01','','inherit','open','open','','wtn-theme-logo-retina-01','','','2015-04-20 13:41:45','2015-04-20 13:41:45','',5,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/wtn-theme-logo-retina-01.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(11,5,'2015-04-21 10:00:52','2015-04-21 10:00:52','Los Angeles iconic sprawl can be a little hard to decode when it comes to nightlife  at any given moment, countless parties are breaking out and being broken up by cops. By the time you get to tonights happening club, your friends have left and a cast member of <i>Girls</i> is loudly holding court in the corner booth. Though theres always something going on, its easy to feel like youre the last one to find out. This week, as youre fighting off your Coachella hangover or elbowing through Whole Foods for the last bottle of 5HTP, remember LAs got plenty to offer its subterraneans. Here are our favorite of this weeks nightlife offerings.\r\n<h2>Tuesday</h2>\r\nKick off your evening with poetry, music and dance at Cal State LAs Gender &amp; Sexuality Center. The <b>Sapphic Showcase</b> promises readings by local literary folk and features a DJ set and live performance by LA Drones. The free two-hour <a href=\"http://www.calstatela.edu/event/sapphic-showcase\">event</a> will showcase local queer artists and writers making a difference in the community.\r\n\r\nIf youre still feeling the girl power, stop by the Ace for Desert Natives, Bedrock, LAs all-local, all-female <a href=\"http://www.acehotel.com/calendar/la/bedrock-la-april\">party</a>, featuring sets from <a href=\"http://www.ladyhawkemusic.com/\">Ladyhawke</a>, <a href=\"http://www.gavinturek.com/\">Gavin Turek</a>, <a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/mereki\">Mereki </a>&amp; MJMaelstrom. Make sure to RSVP on eventbrite for free entry.\r\n\r\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DrJAj-XcaWU[/embed]\r\n<h2>Wednesday</h2>\r\nJoin <b>A New Stand Up Show</b> hosts Josh Fadem (<i>30 Rock</i>, <i>Better Call Saul</i>) and Johnny Pemberton (<i>21 Jump Street</i>,<i> This is 40</i>) and this weeks guests for a night of comedy inconspicuously set in a Koreatown Salvadorean restaurant. Top notch pupusas, spicy tequila drinks and jokes about The Copper Stills bizarre mural of a child emerging from a mountain make this free, weekly standup <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/standup.atcinefile.5\">night</a> one of the Eastsides best kept secrets.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"600\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-37tAW9-48Aw/URHyrfpNkWI/AAAAAAAAMwo/oJOTVDKpC90/s640/josh-fadem-30-rock.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"431\" /> Josh Fadem as Liz Lemon\'s agent in 30 Rock[/caption]\r\n\r\nAfter the show, stop by The Lash for <b>SIREN, </b>a DTLA Ladies Night featuring live art, dancing and drinks. Savannah will be headlining, with support from guest DJs Eli M + LMK + Dred Foxx + Crichlow. The nights <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/867299586642233/\">entertainment</a> will also feature live art from Lazy Mills - the final piece will be raffled off.\r\n<h2>Thursday</h2>\r\nMid-week blues? Work got you feeling (un)dead? Dont pluck your eyes out. Throw on your most horrific ensemble and head over to Nerdmelt to groan alongside other zombified Angelinos in an interactive staged <a href=\"http://holdmyticket.com/event/203477\">reading</a> of the 1968 classic <b>Night of the Living Dead</b>.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1250\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://vestaviavoice.com/downloads/159/download/Night-of-the-Living-Dead-Screen-Shot.jpg?cb=777102baaf879d25b25d92be1cf83db4\" alt=\"\" width=\"1250\" height=\"702\" /> via vestaviavoice[/caption]\r\n<h2>Friday</h2>\r\nWe all sell out our real friends out for <i>Swatch dogs and Diet Coke heads</i> every now and then. Luckily, Gen Xers and 80s enthusiasts of all ages are invited to swing by NerdMelt for GENTLY, WITH A CHAINSAW, a raucous <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1430074463957028\">art-homage</a> to Heathers. The night promises a <i>what-a-cruel-world-let\'s-toss-ourselves-in-the-abyss type ambience - </i>plus frenemies, refreshments, and croquet, so you can get your classic Winona fix in without offing anyone or letting your <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=unyKRYb7WPo\">sticky-fingers</a> get the best of you. Admission is free, and includes free beer and wine - though it may be best to check your cup for drain cleaner.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1338\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://andymckendry.files.wordpress.com/2014/10/heatherchandlerdies_heathers.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1338\" height=\"738\" /> via Andy Mckendry[/caption]\r\n\r\nIf youre a cinephile hankering for something a little more on the avant-garde side, pack up the baguettes and beret and head over to The Cinefamily for a night of abstract film and Francophone festivities. The screening will kick off with shorts before the main attraction - a <a href=\"http://www.cinefamily.org/films/la-collectionneuse/#la-collectionneuse-black-and-white-night-feat-cocteaus-blood-of-a-poet\">showing</a> of <b>Jean Cocteaus </b><b><i>Blood Of a Poet </i></b><i>f</i>rom the iconic filmmakers 35mm collection. DJs will be spinning Gallic tunes, and libations will be served on the theaters back patio. There will also be a photo booth where you can snag noir-style snapshots to take home as souvenirs. Dont forget to wear black and white though - c\'est trs important!\r\n<h2>Saturday</h2>\r\nJoin the witches, wizards and muggles of Los Angeles as they <a href=\"http://www.timeout.com/los-angeles/things-to-do/harry-potter-roller-skating-night\">lace up</a> their skates for The 4th Annual <b>Harry Potter Roller Skating Night</b>. Housed in Glendales Moonlight Rollerways, skaters will enjoy butterbeer, raffles and costume contests, and skate to wizard rock and music from the films.\r\n\r\nOr, for you Subterraneans more interested in whips and chains than wands, head over The Lash for Los Angeles inaugural <b>CLUB FIST</b>. The <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1603198363251861/\">party</a> is thrown by Cleo aka Daddy aka Sativa Rose, who launched it in SF when she worked at The Lusty Lady Peep Show. The kink party promises strippers, gogo dancing, and a wild time for queers and weirdos of all sexual orientations and gender identities.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_16\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"960\"]<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/cletorres.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-16 size-full\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/cletorres.jpg\" alt=\"Photo by Cle Torres \" width=\"960\" height=\"636\" /></a> Photo by Cle Torres[/caption]\r\n\r\nDon\'t forget to stop by Teddy\'s for The Catnip Club Goddesses Party, for a <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/912794302104880/\">night</a> of feline sensuality featuring tunes fromChaka Khan, Donna Summer, Chic, Whitney Houston and more! As always, proceeds will go to Kitty Bungalow, a local rescue that rehabilitates feral felines. For a limited time, <a href=\"http://thecatnipclub.com/membership/\">membership</a> is only $10 - and for all you high rolling kitties, there are also VIP packages available, so you can treat (and seat) your whole pride to bottle service and your very own house cat.\r\n<h2>Sunday</h2>\r\nAfter you <a href=\"http://www.lacma.org/event/community-free-day\">fight</a> through the crowds at <b>LACMA Free Day</b>, head over to UCB Sunset to laugh it off as lauded improv <a href=\"https://la.ucbtheatre.com/show/3802\">show</a> <b>Search History</b> riffs on the questions we ask when we think no ones watching (our browsers). The show, which boasts big-time comedy alums like Aubrey Plaza, will create improv sketches and confessionals from our idle inquiries into the digital landscape.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1920\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://fanart.tv/fanart/music/40f5d9e4-2de7-4f2d-ad41-e31a9a9fea27/artistbackground/smiths-the-50f664a13b769.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" /> via fanart.tv[/caption]\r\n\r\nOr, if the imminent work weeks got you feeling dreary, stop by The Avalon in Hollywood for the <b>The 19th Annual Smiths/Morrissey Convention. </b>Hosts Richard Blade and special musical guests The Sons &amp; Heirs promise a <a href=\"http://avalonhollywood.com/event/special-event-the-2015-smiths-morrissey-convention/\">night</a> of comatose spouses, summer days indoors, morbid love songs and playfully grim self-reflection from everyones favorite glum vegetarian. Just dont wear fur.\r\n<h2>Monday</h2>\r\nLet the quarter life crises roll in with a <a href=\"http://www.thenewbev.com/dfsource/2015/2/27/april-26-amp-27-reality-bites-x2fx2f-singles\">double-feature</a> of <i>Reality Bites</i> and <i>Singles</i> at the New Beverly. Weve yet to hear if theyll be serving up special Big Gulps for the occasion, or just offering the usual unapologetically-from-the-frozen-foods-aisle White Castle sliders.\r\n\r\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SQVw58aDt3Y[/embed]\r\n\r\nNeed we say more?\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend. Like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange  we scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest hanging fruit, and stick out after hours til the last last-call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Suicide Tuesdays 4/21','','publish','open','open','','suicide-tuesdays','','','2015-05-14 00:28:53','2015-05-14 00:28:53','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=11',0,'post','',0),(13,5,'2015-04-20 18:20:54','2015-04-20 18:20:54','','Screen Shot 2015-04-20 at 11.20.32 AM','Winona Ryder in Heathers','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-04-20-at-11-20-32-am','','','2015-04-20 19:44:23','2015-04-20 19:44:23','',11,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Screen-Shot-2015-04-20-at-11.20.32-AM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(16,5,'2015-04-20 19:45:41','2015-04-20 19:45:41','','cletorres','Photo by Cle Torres ','inherit','open','open','','cletorres','','','2015-04-20 19:45:58','2015-04-20 19:45:58','',11,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/cletorres.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(27,1,'2015-04-21 16:48:03','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Home','','draft','open','open','','','','','2015-04-21 16:48:03','2015-04-21 16:48:03','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?page_id=27',0,'page','',0),(30,5,'2015-04-24 10:00:45','2015-04-24 10:00:45','Whether youre overworked,<em> O</em><i>ver It</i>, suffering from Spring Fever or still feeling the Nochella blues, dont worry  weve got your weekend required reading covered.\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend. Like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange - we scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest hanging fruit, and stick out after hours til the last last-call. We walk the night hard - so you dont have to. </i>\r\n\r\nThis week, <b>Dazed Digital</b>s <b>Natalie Turco-Williams</b> summed up Instagrams new community guidelines: nudity is, for the most part, barred from the app (noted exceptions include sculpture, painting and other fine art). Precisely which <a href=\"http://www.dazeddigital.com/artsandculture/article/24456/1/instagram-finally-updates-its-confusing-policy-on-nudity?utm_source=MadMimi&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_content=Why+Don%27t+British+Politicians+Care+About+Fashion%3F+%7C+Music+Videos+of+the+Month+%7C+Hot+Boys+Smoking+Weed&amp;utm_campaign=20150421_m125428621_Why+Don%27t+British+Politicians+Care+About+Fashion%3F+%7C+Music+Videos+of+the+Month+%7C+Hot+Boys+Smoking+Weed&amp;utm_term=Instagram+finally+updates+its+confusing+policy+on+nudity\">nipples</a> are and are not allowed still remains unclear.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong></strong></strong>\r\n\r\n   \\_()_/\r\n\r\n<strong><strong></strong></strong>\r\n\r\nIn the most recent of a series of bizarre PR moves,<b> Madonna </b>instagrammed an image of former Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher and promptly deleted in - though not before <b>Dazed </b><a href=\"http://www.dazeddigital.com/artsandculture/article/24475/1/madonna-instagrams-picture-of-thatcher-deletes-it\">scooped</a> it up. Thatchers critics feel that Madonna, whose fame is largely predicated by her status as a gay icon, should not express her support of Thatcher, who championed anti-gay policies in British schools and expressed her hatred of feminism to advisors.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"395\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://images.dazedcdn.com/786x700/dd/1110/8/1118454.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"395\" height=\"588\" /> via Dazed Digital[/caption]\r\n\r\nMadonnas problem-status is not news to many. In Ballr (Madonna Free Zone) <b>Terre </b><b>Thaemlitz</b> aka DJ Sprinkles says:\r\n\r\nWhen Madonna came out with her hit Vogue I knew it was over. She had taken a very specifically queer, transgendered, Latino and African-American phenomenon and totally erased that context with her lyrics, it makes no difference if you\'re black or white, if you\'re a boy or a girl. Madonna was taking in tons of money, while the Queen who actually taught her how to vogue sat before me in the club, strung out, depressed and broke. So if anybody requested Vogue or any other Madonna track, I told them, no, this is a Madonna-free zone! And as long as I\'m DJ-ing, you will not be allowed to vogue to the decontextualized, reified, corporatized, liberalized, neutralized, asexualized, re-genderized pop reflection of this dance floor\'s reality!\r\n\r\n<b>The Quietus</b> dissected the Fame and camp of Grace Jones, expanding on the significance of disco as a social movement. It\'s easy to forget how liberating disco must have been for minority groups back in the mid-70s, <a href=\"http://thequietus.com/articles/17650-grace-jones-disco-review\">says</a> writer <b>Jeremy Allen</b>. And by minority I mean pretty much anyone who wasn\'t white, straight and male; not only was it the sound of liberation, disco was also a defiant raposte to the muso-wankery of Rolling Stone and Creem and the idea disseminated by the media that music had to be serious and made with guitars for it to be proper.\r\n\r\nWe learned about the auditory <a href=\"http://www.bbc.com/future/story/20150420-the-strangest-sounds-in-the-world\">illusions</a> that enable and inhibit our perceptions of soundscapes, in a discussion of the mechanisms and factors that contribute to the guessing game of being a good listener.\r\n\r\nYoure basically an auditory detective every day because you get all this ambiguous info, like sound spaghetti, and you do it so well you dont know youre even doing it, deaf neuroscience PhD student <b>Sophie Meekings</b> explained to <b>The BBC</b>s <b>David Robson</b>.\r\n\r\nPsychiatrist <b>Dr David Veal </b>revealed that 2/3 patients who come to see him for Body Dysmorphic Disorder since the rise of camera phones have a compulsion to repeatedly take selfies, as <a href=\"http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/selfies-linked-narcissism-addiction-mental-illness-say-scientists-1441480\">reported</a> by the <b>International Business Times</b>.\r\n\r\nIndie lit blog <a href=\"http://cuttyspot.tumblr.com/\"><b>cutty spot</b></a> shared screenshots of Atlanta based writer/editor <a href=\"http://amy-mcdaniel.com/\"><b>Amy McDaniel</b></a>s thoughts on the Internet as a metaphor.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong><a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Screen-Shot-2015-04-22-at-11.47.11-AM.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-31\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Screen-Shot-2015-04-22-at-11.47.11-AM-300x293.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-04-22 at 11.47.11 AM\" width=\"300\" height=\"293\" /></a></strong></strong>\r\n\r\n16-year-old actress <b>Amandla Stenberg</b> educated us on the <a href=\"http://www.rawstory.com/2015/04/hunger-games-stars-stunning-critique-what-if-america-loved-black-people-as-much-as-black-culture/\">problem</a> with stars like Taylor Swift and Kendall Jenner sporting cornrows, observing, The line between cultural appropriation and cultural exchange is always going to be blurred, but heres the thing: Appropriation occurs when a style leads to racist generalizations or stereotypes where it originated, but is deemed as high fashion, cool or funny when the privileged take it for themselves. Appropriation occurs when the appropriator is not aware of the deep significance of the culture that they are partaking in.\r\n\r\nIn a <a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2015/04/19/books/review/jon-ronsons-so-youve-been-publicly-shamed.html?_r=0\">review</a> of Joe Ronsons <i>So Youve Been Publicly Shamed</i>, <b>The New York Times</b><b> Choire Sicha </b>took the author and his readers to task in a smart and generous reflection on the different forms of hate speech men and women encounter on social media. For women  and for all gender offenders, from gays to trans people  insult and the threat of murder are issued simultaneously, Sicha observes. Like almost every other book, then, So Youve Been Publicly Shamed would probably have been handled better by a woman. Often we send a married, middle-aged man who makes $250,000 a year (half a million in a good year, apparently) to do the job.\r\n\r\nOn <b>The Huffington Post,</b> UT Austin Professor <b>Kali Nicole Gross</b> <a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/kali-nicole-gross/silence-on-black-female-victims_b_7092128.html\">discussed</a> the representation and omissions of black female victims in conversations about police brutality, citing Marissa Alexanders case and that of Cece McDonald, a 24-year-old African American transwoman forced to serve 19 months in solitary in a male facility for defending herself against a racist, transphobic attack.\r\n\r\nIn the tech-space, <b>The Guardian</b>s <b>Nicole Kobie</b> <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/apr/20/internet-of-things-traffic\">guided</a> us through the physical and information traffic that faces - and often imbolizes navigation technology in a succinct discussion of the challenges and possibilities developing connected, self-driving cars, while <b>Sangeet Paul Choudary</b> broke <a href=\"https://medium.com/platform-thinking/how-paypal-and-reddit-faked-their-way-to-traction-9411fb583205\">down</a> the seeds and weeds that brought some of todays most successful apps from scrappy startups to Dot Com Tycoons on <b>Medium</b>.\r\n\r\n<b>Dazed</b> delivered eye-candy in the form of a sneak <a href=\"http://www.dazeddigital.com/fashion/article/24383/1/chloe-sevigny-the-coolest-girl-in-the-world\">preview</a> of the forthcoming <b>Chloe Sevigny </b>photobook (!) while Slate let us <a href=\"http://www.slate.com/blogs/atlas_obscura/2015/04/21/gustav_eiffel_s_science_apartment_high_atop_his_famed_tower_was_once_the.html\">peek</a> inside the apartment where Gustave Eiffel lived and entertained guests like Thomas Edison.\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend. Like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange  we scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest hanging fruit, and stick out after hours til the last last-call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Thank Fuck It\'s Friday 4/24 Weekly Web Roundup','','publish','open','open','','thank-fuck-its-friday-424-weekly-web-roundup','','','2015-05-14 00:27:15','2015-05-14 00:27:15','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=30',0,'post','',0),(31,5,'2015-04-23 21:09:57','2015-04-23 21:09:57','','Screen Shot 2015-04-22 at 11.47.11 AM','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-04-22-at-11-47-11-am','','','2015-04-23 21:09:57','2015-04-23 21:09:57','',30,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Screen-Shot-2015-04-22-at-11.47.11-AM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(32,5,'2015-04-23 21:24:29','2015-04-23 21:24:29','','tfifchloe','','inherit','open','open','','tfifchloe','','','2015-04-23 21:24:29','2015-04-23 21:24:29','',30,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/tfifchloe.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(34,5,'2015-04-23 21:27:06','2015-04-23 21:27:06','','Screen Shot 2015-04-23 at 2.26.43 PM','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-04-23-at-2-26-43-pm','','','2015-04-23 21:27:06','2015-04-23 21:27:06','',30,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Screen-Shot-2015-04-23-at-2.26.43-PM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(35,5,'2015-04-23 21:30:51','2015-04-23 21:30:51','','Chloe Sevingy via Jacopo Coccia','','inherit','open','open','','15814338497_f03099544d_o','','','2015-04-23 21:31:41','2015-04-23 21:31:41','',30,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/15814338497_f03099544d_o.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(37,5,'2015-04-23 22:56:15','2015-04-23 22:56:15','','MariaShriverGraceJones','Grace Jones & Maria Shriver at Studio 54, as photographed by Andy Warhol','inherit','open','open','','mariashrivergracejones','','','2015-04-23 22:57:19','2015-04-23 22:57:19','',30,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/MariaShriverGraceJones.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(39,6,'2015-04-24 23:09:14','2015-04-24 23:09:14','In a Chihuahua <a href=\"http://m.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/paris-hilton-beloved-chihuahua-tinkerbell-dead-14-article-1.2193730\">whimper</a> heard round the world (or at least echoed through Beverly Hills), this Monday, Paris Hiltons emblematic canine accessory Tinkerbell passed on to greener, less <a href=\"http://blackbag.gawker.com/just-a-400-kilo-drug-bust-at-paris-hiltons-family-ranc-1630424516\">powdered</a> pastures.\r\n\r\nMy heart is broken, Hilton remarked. I am so sad &amp; devastated. After 14 amazing years together my baby Tinkerbell has passed away of old age. I feel like I\'ve lost a member of my family.\r\n\r\nI like to think of the rise and fall of Paris Hilton as Hollywoods own little Greek Tragedy. One minute youre at the top of the world and the next youre plucking your eyes out because the nice lady you sleptwith was your mum - or, in Pariss case, youre holding down a Vegas DJ <a href=\"http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/music-festivals/6516788/paris-hilton-ultra-music-festival-video\">residency</a>, running in circles with fellow-pop cultural ghost<a href=\"http://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/celebs/news/a37438/justin-bobby-from-the-hills-is-alive/\">Justin Bobby</a>, and posing in epileptic unicorn <a href=\"https://instagram.com/p/1RwT62qgHv/\">videos</a> on Instagram.\r\n\r\nMuch like Tinkerbells gradual <a href=\"http://m.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/paris-hilton-beloved-chihuahua-tinkerbell-dead-14-article-1.2193730\">demise</a>, her owners fall from grace weirdly manages to invoke karmic bite and elicit a modicum of genuine pity.\r\n\r\nWhile Paris first became most widely known across the country with the success of <i>The Simple Life</i>, Hollywood endured her form of winky, <a href=\"http://www.hollyscoop.com/paris-hilton/paris-hilton-carrying-tiny-dogs-evolution.html\">dog-toting</a> mass-cultural defecation for quite some time before she was a household name and, terrifyingly, a role model to many prepubescent and teenage girls.\r\n\r\nWhile Paris certainly wasnt the first starlet to be a bad role model, her rise to fame was timed closely with the rise of the Internet as <i>The</i> definitive force shaping the popular imagination, particularly for teenagers - so her problems, though not new or worse, become bigger problems than those of her predecessors.\r\n\r\nThe doubleness of Paris and the Love/Hate she inspires in self-identified intellectual women and cultural critics also highlights the variability of how we consume pop culture: while the idea of 14 year old girls looking to Paris as a role model is terrifying to us, we condone our own Amazon purchases of <i>The Simple Life </i>because we have enough access to other kinds of role models to enjoy her in irony or with a schadefreude-y pleasure.\r\n\r\nWhether we love, hate, or love to hate Paris, though, she represents an important moment in digital media, and still shapes the way we experience pop culture on the Internet to this day.\r\n\r\nReality Television and online gossip rags like TMZ, Perez Hilton and, Gawker are incredibly indebted to Paris and The Parises that followed her, whose layered expressions of narcissism and unapologetic fame-whoring on social media became a template for the way we film and write about celebrities, and provided good and bad examples of how to discuss delicate issues like sex tapes and addiction online.\r\n\r\nLuckily, the rise of the online media has seen a massive diversification of pop culture sites, many of which operate in the fashion and social spaces once dominated by the Hiltons of the world. Young <a href=\"http://www.dazeddigital.com/artsandculture/article/24497/1/the-teen-feminists-changing-the-world-in-2015\">women</a> like Tavi Gevinson, Amandla Stenberg, and even Taylor Swift illustrate that being glamourous doesnt mean you cant be smart as well.\r\n\r\nSwift, a proud cat lady, also likes to show off her pets on social media, but unlike the characteristically <i>catty</i> Paris, frequently shares her thoughts on the <a href=\"http://flavorwire.com/476139/in-defense-of-taylor-swifts-female-friendship-renaissance\">virtues</a> of female friendship and her gratitude to artistic peers and colleagues. Swift also seems to be a responsible cat owner and leaves <a href=\"http://www.etonline.com/news/155589_a_year_the_life_of_taylor_swift_cats/\">kitties</a> Olivia and Meredith home when she hits the clubs.\r\n\r\nRest in Peace, Tinkerbell. Every time we see a Tender Greens employee sadly scooping chihuahua poop from under a stiletto, we will think of you.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"\" src=\"http://i.kinja-img.com/gawker-media/image/upload/s--4hnoVh9---/18k1xitnky9zijpg.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"532\" height=\"299\" />\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend. Like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange  we scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest hanging fruit, and stick out after hours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Ding Dong, The Bitch is Dead','','publish','open','open','','ding-dong-the-bitch-is-dead','','','2015-04-25 11:48:56','2015-04-25 11:48:56','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=39',0,'post','',0),(40,5,'2015-04-24 22:38:23','2015-04-24 22:38:23','','U257413','Paris Hilton in Beverly Hills. Thursday, June 12, 2014','inherit','open','open','','u257413','','','2015-04-24 22:38:23','2015-04-24 22:38:23','',39,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/paris2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(41,5,'2015-04-24 22:38:59','2015-04-24 22:38:59','','gallery-1429668789-85491318','','inherit','open','open','','gallery-1429668789-85491318','','','2015-04-24 22:38:59','2015-04-24 22:38:59','',39,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/gallery-1429668789-85491318.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(42,5,'2015-04-24 22:39:24','2015-04-24 22:39:24','','Paris Hilton at the 2005 Gay Pride Parade in West Hollywood , CA','Paris Hilton at the 2005 Gay Pride Parade in West Hollywood , California . Paris was accompanied with her parents Kathy and Rick Hilton . She also had her pet chihuahua named \' Tinkerbell \' . <P> <B> Pictures by Jonathan Friolo / IHP / Splash News </B> <P> <B>Ref:  IHPLA FHLA 120605 A  </B> <P> <B>Splash News and Pictures</B><br> Los Angeles: 310-821-2666<br> New York: 212-619-2666<br> London: 207-107-2666<br> photodesk@splashnews.com','inherit','open','open','','paris-hilton-at-the-2005-gay-pride-parade-in-west-hollywood-ca','','','2015-04-24 22:39:24','2015-04-24 22:39:24','',39,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/paris_hilton.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(54,5,'2015-04-28 10:00:56','2015-04-28 10:00:56','As LA emerges from a brief grey streak, cut loose at one of our favorite parties, pop-ups, or performances. From steampunk song and dance to Cinco de Mayo psychedelia, this weeks picks ring Spring in with style.\r\n\r\n<b>Tuesday</b>\r\n\r\nInfuse a little movement in your work week at <b><i>Youre Working On What (aka Youre W.o.W?!)</i></b> a risky performance <a href=\"http://showboxla.org/2015/03/29/youre-w-o-w/\">show</a> at the Highland Park Ebell Club. SHOWBOX LA promises a night of dynamic dance and performance, where artists are invited to share excerpts from works in progress, experiment with form and impulse, and channel their weirdest and wackiest. While youre in the area, we recommend kicking the Gluten-Fear at Antigua Bread. Youll never look at a bean and cheese burrito the same way again.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_55\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"255\"]<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/cabaretawesome.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-55\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/cabaretawesome-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"Cabaret Awesome hosts  Joey Bybee and Lee Huff\" width=\"255\" height=\"255\" /></a> Cabaret Awesome hosts Joey Bybee and Lee Huff[/caption]\r\n\r\nOr, if youre craving steampunk seduction, swing by The Rockwell for a <a href=\"http://la.gaycities.com/events/490571-cabaret-awesome\">night</a> of edgy burlesque at <b>Cabaret Awesome</b>. Were not sure precisely what the retrofuturist festivities will entail  dances on 19th century industrial machinery? Pre-electric power?  Though the details aptly remain shrouded in smoke (and clanging), attendees are surely in for plenty of techno-victorian fantasy.\r\n\r\n<b>Wednesday</b>\r\n\r\nKick off your Wednesday with a little contemplation of the morbid at The Last Bookstores <strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/684056328366425/\">Death and Music</a></strong>. Though Author Paul Koudounaris has produced a glossy coffee table book in <i>Memento Mori: The Dead Among Us</i>, his passion project is equally filled with decay. The necrophiliac art historian is speaking about his work for one night only, and will be accompanied by a macabre slide show, plus live musical accompaniment and spoken word by auteur Dan Collins.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" alignright\" src=\"http://www.backyardopera.com/uploads/1/3/2/6/13265699/710606_orig.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"383\" height=\"255\" />\r\n\r\nThen, boogie on over to <strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/660963557363558/\">No Lights No Lycra Los Angeles</a></strong>, which takes all of the judgement away from your dance moves, and leaves you with nothing but the joy of movement. Started by a crew of inspired subterraneans dancing in the dark in the land Down Under, the latest Australian craze to hit Lalaland is about getting all of the accidental exercise out of music and movement, and shaking the embarrassment off the dance floor. Find yourself there for a delightfully sweaty hour or so.\r\n\r\n<b>Thursday</b>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_56\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"208\"]<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/pilar-zeta.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-56\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/pilar-zeta-218x300.jpg\" alt=\"Pilar Zeta\" width=\"208\" height=\"287\" /></a> Pilar Zeta[/caption]\r\n\r\nStop by The Ace for <b>Semiospheres</b>, WORK Magazines Issue 07 Release. In keeping with the issues focus on collaboration, the <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1725114724382365/\">party</a> will bring together prolific LA artists from myriad disciplines. The night will feature music by TIT, dance performance by Danny Dolan, DJ sets by Silent Servant &amp; Kid 606. Were hoping to catch <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/toddskiweaver\">Todd Weaver</a>s unique editorials, florals by <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/lanitrock\">Lani Trock</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pilar.zeta.artist\">Pilar Zeta</a>s retro-psychedelic geometries, and an installation by <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/suzy.poling\">Suzy Poling</a>.As space is limited, we recommend RSVPing in advance by emailing <a href=\"mailto:Info@theworkmag.com\">Info@theworkmag.com</a>.\r\n\r\nWhile youre downtown, head over the the Container Yard for <strong>LA Weekly\'s</strong><strong>Artopia</strong>, an art <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/400315903480066/\">popup</a> celebrating the paper\'sannual people issue. Confirmed artists include Victor Wilde and Bohemian Society, Mud Baron, Debi Cable. Mikael B., Amy Kaps, Marcus Kuiland-Nazario and Jeremy Sole. Vendors such as Arts District Printing Co., <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/Bigsqueezepress\">Big Squeeze Press</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/ChurchOfType\">Church of Type</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/cowpunkleatherproducts\">Cowpunk Leather Products</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/deja.vita\">DejaVita</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/detroit.trash\">Detroit Trash</a>, Downtown Muse, The Fenix, Fox Force Three,<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/HumanTreeRobot\">Humantreerobot</a> | <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/mark.s.brunner\">Mark S Brunner</a>, London Manori, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/MayuSilkArt\">Mayu Silk Art</a>, Pop &amp; Timber, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/RootsRevivalCo\">Roots Revival Co.</a>, SoCalEtsy, and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/bryaneaker\">Tin Man Art</a> will be hawking their wares - the event will also feature craft cocktails and snacks from some of LAs most beloved food trucks.\r\n\r\n<b>Friday</b>\r\n\r\nEgyptian-walk over to Nerdmelt for a comedy<a href=\"http://holdmyticket.com/event/203920\"> show</a> hosted by Bangle Susanna Hoffs. The aptly named Wheel Shows lineup appeals to chance and audience participation: volunteers spin a big-wheel on stage that determines what sketch, game, video, performance, or guest comes next. Though guests arent announced in advance, past stars have included Bob Odenkirk and Lisa Loeb - which should be more than enough to ignite your Eternal Flame.\r\n\r\n[embed]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Cv6tuzHUuuk[/embed]\r\n\r\n<b>Friday &amp; Saturday</b>\r\n\r\nLyft over to the arts district for a night of debauched delights and delectables at LAs largest pop-up underground art show, <b>Pancakes and Booze</b>. The vertically integrated <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1498531810426575/\">evening</a> promises body painting and an all-star line up  though you had us at ALL-U-CAN-EAT PANCAKES.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" alignright\" src=\"https://ksr-ugc.imgix.net/projects/1604916/photo-original.jpg?v=1421877596&amp;w=1536&amp;h=1152&amp;fit=crop&amp;auto=format&amp;q=92&amp;s=6b932563d2a816ba94db69a53c6e5dc5\" alt=\"\" width=\"341\" height=\"279\" />\r\n\r\nOr, join performance artist Ian Mackinnon on a multimedia <a href=\"http://gaymusicrevolution.bpt.me/\">tour</a> through the history of queer music - and the childhood of the author. The erotic quest, entitled <strong>Ian Mackinnons Gay Music Revolution,</strong> will take place at Spirit Studios and begin in the Classical Era - weve heard the performance travels through the jazz age to glam, punk, and disco. Mackinnon, who curates the annual Adonis Project, Homo-Harvest and the monthly performance night PLANET QUEER promises a rich lineup of raunchy song, dance, and LGBT history.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Sunday</b>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://scontent-sjc.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xfp1/v/t1.0-9/11182039_864333826972141_3334833072293834646_n.jpg?oh=5453f69eafd4e36541fed5c3100f5715&amp;oe=55C93A9F\"><img class=\" alignleft\" src=\"https://scontent-sjc.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xfp1/v/t1.0-9/11182039_864333826972141_3334833072293834646_n.jpg?oh=5453f69eafd4e36541fed5c3100f5715&amp;oe=55C93A9F\" alt=\"\" width=\"277\" height=\"277\" /></a>Saunter over to The Regent for the monthly <strong>Rock n Roll Flea Market</strong>. The <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1439321733032165/\">fair</a> will be populated by vintage clothing stores, antique dealers, jewelry makers, music memorabilia, vinyl, instruments and local food and crafts! Confirmed vendors include Hellhound Vintage, Phraseology and Biological Jewels. Entry is free if you eat at Profrock, and $2 otherwise - making the day a rockin bargain.\r\n\r\n<b>Monday</b>\r\n\r\nJoin in the Cinco de Mayo festivities with <a href=\"http://www.ticketweb.com/snl/EventListings.action?pl=lucha&amp;orgId=19940\">Lucha VaVOOM</a>, a psychedelic fiesta at the lavish Mayan Theater. We cant wait to party with the mariachis and folklorios - and get our tamale fix in. The show promises masked wrestling, Music, South-O-The-Border Striptease, Lowriders, Comedians, an aerial pole-star, and hula-hoopers to boot. We even hear there will be an amazing flying luchadore and ...psychedelic chickens?! This one may be a little pricier than our usual fare (tickets run $50) but with a diverse roster of performances and atmospheric environs, were dying to check it out. Hasta luego!\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend. Like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange  we scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest hanging fruit, and stick out after hours til the last last-call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>','Suicide Tuesdays 4/28','','publish','open','open','','suicide-tuesdays-428','','','2015-04-28 03:09:08','2015-04-28 03:09:08','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=54',0,'post','',0),(55,5,'2015-04-28 02:21:26','2015-04-28 02:21:26','','cabaretawesome','Cabaret Awesome hosts  Joey Bybee and Lee Huff','inherit','open','open','','cabaretawesome','','','2015-04-28 02:21:43','2015-04-28 02:21:43','',54,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/cabaretawesome.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(56,5,'2015-04-28 02:45:35','2015-04-28 02:45:35','','pilar-zeta','Pilar Zeta','inherit','open','open','','pilar-zeta','','','2015-04-28 02:45:38','2015-04-28 02:45:38','',54,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/pilar-zeta.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(68,5,'2015-05-05 10:00:08','2015-05-05 10:00:08','<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Screen-Shot-2015-05-05-at-1.23.40-PM.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-94 alignright\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Screen-Shot-2015-05-05-at-1.23.40-PM-300x226.png\" alt=\"via Instagram: Kim Kardashian \" width=\"300\" height=\"226\" /></a>\r\n\r\nMet Gala FOMO got you down? Don\'t worry.\r\n\r\nThis week, we\'ve got burlesque, brews, movie nights and afterhours for you Subterraneans. Here are our favorite events to get you through your weekday slump.\r\n\r\n<b>Tuesday</b>\r\n\r\nJoin UCLAs Dr. Jan-Christopher Horak for <b>Forbidden Films</b>, a <a href=\"http://www.goethe.de/ins/us/los/ver/en14248343v.htm\">showing</a> and critical discussion of Nazi propaganda films of the Third Reich. Sponsored by the LA Jewish Film Festival, the talk will address these fraught works and if  and <i>how</i> they should be viewed and discussed as historical artifacts in Germany and beyond.\r\n\r\nOr, head down Vermont and towards Emerald City for a <b>Journey To The Land Of Oz</b>, a burlesque <a href=\"http://www.hollywoodjanerevue.com/upcoming-shows/\">interpretation</a> of the wiz. Attendees are encouraged to call (323) 661-6163 ext. 20. for tickets as space is limited. No ruby slippers required (though they never hurt).\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1024\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://www.hollywoodjanerevue.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Journey-To-Oz-1024x404.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1024\" height=\"404\" /> via the Hollywood Jane Revnue[/caption]\r\n\r\n<b>Wednesday</b>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"271\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://manomuzika.lt/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/record-player-vintage-vinyl.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"271\" height=\"180\" /> via Mano Muzika[/caption]\r\n\r\nGo analog at <b>Vinyl in the Valley</b>, a free BYO (records that is) community listening <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/e/vinyl-in-the-valley-byo-vinyl-tickets-16070405014?aff=es2\">party</a> whose spontaneous set is determined by the selection of records brought by partygoers. Whether youre a vinyl aficionado or just looking for a chance to wipe the dust off those 45s your dad keeps giving you, the party is a great chance to mingle, sip beer and wine and cool off to some tunes mid-week.\r\n\r\n<b>Thursday</b>\r\n\r\n<img class=\" alignleft\" src=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-e70CnO3d4p8/Ty2zgmIo9-I/AAAAAAAAAmk/aToFejNKliY/s1600/bureau_pic2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"479\" height=\"246\" />\r\n\r\nFirst, head over to Chinatowns Poetic Research Bureau for a <a href=\"http://www.poeticresearch.com/\">reading</a> from <b>Kristen Gallagher </b>and <b>Chris Alexander.</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Friday</b>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"278\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://41.media.tumblr.com/db2d691fa166d5818281eb904719d750/tumblr_nlogunk5io1rnfqt4o1_500.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"278\" height=\"417\" /> Winking Cat, Bryn Perrott. 2015.[/caption]\r\n\r\nStop by the pskaufman gallery for <b>uprooted strata</b>, a show of woodworkings, print, and sculpture from artist Bryn Perrott (deerjerk). Were excited to check out Bryns latest and the brand new venue, which describes itself as a multi-function subterranean space. If the crafty carvings leave you with a desire to hack apart a tree trunk of your own, dont worry - Bryn is hosting two hour workshops Saturday and Sunday at the gallery for $60, which includes wood and tools and the one-of-a-kind experience of learning from the master carver.\r\n\r\nStill wide awake? Night owls head to a <a href=\"http://www.brownpapertickets.com/event/1470830\">midnight screening of <b>Weird Science</b></a>, especially if you like your movies with a side of original actors - anticipate audience discussion with the guy who played Wyatt himself, <b>Ilan Micheal Smith</b>. With the threat of awards for era-appropriate costumes, anticipate joining a crowd of rampant enthusiasts potentially clad in head-bras, baben bandage dresses and huge hair.\r\n\r\nThen, keep the night going (and going) with Londons <b>Floating Points</b> at <b>Far Away</b>s all-night afterhours <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1406726009637240/\">party</a>. RSVP to Restless Nights for details &amp; the secret location.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Saturday</b>\r\n\r\nSaturday nights alright for fighting in our book. Pick your battle: you can stop by Spoken Funks <b>Fight of The Century and The Funk of The Century </b>for a funky spoken word <a href=\"http://spokenfunk.com/\">tte--tte</a>, or cruise through Electric Dust Drive-In to watch machismo dudes hash out their anti-capitalist qualms at an atmospheric <a href=\"https://www.ticketfly.com/purchase/event/782987\">showing</a> of <b>Fight Club</b>.\r\n\r\nAfterwards, head on over to Glendale for <b>Moony Habits\'</b>inaugural monthly party to check out sets from<b> Falty DL</b>, <b>MONO/POLY</b>, <b>Mike Gao</b> and resident <b>JoJo Armani.</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Sunday</b>\r\n\r\n<img class=\" alignleft\" src=\"http://40.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lbn02ukyc81qbwgnmo1_1280.jpg#_=_\" alt=\"\" width=\"464\" height=\"402\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLooking for Mothers Day relief after a long morning of maternal love? Pick up a beer and put BBQ in the other hand at <b>Dyke Day LA</b>s <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1629004043988943/\">fundraiser</a>, and remember that your busy hands still leave room for spanking services provided by <b>Mistress Justine Cross</b>. Boot blacking also available. Keep a kinky sizzle on all afternoon, and raise money to boot? Yes please, mommy.\r\n\r\n<b>Monday</b>\r\n\r\nIf you havent gotten enough sunny days indoors in, take this one south of the border to Mexico, for <a href=\"http://www.theregenttheater.com/event/802953-mexrrissey-mexico-goes-los-angeles/\"><b>Mexirressey</b></a>. From <b>The Smiths</b> to the man himself, see Latin artists gather from all over to bring their own interpretations of classic Morrissey with the addition of horns and accordions, and even a little Spanish-language reinterpretation. Get in there and ask: Qu Tan Pronto Es Ahora?\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend. Like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange  we scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest hanging fruit, and stick out after hours til the last last-call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>','Suicide Tuesdays 5/5','','publish','open','open','','suicide-tuesdays-55','','','2015-05-14 00:30:11','2015-05-14 00:30:11','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=68',0,'post','',0),(79,5,'2015-05-01 10:30:34','2015-05-01 10:30:34','With uprisings in Baltimore following the death of Freddie Gray in police custody, this week was a good ole fashioned media-shitstorm of think pieces, editorials, and angry status updates.\r\n\r\nWhile many posted the words of Dr. Martin Luther King, <a href=\"http://www.esquire.com/news-politics/a3638/fifth-avenue-uptown/\">those</a> of James Baldwin seemed to us to be equally significant and timeless, and far more apt introduction to the weeks social-media blitz as any we could construct.\r\n\r\nBenji Hart at<b> Salon</b> took a generous <a href=\"http://www.salon.com/2015/04/28/baltimores_violent_protesters_are_right_smashing_police_cars_is_a_legitimate_political_strategy/\">look</a> at the difficult conditions and tactics facing Baltimore protesters, while many cracked open the <b>Baltimore Sun</b>s investigation of police using undue <a href=\"http://data.baltimoresun.com/news/police-settlements/\">force</a> in the city.\r\n\r\nWe learned how we can help - not only by sharing ethical and well-reported stories with our friends on social media, but also by contributing to worthwhile causes like <b>Rethinking Schools</b>, an <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/rethinkingschools?hc_location=ufi\">organization</a> that works to educate inner-city students about social justice.\r\n\r\nFollowing Bruce Jenners Diane Sawyer interview over the weekend, <b>Dazed</b> <a href=\"http://www.dazeddigital.com/artsandculture/article/24522/1/trans-trailblazers\">spotlit</a> important transgender trailblazers less known outside the mainstream.\r\n\r\n<b>N+1</b>s Agata Pyzik addressed aesthetic and class differences that often pit different forms feminism in opposition in a thorough literary <a href=\"https://nplusonemag.com/online-only/book-review/in-praise-of-vulgar-feminism-2/\">review</a> of Kim Gordons recent memoir.\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, the men of pop music got touchy-feely, at least according to <a href=\"http://pitchfork.com/thepitch/753-drake-kanye-1d-and-the-rise-of-emotional-men/\"><b>Pitchfork</b></a>.\r\n\r\n<b>Meryl Streep</b> <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/apr/20/meryl-streep-screenwriting-initiative-women-over-40-writers-lab\">announced</a> an exciting screenwriting initiative for women over 40 while <b>Rose Byrne</b> and <b>Lena Dunham</b> <a href=\"http://blogs.indiewire.com/womenandhollywood/lena-dunham-and-rose-byrne-launch-all-female-production-companies-20150423\">launched</a> all female production companies of their own.\r\n\r\nWhen theres an industry devoid of women, theres a tendency for women to feel like they have to protect their spot, like theres not enough room in town for both of us, Dunham told <b>Indiewire</b>. We need to break that down and support each other, because as my dad always says, A rising tide lifts all boats. ... Its our job as women who have been given a certain amount of success and visibility to pull other women along with us.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, feminist efforts didnt extend to legislation, as <b>Michigan House Representatives</b> <a href=\"http://www.mlive.com/lansing-news/index.ssf/2015/04/michigan_house_passes_379_bill.html\">cut</a> much needed funds for Planned Parenthood and Conservative Supreme Court <b>Justice Scalia</b> <a href=\"http://nymag.com/news/features/antonin-scalia-2013-10/\">told</a> New York Magazine that many of societys problems today might be lessened if all those rabble rousing modern women werent cavorting around f-bombs - well stick with the always wise and occasionally <a href=\"http://dailycaller.com/2015/02/13/justice-ginsburg-was-drunk-at-state-of-the-union/\">tipsy</a> <b>Judge Ginsberg</b> on this one, who went to bat for Gay Marriage at Tuesdays hearing on the constitutionality of <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/society/gay-marriage\">gay marriage</a>.\r\n\r\nMarriage today is not what it was under the common law tradition, under the civil law tradition, Ginsburg responded to Justices Roberts and Kennedys worries about challenging the historical institution of marriage - remarks that also seem quite applicable to other social issues that have arisen this week and the argument that history is best left unchallenged.\r\n\r\nMarriage was a relationship of a dominant male to a subordinate female, she explained. That ended as a result of this courts decision in 1982 when Louisianas Head and Master Rule was struck down  Would that be a choice that state should [still] be allowed to have? To cling to marriage the way it once was?\r\n\r\nMeanwhile<b>, The Huffington Post</b> gave much deserved <a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/04/24/beach-body-ads-each-body-is-ready_n_7138770.html\">props</a> to NYCs guerilla feminist efforts to take on a body-shaming ad campaign, while <b>The Kernel</b> looked to performance art and medicine as to what gadgets and artificial limbs the human <a href=\"http://kernelmag.dailydot.com/issue-sections/features-issue-sections/12705/vitruvian-man-body-hacking-infographic/?fb=dd\">body</a> may soon be flaunting.\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend. Like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange  we scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest hanging fruit, and stick out after hours til the last last-call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>','Thank Fuck It\'s Friday 5/1','','publish','open','open','','thank-fuck-its-friday-may-day-edition','','\nhttps://nplusonemag.com/online-only/book-review/in-praise-of-vulgar-feminism-2/','2015-05-07 23:38:55','2015-05-07 23:38:55','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=79',0,'post','',0),(82,5,'2015-05-01 17:37:08','2015-05-01 17:37:08','','ruthbadergin2','via The Washington Post','inherit','open','open','','ruthbadergin2','','','2015-05-23 19:10:03','2015-05-23 19:10:03','',79,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/ruthbadergin2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(88,5,'2015-05-05 01:35:38','2015-05-05 01:35:38','','4975032820_3c6299e44f_o','Romaine Decker','inherit','open','open','','4975032820_3c6299e44f_o','','','2015-05-05 01:36:19','2015-05-05 01:36:19','',68,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/4975032820_3c6299e44f_o.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(94,5,'2015-05-05 20:26:12','2015-05-05 20:26:12','','Screen Shot 2015-05-05 at 1.23.40 PM','via Instagram: Kim Kardashian ','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-05-05-at-1-23-40-pm','','','2015-05-05 20:26:24','2015-05-05 20:26:24','',68,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Screen-Shot-2015-05-05-at-1.23.40-PM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(97,5,'2015-05-08 10:00:05','2015-05-08 10:00:05','For this week\'s roundup, we\'ve decided to do something a little different. Here at Walk the Night HQ, we\'ve been talking a lot aboutwhat jams get us going and push us through our afternoon slumps, so we thought, what better way to share them than a playlist of some of the baddest bitches around?\r\n\r\nOur<strong> \"Come on Girls\"</strong> playlist celebrates brave and powerful women across genres and industries and certainly isn\'t exhaustive or just for the girls - these are just a few of our favorites. We\'ve got more playlists to come - watch for disco, hip-hop,city-specific ones and more,or even better, shoot us a <a href=\"mailto:press@lamother.com\">line</a> to let us know what you like to groove to when you\'re kicking ass or just holding out for the weekend.\r\n\r\nWhile some of our feminist anthems are from riot grrl bands like Bikini Kill, who openly aimed to challenge gender roles and championed female-empowerment in lyrics and interviews, others like Erykah Badu have openly revoked the feminist label in favor of another term or none at all. Here are some of the songs that get us amped to take on the world in style.\r\n\r\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLAnM9YAqoTmgMZaCXNM5KO-4sZHQUpfZu[/embed]\r\n\r\n<b>Track List:</b>\r\n\r\nBeginning Come on girls, <b>Madonna</b>s Express Yourself reminds women to find real love, not compromise or settle for cheapened materialized expressions of love.\r\n\r\nIn Entertain <b>Sleater Kinney</b> takes on the doubleness of the (oft-sexualized) attention experienced by female public figures, artists, and women generally. Though the all-girl trio might not be at anyones beck and call but their own, the song manages to be just as catchy and fun as it a riotous declaration of independent womanhood.\r\n\r\nIn Holy Matrimony (Letter to the Firm) hip-hop queen <b>Foxy Brown</b> spits fiercely about an unconventional union with her hip-hop supergroup. Whether you agree with Foxys form of female empowerment or her lifestyle, which seems to involve a lot of drug-dealing, her matriarchal rhymes take on uncharted territory, especially in the often-male-dominated world of hip-hop.\r\n\r\nEpic grunge poetess <b>Courtney Love</b> takes on female pain and objectification in Doll Parts singing:\r\n\r\n<i>I want to be the girl with the most cake</i>\r\n\r\n<i>He only loves those things because he loves to see them break</i>\r\n\r\n<i>I fake it so real I am beyond fake</i>\r\n\r\n<i>And someday you will ache like I ache</i>\r\n\r\nCourtneys starkly honest lyrics remind us that feminism isnt all sleepovers, girl power, and sex-positivity - and it doesnt free us from loneliness, pain, or abuse. However, she also reminds us the importance of art, which allows us to speak about pain in novel and powerful ways, even if they cannot fully eradicate it.\r\n\r\n<b>Janelle Monae</b>s Electric Lady is a testament to empowered femininity, addressing a woman who knows who she is and knows how to get down - whats better than that?\r\n\r\nGimme a beat! <b>Janet Jackson</b>s Nasty tells us not to make any time for nasty boys, and that asking for respect doesnt make you a prude.\r\n\r\n<b>Fiona Apple</b> reclaims her #dirtyword in Fast As You Can, riffing on the experience and stigma of mental illness and speaking honestly about its effect on her relationships. I get to the place where my mind dont shake and shift/but most of the time it does Apple sings harrowingly, reminding us of that the beast within can also be harnessed as a source of power and not shame.\r\n\r\n<b>Chaka Khan</b>s Im Every Woman is a testament to eternal femininity and the links that join female experience, from A to Z.\r\n\r\nIn Gloria Godmother of Punk <b>Patti Smith</b> owns her sins, body, and experience, and carvesout a form of sex appeal that has nothing to do with male gaze or showing T&amp;A, and everything to do with being yourself.\r\n\r\nNext, icon <b>Ani Difranco</b> tells a story about love and friendship and heartbreak between women, saying love is a piano dropped from a four story window/and you were at the wrong place at the wrong time. While Two Little Girls isnt a story about or featuring men, its power is amplified because it doesnt include them or talk about her relationship through the lens of heterosexual love or male judgement.\r\n\r\n<b>Donna Summer</b> changed the dance music landscape for women with with I Feel Love and created an anthem championed by the queer community. David Bowie says: One day in Berlin ... Eno came running in and said, \"I have heard the sound of the future. He puts on \"I Feel Love,\" by Donna Summer ... He said, \"This is it, look no further. This single is going to change the sound of club music for the next fifteen years.\" Which was more or less right.\" Though Bowie and Eno endorsements certainly dont hurt, her performance speaks for itself.\r\n\r\nIn Hit Em Up Style <b>Blu Cantrell</b> sasilly details a fantasy shopping spree on her cheating exs dime - instead of tying her down, the group playfully turns financial dependence on a spouse into metaphorical vehicle that moves away from it.\r\n\r\nLegend<b> Nina Simone</b> begins Aint Got No - I Got Life with listing the possessions, education, privilege, and experiences she doesnt have, but by the end of the song she has wholly reclaimed her experience of her life as her own, saying Ive got life and nobodys going to take it away.\r\n\r\nIn Queen, <b>Janelle Monae &amp; Erykah Badu</b> speak powerfully about self-love and identity asking Will you be electric sheep? Electric ladies, will you sleep? Or will you preach?\" As much as it is a feminist anthem, the song reminds us that spiritual rhetoric can take on myriad forms, and there\'s nothing wrong with preaching what you believe in.\r\n\r\nIn Fuck the Pain Away <b>Peaches</b> gave a voice to sex-positive feminism, turning the machismo reputation of electronic music on its head. The electroclash troubadours sexually explicit and demanding lyrics were seen as genuinely shocking at the time, and the teaches of peaches paved the way for artists like Rihanna and Lady Gaga to be open about their sexual appetites.\r\n\r\n<b>Joan Jett </b>doesnt give a damn about her reputation, and reminds us neither should we in the anthemic 1980 hit. Later, the song was picked up as the theme for 90s teen show Freaks and Geeks. When the show became a cult classic, it brought Bad Reputation and the singer/songwriter/guitarist into the cultural consciousness of yet another generation of badass rocker chicks.\r\n\r\nIn the eponymous Doo Wop (That Thing) <b>Lauryn Hill</b> reminds men and women about the importance of being yourself, casting materialism aside, and being about more than just sex and money. <em>Don\'t be a hard rock when you really are a gem, baby girl.</em>\r\n\r\n<b>Stevie Nicks</b> Rooms on Fire speaks to Nicks journey accepting her own experience of womanhood. Nicks told an interviewer Rooms on Fire is about a girl who goes through a life like I have gone through, where she finally accepts the idea that there never will be those other things in her life. She will never be married, she will never have children, she will never do those [that] part of life.\r\n\r\n<b>Grimes</b> single Oblivion made a massive splash that echoed through pop culture and beyond it, but were just as crazy about the singers feminist ethos. \"I don\'t want to be infantilized because i refuse to be sexualized,\" she writes. \"I don\'t want to be molested at shows or on the street by people who perceive me as an object that exists for their personal satisfaction.\"\r\n\r\nIn Family Affair, <b>Mary J. Blige</b> teams up with Dr. Dre, inviting everyone to dance and get crunk in a no hateration, drama-free zone. As Mary J says, leave all that BS outside and get it percolatin.\r\n\r\nLast but not least, Bikini Kills <b>Rebel Girl </b>is a love letter to a feminist icon and the movement, in a narrative centered around empowerment and friendship.\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend. Like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange  we scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest hanging fruit, and stick out after hours til the last last-call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>','Thank Fuck It\'s Friday 5/8','','publish','open','open','','thank-fuck-its-friday-58','','','2015-05-08 00:15:24','2015-05-08 00:15:24','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=97',0,'post','',0),(100,5,'2015-05-08 00:11:10','2015-05-08 00:11:10','','6200829305_f1b9497e21_b','NY Slutwalk 2011 via David Shankbone','inherit','open','open','','6200829305_f1b9497e21_b','','','2015-05-08 00:11:48','2015-05-08 00:11:48','',97,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/6200829305_f1b9497e21_b.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(105,5,'2015-05-12 10:00:42','2015-05-12 10:00:42','This weeks nightlife pickings skew arty, erotic, and ripe with energetic performance - from drag, to metal, to dressed-up TVand dressed-downTV satire.While a few of our luxury splashings might trigger a tinge of nightlife-envyamong some of you thriftier subterraneans, we\'ve also included our favoritefree and low cost performances and showings - so your nights can stay full, even whenyou\'re pockets are looking a <em>little</em> feeble.\r\n\r\n<strong>Tuesday</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\" alignleft\" src=\"https://scontent-lax.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xap1/v/t1.0-9/1472998_813697155387237_4703371602684652785_n.jpg?oh=b817c7286daec1cbac8b8ef5fe96a5a9&amp;oe=55C20B1A\" alt=\"\" width=\"207\" height=\"286\" />\r\n\r\nWorkout your best head-banging moves, then thrash your way towards<strong>The Viper Room</strong> for <strong>Black Sabbitch</strong>, THE All Female Black Sabbath take over. Each Tuesday <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/361607360711947/\">show</a>is rich with savage girl-power and features a different set of classic Sabbath tracks, plus special guests, original songsand more. After all, what\'s more face-meltingly #metal than <em>~the element of surprise~</em>?!\r\n\r\n<strong>Wednesday</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_112\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"224\"]<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/dolphin-dream2015.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-112\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/dolphin-dream2015-293x300.jpg\" alt=\"Jim Drain, Dolphin Dream, 2015, Acrylic, colored pencil on paper, and mixed materials on burlap, 65 x 65 in\" width=\"224\" height=\"229\" /></a> Jim Drain, Dolphin Dream, 2015.[/caption]\r\n\r\nIf you\'re feeling a little boxed-in after oogling <strong>Jim Drain</strong>\'s edgy geometrics at the artist\'s Highland Park\'s <strong>Seems/Seams</strong> <a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/event/jim-drain-seems-sems-5563006\">exhibition</a>head over the pond via west towards Santa Monica for<em><strong>Westside</strong><strong>Abbey</strong></em>- hey! where are you going? Santa Monicaisn\'t <em>that</em> far! It\'ll be fine. Just use Waze.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Thursday</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\" alignleft\" src=\"http://www.trbimg.com/img-532ca0d4/turbine/tn-gnp-dvd-review-the-hidden-fortress-released-001/2000/2000x1336\" alt=\"\" width=\"259\" height=\"173\" />\r\n\r\nJoin your fellow-cinephiles at the Linwood Dunn Theater, as you prepareto <a href=\"http://www.themirrorcube.com/event/the-hidden-fortress-linwood-dunn-theater-la\">enter</a><strong>The Hidden Fortress -</strong>which, in this case, is located in 16th century rural Japan.The director\'s debut work is not only a fan-favorite among Kurosawa buffs an art-house afficianados, but also well-loved by Star Wars fans, as \"The Hidden Fortress\" is widely considered one of George Lucas\'s formative filmic influences.\r\n\r\n<strong>Friday</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\" alignright\" src=\"https://scontent-lax.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xap1/v/t1.0-9/11206964_1596406697283229_5064785370247340248_n.jpg?oh=692d79d80937a34a542679cd71eb2814&amp;oe=55CC51FC\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" />\r\n\r\nRing the weekendin feline-style at <strong>The Catnip Club\'s Swim Club</strong> debut, an afternoon and eveningofpleasure, dips, and disco with Hollywood\'scoolest subterranean cats and kittens. We\'re told pussies will be wet and mimosas flowin\' - as<a href=\"http://thecatnipclub.com/membership/swim-club\">tickets</a>are going fast, we advise you reserve yours early if you don\'t want to be a housecat come Friday night.\r\n\r\nWe are here, we are queer! -say <strong>John Early</strong>(<em>Broad City</em>, <em>30 Rock</em>, <em>High Maintenance</em>) and Brooklyn drag icon<strong><a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/01/12/hamm-samwich-brooklyn_n_4557336.html\">Hamm Samwich</a></strong>. Or, at least that\'s the gist of it. The dynamic duo will hit <strong>The Virgil</strong> for <strong>JOHN</strong><strong>HAMM: LA,</strong> afeisty Friday evening<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/781947338593617/\">performance</a>that promisesa gay-old time to be had byall. The evening is perhapsbest described by its stars, the self-identified OUT 100-snubbed gay icons themselves, who\'ve dubbedit anan exclusive, one-night-only LA event, \"a shameless ploy for visibility\" and \"FREE AS HELL.\"\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/3853424889_eb2468830c_o.jpg\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-114 alignleft\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/3853424889_eb2468830c_o-300x225.jpg\" alt=\"3853424889_eb2468830c_o\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>\r\n\r\nIf Saturday night is alright with you, why not hip-thrust your way over to ask What else is in the Teaches of Peaches? Former elementary school pedagogue turned electroqueer star, Peaches, is signing a photographic book of the artists performances, captured by the talents of Berlin-based photographer, Holger Talinski. Paw the books pages for evocative and erotic images from across the world, with added textual contributions by Peaches herself, as well as Michael Stipe (R.E.M.), Yoko Ono, and Ellen Page.\r\n\r\nThen, crawl away from the pulsing clutches of Peaches, and into a subterranean graveyard. Though fans of the bizarrecultclassic span far beyond the city of angels, David Lynch\'s LA movies are particularly beloved among locals -hey, we love seeing spooky shit go down on familiar streets!<strong><a href=\"http://cinespia.org/event/mulholland-dr/\">Mullholland Drive</a></strong>will be shown on the huge screen in the Hollywood Forever cemetery. Dining amongst the dead, creepiness aside (take a picnic to best relish the night), where better to watch such an LA classic than surrounded by starlets from all ages of classic Hollywood? Knowing <strong>Cinespia</strong>s pull, keep your eyes peeled for a movie star or film-maker making an appearance or even saying a few words post-screening.\r\n\r\n<strong>Sunday</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/peggyswag.jpg\"><img class=\"  wp-image-117 alignright\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/peggyswag-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"peggyswag\" width=\"379\" height=\"214\" /></a>If the weekend hasn\'t left you totally skint, throw on your sassiest60shousedress or 70s slacks and let your mustache inch past its usual cut-off point foran <a href=\"http://www.timeout.com/los-angeles/things-to-do/mad-men-live-read-series-finale#tab_panel_3\">exclusive</a> <strong>Mad Men live-read and showingatThe Ace. </strong>The night will kick off with a live read of the show\'s Season 1 finale before the main event,a star-studded showing of this week\'sfinal chapter. If you\'re worried about spending the finalecurled up with a box of tissues and ad-hoc rendering of Don Draper\'s box of stolen war memorabilia, don\'t fret - the night\'s festivities are in expert hands,hosted by Mad Men creator Matthew Weiner and director Jason Reitmanwithshow regulars Jon Hamm, January Jones, Elisabeth Moss, John Slattery and Kiernan Shipka filling out the bill. For those of you new to Sterling-Cooper-Draper-whatsitcalled, that\'s Don, Betty, Peggy, Sally, and WTN favorite ROGER STERLING. Astickets are somewhat steep and reportedly scarce, it\'s worth scoping one out in advance, or even breaking out the rolodex to look for someonehawking anextra invite. If there\'s ever a good reason to blow your paycheck on martinis, this seems like the one...\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday &amp; Sunday</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Screen-Shot-2015-05-12-at-1.43.36-AM.png\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-129 alignleft\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Screen-Shot-2015-05-12-at-1.43.36-AM-297x300.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-05-12 at 1.43.36 AM\" width=\"297\" height=\"300\" /></a>Sashay your way to <a href=\"http://rupaulsdragcon.com/\"><strong>RuPauls DragCon</strong></a> this weekend: the first of its kind! Anticipate your favorites from the reality show to be present and oh so fabulous dahling. Expect to be getting your booty bouncing with azz everywhere, as the amazing Queen Diva of Bounce music and RuPaul auditory collaborator, Big Freedia, makes a showing you wont easily shake off. Even though his dance troupe will have you trying your hardest. Film screenings, panels and presentations as well as some extra special drag celebrity sightings should round out your weekend of camp extravaganza!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Monday</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\" alignright\" src=\"http://static.stereogum.com/uploads/2014/12/lana-del-rey-courtney-love.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"597\" height=\"594\" />\r\n\r\nShake off the blue Mondays with a dose of multi-generational girl power from sassy songstresses <strong>Courtney Love</strong> and <strong>Lana Del Rey</strong>.\r\n\r\nThe aptly named (for Los Angeles at least) Endless Summer tour will visit <strong>The Hollywood Bowl</strong>for a likely-sweltering<a href=\"http://www.ticketmaster.com/event/0B004D74BBDB244D&amp;brand=hollywoodbowl\">night</a>of edgy song and performancefrom the twoiconic bad girls. While they seem to have squashed the <a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/07/31/courtney-love-lana-del-rey-heart-shaped-box_n_1723074.html\">beef</a>, we\'re betting against eitherheart-shaped box making a live appearance.\r\n\r\nHey, it\'s not Hole, but it\'ll do.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend. Like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange  we scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest hanging fruit, and stick out after hours til the last last-call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>','Suicide Tuesdays 5/12','','publish','open','open','','suicide-tuesdays-512','','','2015-05-14 01:22:29','2015-05-14 01:22:29','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=105',0,'post','',0),(112,5,'2015-05-12 08:02:20','2015-05-12 08:02:20','','dolphin dream2015','Jim Drain, Dolphin Dream, 2015, Acrylic, colored pencil on paper, and mixed materials on burlap, 65 x 65 in','inherit','open','open','','dolphin-dream2015','','','2015-05-12 08:02:25','2015-05-12 08:02:25','',105,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/dolphin-dream2015.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(114,5,'2015-05-12 08:11:24','2015-05-12 08:11:24','','3853424889_eb2468830c_o','','inherit','open','open','','3853424889_eb2468830c_o','','','2015-05-12 08:11:24','2015-05-12 08:11:24','',105,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/3853424889_eb2468830c_o.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(116,5,'2015-05-12 08:15:31','2015-05-12 08:15:31','screencap from David Lynch\'s \"Muholland Drive\" via blogspot','mulholland drive','','inherit','open','open','','mulholland-drive','','','2015-05-12 08:16:34','2015-05-12 08:16:34','',105,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mulholland-drive.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(117,5,'2015-05-12 08:18:13','2015-05-12 08:18:13','\"Mad Men\" screencap courtesy of Paige Elizabeth Gresty','peggyswag','','inherit','open','open','','peggyswag','','','2015-05-12 08:20:58','2015-05-12 08:20:58','',105,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/peggyswag.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(129,5,'2015-05-12 08:44:20','2015-05-12 08:44:20','','Screen Shot 2015-05-12 at 1.43.36 AM','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-05-12-at-1-43-36-am','','','2015-05-12 08:44:20','2015-05-12 08:44:20','',105,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Screen-Shot-2015-05-12-at-1.43.36-AM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(142,5,'2015-05-15 10:00:52','2015-05-15 10:00:52','Whether you\'re twisting the <a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/2015/05/12/suicide-tuesdays-512/\">night</a> away with drag queens or mourning Mad Men, we\'ve picked out yourperfect weekendrequired reading. Peruse some of our favorite articles while you primp for Friday after hours,trim your whiskers for The Catnip Club\'sMob Happy Houror flake on that Sunday brunch.\r\n\r\nThis week, Anna F. at <b>Rookie </b>told us<b></b>how to combat Spring Fever and get your <a href=\"http://www.rookiemag.com/2015/05/create/\">creative</a> juices flowing, while <b>Akiliah Hughes </b>explainedthat black culture isnt about white acceptance. In a smart and gracious piece on the <a href=\"http://abcnews.go.com/US/blackoutday-trending-twitter-hashtag-celebrates-black-people-fights/story?id=29439319\">Blackout Day of March 6</a>, the author<b></b>explains that being an ally sometimes means knowing it isnt your turn to talk, reflecting,\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em>Our society still has loads of unlearning to do when it comes to racist and damaging stereotypes. Racism is more than hurting my feelings, it affects the way the gatekeepers of the world<a href=\"http://thinkprogress.org/education/2014/06/25/3452887/education-race-gap/\">employers</a>, <a href=\"http://www.npr.org/blogs/codeswitch/2014/03/21/292456211/black-preschoolers-far-more-likely-to-be-suspended\">educators</a>,<a href=\"https://medium.com/sportspickle/the-nfl-s-10-most-racist-head-coaches-b6172ef58870\">coaches</a>, <a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/news/african-americans-are-far-less-likely-to-get-home-loans-in-la-5378138\">landlords</a>, the entire infrastructuresees and treats me. And there are huge privileges in passing as white in a world that values lighter skin above all other shades. Representation matters, and seeing people who look like you in media not only affects the way you see yourself, but the way others see you.</em></p>\r\n<strong>Everyday Feminism</strong>\'s<strong>Luna Merbruja</strong> told us how cisgender feminists can make spaces and language more trans inclusive and <a href=\"http://everydayfeminism.com/2015/05/feminist-phrases-marginalize-trans-women/\">which</a>well-intentioned\"feminist phrases\" conveytransmisogyny.\r\n\r\nOver at <strong>The New Yorker</strong>, <strong>Sheila Heti</strong> <a href=\"http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2015/05/11/my-life-is-a-joke\">answered</a> an age old question inher wry, riveting and ultimately quite serious short story, \"My Life IsA Joke.\" The author writes:\r\n<p class=\"descender\"><em>When a person slips on a banana peel and dies, then her life is a joke. Slipping on a banana peel is not how I died. When a person walks into a bar with a rabbi, a priest, and a nun, and that is how she dies, then her life is a joke. That is not how I died. When a person is a chicken who crosses the road to get to the other side, and that is how she dies, then her life is a joke. Well, that is how I diedas a chicken crossing the road to get to the other side.</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"descender\">Need to infuse a dose of sass into your twitter feed? <strong>The Frisky</strong> told us<a href=\"http://Need to infuse a dose of sass into your twitter feed? The Frisky told which 25 funny feminists to follow next.\">which</a> 25 funny feminists to follow next.</p>\r\nIn <strong>Mic</strong>s <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/MicMedia/videos/vb.174742062548592/926404477382343/?type=1&amp;theater\"><i>Flip the Script</i></a> video star<b>Elizabeth Plank</b> shed<b></b>a sarcastic light on women who opt not to have children. Even though the Pope went on record saying women who dont reproduce are Selfish, <strong>Plank</strong> goes on to interview <b>Susan Mcpherson, </b>a successful CEO who chose not to bear children with the bottom line of, <em>do what you want</em>.\r\n\r\nThough well watch anything starring talented bombshell AND equal pay <a href=\"http://hollywoodlife.com/2015/01/08/charlize-theron-demands-equal-pay-chris-hemsworth-10-million/\">advocate</a><b> Charlize Theron</b>,<strong> Vice</strong>s <strong>David Perry</strong> broke down exactly what makes the new <i>Mad Max </i>a badass feminist <a href=\"http://www.vice.com/read/the-new-mad-max-movie-is-both-badass-and-totally-feminist-944\">flick</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Slate</strong> <a href=\"http://www.slate.com/blogs/xx_factor/2015/04/24/hillary_clinton_s_first_campaign_speech_it_s_all_about_feminism.html\">dissected</a> Hilary Clinton\'s feminist campaign rhetoric, writing:\r\n\r\n<em>The political chatter is centered around how Clinton isn\'t downplaying her gender, as she did in 2008, but holding it up as an asset. This speech suggests she is running an aggressively feminist campaign. It\'s a smart move. Her opposition is going to try to paint her as a ball-busting \"feminazi\" no matter what she does, so she might as well get ahead of them, openly embracing feminism, sharing a vision of feminism that is optimistic and pro-family. Luckily, she has a more accurate vision of what feminism is really about than her detractors do.</em>\r\n\r\nSick of looking at old white men on all of our US currency? Then good news for you, <b><a href=\"http://www.vice.com/read/a-bunch-of-people-want-to-put-harriet-tubman-on-the-20-instead-of-slave-owning-andrew-jackson-vgtrn\">Vice</a></b>reports that the <a href=\"http://www.womenon20s.org/\">people have spoken</a>, and they want Harriet Tubman to replace Andrew Jackson on the 20 dollar bill.\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, <strong>Muchies</strong>\' <strong>Emily Steer</strong> shared what restaurants, everyday winos, and the State of California can do to <a href=\"http://munchies.vice.com/articles/what-exactly-is-sustainable-wine\">toast</a>vino sustainably.\r\n\r\nDo you dream of being Instafamous? <b></b>Instagram and Getty images are now giving out 3 grants of 10,000 each for amateur photographers who document underrepresented communities, reports<b><a href=\"http://www.dazeddigital.com/artsandculture/article/24697/1/hey-photographers-instagram-wants-to-give-you-10-000\">Dazed</a>.</b>If you think you have what it takes, start uploading your shots with the hashtag #GettyInstagramGram and get your pictures in by June 4th.\r\n\r\n<strong>Andy</strong><b> Warhols</b> drag selfies including polaroids of the famous artist dressed in full makeup and wigs went up for bid on <a href=\"http://www.ebay.com/itm/181731798424\"><b>Ebay</b></a>Wednesday, with the highest bid closing at a whopping 220 grand.\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, in the music industry, analog may <a href=\"http://www.stereogum.com/1801049/vnyl-sliding-why-the-netflix-for-vinyl-service-is-such-a-mess/franchises/essay/\">stay</a> analog - at least for now. <b>Stereogum</b>s <b>Michael Nelson</b> told us where - and why the Netflix model bottomed out for <strong>VNYL</strong>s subscription record-sharing service.\r\n\r\nBritish rescue cat <b>Merlin</b> was <a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3078935/Noisier-washing-machine-cat-loudest-purr-world-Merlin-breaks-record-67-8db-growl.html?ito=social-facebook\">awarded</a> a <strong>Guinness World Record</strong> for his earth-shaking, conversation-stopping purrs, while <b>P!nk</b> <a href=\"http://perezhilton.com/2015-05-13-pink-fights-body-shame-bmi-pop-awards-happy-human/?from=post\">shut down</a> body-shamers and trash-talk once again, saying:\r\n\r\n<em>I think people have gotten it wrong. They think their opinion matters and holds weight, and I don\'t know where or why they\'re giving themselves so much credit, you know? So I thought it was important for me to remind them that I don\'t care. My life is full, I like food a lot, and I really like to cook, I like to live. I find joy in that, and we\'re doing all right in the Hart household... I\'m raising a girl. I am a girl. I have feelings. People think I take no st and I\'m tough, tougher than nails, but I\'m a human being... I don\'t take well to bullying. I never have. I\'m not a person that will be bullied. I\'m not a person that will stand by watching other people bullied.</em>\r\n\r\nLast - and perhaps least, no week is complete without <b>Bill O\'Reilly</b> <a href=\"http://www.stereogum.com/1801391/bill-oreilly-blames-rap-industry-for-decline-of-christianity-in-america/video/\">attributing</a> the decline of religious morality in America to those dang kids and their hip-hop rappings!\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend. Like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange  we scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest hanging fruit, and stick out after hours til the last last-call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Thank Fuck It\'s Friday 5/14','','publish','open','open','','thank-fuck-its-friday-514','','','2015-05-14 22:29:51','2015-05-14 22:29:51','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=142',0,'post','',0),(143,5,'2015-05-13 23:40:22','2015-05-13 23:40:22','','1120439','Andy Warhol, Courtesy of Ebay','inherit','open','open','','1120439','','','2015-05-13 23:41:11','2015-05-13 23:41:11','',142,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/1120439.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(163,5,'2015-05-19 10:00:45','2015-05-19 10:00:45','Gear up for Memorial DaySubterreanean-styleat this week\'s wildest &amp; weirdestperformances, plays, open-air markets, and afterworkdiscos.\r\n\r\n<b>Tuesday</b>\r\n\r\n<img class=\" alignleft\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/8f/Zan_Zig_performing_with_rabbit_and_roses,_magician_poster,_1899-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"378\" height=\"592\" />\r\n\r\nGet your week off to an illusive start as <b>Steve Spill</b> <a href=\"http://www.booksoup.com/steve-spill-2015\">reveals</a> the tips and tricks that turned his beloved childhood pastime into a rich, lifelong journey - and his livelihood. Join the author/magician at <b>Book Soup</b>, where he will read from his recent book, I Lie for Money, taking readers on a gripping tour through Europe, Africa, and the Caribbean, and back to Santa Monica. The star-studded memoir also promises cameos from the likes of Joan Rivers, Bob Dylan, and Sting - which is more than enough to make us break out the old hat &amp; rabbit and head down Sunset.\r\n\r\n<b>Wednesday</b>\r\n\r\nGo small-batch at L.A. LIVEs <b>POPUP Marketplace</b>, an <a href=\"http://www.lalive.com/events-calendar/popup-marketplace\">evening</a> of shopping and entertainment from LAs biggest-littlest movers, shakers, and home-makers. The pop-up runs from 5-10pm, and features food and drink deals plus a live soundtrack via adjacent DJ booths - so you can skip the disco nap, and go straight to retail therapy.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/15229379983_97062ec16e_b.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-164 alignright\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/15229379983_97062ec16e_b-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"via flickr commons\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a>The curated, open air market will hostas many as sixty artists (with mason jars in tow).If you start to feel any creeping buyers remorse, remember,youre not just oogling cutesy doo-dads, youre <i>giving back</i>by supporting local artisans.\r\n\r\nThen, show off your locally-sourced bling as you twist the night away to tunes from DJ <strong>Dirtie Blonde</strong> at <strong>The Catnip Club</strong>\'s<strong> Hump Day <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/878242365553083/\">Party</a>!</strong>\r\n\r\n<b>Thursday</b>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/autry-social-media-final-1.jpg\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-182 alignleft\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/autry-social-media-final-1-300x114.jpg\" alt=\"autry-social-media-final (1)\" width=\"300\" height=\"114\" /></a>\r\n\r\nTake a trip out West to a twilight Griffith Park, to catch <b>High Five Art</b>, the first-ever <a href=\"http://theautry.org/programs/special-events/high-five-art-launch-party\">public art contest</a> at T<b>he Autry</b> - aspace chronicling the art, lives and peoples of the American West. Anticipate gigantic 50-footer banner display of the winning entry, <a href=\"http://www.carlosnietoiiiart.com/\"><b>Carlos Nieto III</b></a>\'s design <i>Cultura Nouveau</i>. Get your art and craft on with live participant activities, while you get your wine, beer and food truck fix in to tracks spun by live DJs.\r\n\r\n<b>Friday</b>\r\n\r\n<img class=\" alignright\" src=\"https://scontent-lax.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xft1/v/t1.0-9/11160563_1596408333949732_6374652667528214706_n.jpg?oh=ccece372786d3fb4e0c2408c7d49d419&amp;oe=55C71538\" alt=\"\" width=\"652\" height=\"367\" />\r\n\r\nGoing feline doesnt mean you have to snooze through your weekend. This week, skip the cat nap and high-tail it to <strong>LA Mother</strong> for <strong>Catcercise</strong> aerobics with <strong>The Catnip Club</strong>, LAs only pussy-lovers only exercise <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/975750215770406/\">regimen</a>. Come in cat ears, spandex and sneaks with your whiskers pulled back, ready to dance to your favorite disco classics.\r\n\r\nHeld in a joyous nightclub setting with a live DJ and kitty visuals, theworkout willinspiration from zumba, Jane Fonda-style aerobics,yoga, and disco, also boasting a giant disco ball, dry ice, and elements of vogueing - which is more than enough to get these sleepy cats purring.\r\n\r\n<b>Friday, Saturday &amp;Sunday</b>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/sSISTERSs.jpg\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-177 alignleft\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/sSISTERSs-300x198.jpg\" alt=\"sSISTERSs\" width=\"300\" height=\"198\" /></a>\r\n\r\nSpend an evening in the company of <b>sSISTERSs</b>, the best and worst siblings you never had. The delightfully dark, complex and multi-layered <a href=\"http://highwaysperformance.org/highways/event/gina-young-ssisters/\">play</a> will come alive in three (and more) voices by the very <b>Gina Young</b> that brought us the award-winning delights of <b>Femmes: A Tragedy</b>. Anticipate vocal harmonies, games from your childhood reinterpreted in ways unexpected, and and exploration of the kind of elaborate rituals that only a family bond can nourish. Relish it again on Saturday and Sunday showings.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" alignright\" src=\"http://pixabay.com/static/uploads/photo/2014/08/12/00/01/oia-416135_640.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"398\" />\r\n\r\nOr, if thats Greek to you, try heading to Northridge, for feta, filo and <a href=\"http://valleygreekfestival.com/\">festivities</a> at <b>Saint Nicholas Greek Orthodox Church</b>. The annual <b>Valley Greek Festival </b>begins on Saturday and runs for three days, offering a full weekend of music, dancing and Mediterranean delights.\r\n<strong>Saturday</strong>\r\n\r\nReady for your endless summer to begin? Swing by <b>Exposition Park</b> for a 5pm showing of <b>500 Days of Summer.</b> In addition the classic indie rom-com, <b>Street Food Cinema</b> <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1614136002140702/\">promises</a> live music and tasty snacks from LAs most beloved food trucks.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" alignleft\" src=\"http://images4.fanpop.com/image/photos/21000000/Zooey-Deschanel-500-Days-Of-Summer-zooey-deschanel-21079682-1280-534.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1280\" height=\"534\" />\r\n\r\nOnce you get your Zooey fix in, why not keep the night going at the <b>Far Away </b><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/464588263707772/\">party</a>? SF psych-pop duo <b>Peaking Lights</b> will headline, performing their trippy mix Acid Test, with supporting DJ sets from <b>LCD Soundsystem</b>s <b>David Scott Stone</b> and <b>Benedek</b>s heady synth-soul stylings. Though entry is free(!), attendees are encouraged to stop by the <b>Far Away</b> pop-up shop to pick up records, artwork, and show support for local DJs.\r\n\r\n<strong>Sunday</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/2014soulclaptourposter-1.jpg\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-179 alignleft\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/2014soulclaptourposter-1-194x300.jpg\" alt=\"2014soulclaptourposter (1)\" width=\"194\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n\r\nPolish off your Memorial day weekend with tunes from DJ <b>Jonathan Toubin, </b>the mind Vice hailed as pretty much the only DJ we actually like. <b>New York Night Train </b>promises soul and tons of room to boogie at the <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/805927419482924/\"><b>SOUL CLAP &amp; DANCE-OFF album launch</b></a>.\r\n\r\nDoes Hollywoods vast selection of speakeasies leave you asking, wheres all the pre-industrial power? Ditch the bluenoses and bimbos (20s for prudes and macho dudes), break out the lace and clockwork, and head over to the O Hotel. <b>Lost Angels</b> boasts a darkly opulent <a href=\"http://www.poetryfoundation.org/harriet/2013/08/cassandra-gillig-just-won-poetry-listen-to-drake-feat-frank-ohara/\">speakeasy</a>, bringing together flapper ethos and imagery from an even more distant twenties - which is to say, the 1820s. Citing inspiration from the celtic-pagan Beltaine Festival, guests are encouraged to come in darkly debauched haute couture, and to bring art supplies.\r\n\r\n<strong>Monday</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"762\"]<img src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f2/Ballet_Goes_To_the_Factory-_Dance_and_Entertainment_Organised_by_the_Council_For_the_Encouragement_of_Music_and_the_Arts,_England,_1943_D14046.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"762\" height=\"800\" /> \"Ballet Goes To the Factory\" via Google Commons[/caption]\r\n\r\nGet your week off to a bangin start at <b>Fringe,</b> Los Feliz offbeat comedy pub <a href=\"http://facebook.com/FringeMondayNights.\">night</a>. I want it to feel like if Andy Warhol had a weird comedy club in his Factory inside a very bro\'d-out bar.\" Says host JC Coccoli. Unlike Coccolis long running stand-up show Keep It Clean, Fringe boasts not just local comics - but acts from across the country, and even overseas. If that isnt enough to get you heading down Vermont, theres also pizza and beer - on the house!\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend. Like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange  we scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest hanging fruit, and stick out after hours til the last last-call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Suicide Tuesdays 5/19','','publish','open','open','','suicide-tuesdays-519','','','2015-05-19 17:04:31','2015-05-19 17:04:31','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=163',0,'post','',0),(164,5,'2015-05-16 23:20:57','2015-05-16 23:20:57','','15229379983_97062ec16e_b','via flickr commons','inherit','open','open','','15229379983_97062ec16e_b','','','2015-05-16 23:21:46','2015-05-16 23:21:46','',163,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/15229379983_97062ec16e_b.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(167,5,'2015-05-16 23:27:07','2015-05-16 23:27:07','','14666926298_5d6c7555b8_k','','inherit','open','open','','14666926298_5d6c7555b8_k','','','2015-05-16 23:27:07','2015-05-16 23:27:07','',163,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/14666926298_5d6c7555b8_k.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(168,5,'2015-05-16 23:27:16','2015-05-16 23:27:16','','11410187734_7892cf3887_b','','inherit','open','open','','11410187734_7892cf3887_b','','','2015-05-16 23:27:16','2015-05-16 23:27:16','',163,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/11410187734_7892cf3887_b.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(174,5,'2015-05-17 00:35:56','2015-05-17 00:35:56','','terrarium imgbad','','inherit','open','open','','terrarium-imgbad','','','2015-05-17 00:35:56','2015-05-17 00:35:56','',163,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/terrarium-imgbad.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(177,5,'2015-05-18 20:09:54','2015-05-18 20:09:54','','sSISTERSs','','inherit','open','open','','ssisterss','','','2015-05-18 20:09:54','2015-05-18 20:09:54','',163,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/sSISTERSs.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(179,5,'2015-05-18 20:16:18','2015-05-18 20:16:18','','2014soulclaptourposter (1)','','inherit','open','open','','2014soulclaptourposter-1','','','2015-05-18 20:16:18','2015-05-18 20:16:18','',163,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/2014soulclaptourposter-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(182,5,'2015-05-18 20:23:45','2015-05-18 20:23:45','','autry-social-media-final (1)','','inherit','open','open','','autry-social-media-final-1','','','2015-05-18 20:23:45','2015-05-18 20:23:45','',163,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/autry-social-media-final-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(186,5,'2015-05-18 20:58:27','2015-05-18 20:58:27','','3073952428_b7bb773fdb_o','Need a taste of Santorini? Swing by Northridge this weekend. ','inherit','open','open','','3073952428_b7bb773fdb_o','','','2015-05-18 20:59:20','2015-05-18 20:59:20','',163,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/3073952428_b7bb773fdb_o.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(189,5,'2015-05-22 17:22:09','2015-05-22 17:22:09','This week, in honor of masturbation month, <strong>Crave</strong> let us peek inside the studio of a sex-toy designer.\r\n\r\nFemale sexuality and the pursuit of pleasure has been taboo and stigmatized for so long in our culture that typically people do not consider this to be a legitimate industry. I can assure you it is<a href=\"http://www.cnbc.com/id/100828629\">a multi-billion dollar industry</a> in fact. writes Author <strong>Ti</strong>. However, we have a lot of cultural baggage we need to shed before this industry is viewed as seriously as other consumer product design, and how can that happen if the ultimate sex toy is a two-pronged phallic combo with a neon colored rabbit? How can we move forward when the vast majority of the products that support intimacy are objects that you would be ashamed to be seen with?\r\n\r\nIn response to <b>Emma Sulkowitz</b>s brave performance piece Carry That Weight, some <a href=\"http://jezebel.com/posters-on-columbia-campus-call-emma-sulkowicz-a-pretty-1705750162\">asshole</a> has been plastering posters around upper Manhattan accusing the artist of lying about being assaulted. Jezebel speculated that the posters may be the work of right wing graffiti artist Sabo, while another victim of Paul Nungessers came forward with her <a href=\"http://jezebel.com/i-am-not-a-pretty-little-liar-1705996719\">story</a>, reporting that the assailant was convicted of assaulting her when she was a student at Columbia only a year before.\r\n\r\nWhen I filed the complaint against Paul, I didnt know it would turn into a national event. writes the anonymous victim. It was over a year before Emma started carrying that weight, months before what happened at Columbia helped sparked a national dialogue about rape on college campus. I was just trying to do the right thing.\r\n\r\n<b>Vice News </b><a href=\"https://news.vice.com/article/california-pipeline-spill-dumps-21000-gallons-of-oil-into-the-pacific-ocean\">reported</a> a massive oil spill on Californias Refugio State Beach into the Pacific Ocean near Santa Barbara.\r\n\r\nTwitter persona <b>@sosadtoday</b> revealed herself to <strong>Rolling Stone</strong> as Venice based poet <b>Melissa Broder</b>, and <a href=\"http://www.rollingstone.com/culture/features/sosadtoday-reveals-herself-and-her-existential-beach-read-20150519\">announced</a> a forthcoming book!\r\n\r\n<b>Tavi Gevinson</b> <a href=\"http://www.dazeddigital.com/fashion/article/24817/1/tavi-gevinson-scott-schuman-the-sartorialist-interview-criticism-fashion\">responded</a> to an old dig from <b>The Sartorialist</b> criticizing her for writing about fashion without understanding it fully. Tavi fired back brilliantly, saying:\r\n\r\n\"That young people dont have valid thoughts about the world because they havent been alive long enough is sadly a very popular and, frankly, unoriginal sentiment. When I think about that time, I was just responding to the world around me. And I was perceptive enough that I felt like I could make connections to things in my life. I dont think it was abstract.\r\n\r\n<b>Dame</b>s <b>Robin Abrahams</b> <a href=\"http://www.damemagazine.com/2015/05/18/did-peggy-really-choose-love-over-her-career\">dissected</a> the hard choices made by the career women of <b>Mad Men</b> in her write-up of last weeks finale.\r\n\r\nArtist <b>Vasilisa Forbes</b> adorned London billboards with sex-positive BDSM with an empowering, feminist <a href=\"http://www.dazeddigital.com/photography/article/24771/1/the-story-behind-londons-eye-popping-new-bdsm-billboards\">message</a>.\r\n\r\nIn response to so called dad bods trending, Buzzfeed brought us <a href=\"http://www.buzzfeed.com/lorynbrantz/disney-princesses-with-mombods?bffb&amp;utm_term=4ldqpgp#4ldqpgp\">images</a> of Disney Princesses with mom bods just as beautiful as the original images and their impossibly-teensy waistlines.\r\n\r\nIconic Queen Bee/fetch <i>Mean Girls</i> villainess <b>Regina George</b>s mansion went on the market for a pretty <a href=\"http://www.dazeddigital.com/artsandculture/article/24815/1/regina-george-s-mean-girls-mansion-is-for-sale\">penny</a>, while a group of over 50s women was turned <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/may/19/cannes-backlash-high-heels-emily-blunt-flat-shoes?CMP=share_btn_fb\">away</a> from the <strong>Cannes</strong> red carpet for not sporting heels.\r\n\r\nIm not sure I couldve come up with a better metaphor for sexism in the film industry if I was really, really trying. <a href=\"http://jezebel.com/cannes-film-festival-wont-admit-women-wearing-flat-shoe-1705462774\">wrote</a> Jezebels Anna Merlan. If you wrote this into a novel about sexism in the film industry, it would seem heavy-handed. Too much, your editor would say. Tone it down.\r\n\r\n<b>Dazed</b> responded to the incident, since deemed flatgate with a breakdown of inpiring red-carpet <a href=\"http://www.dazeddigital.com/fashion/article/24797/1/five-rebel-girls-who-shunned-red-carpet-rules\">rulebreakers</a>.\r\n\r\n<b>Vice</b>s <b>Nathaniel Miller</b> told us about the devastating plague that is tearing apart sea star populations, in a beautiful <a href=\"http://www.vice.com/read/the-wasting-0000650-v22n5?utm_source=vicefbus\">piece</a> on the phenomenon scientists call The Wasting. \"No one was able to see it coming,\" comments a local student. \"If we\'re not able to predict something as significant as this, what else don\'t we see coming?\"\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend. Like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange  we scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest hanging fruit, and stick out after hours til the last last-call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Thank Fuck It\'s Friday 5/22','','publish','open','open','','thank-fuck-its-friday-522','','','2015-05-22 17:26:25','2015-05-22 17:26:25','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=189',0,'post','',0),(190,5,'2015-05-22 17:21:27','2015-05-22 17:21:27','','Rachel-McAdams-as-Regina-George-rachel-mcadams-2377123-1600-900','','inherit','open','open','','rachel-mcadams-as-regina-george-rachel-mcadams-2377123-1600-900','','','2015-05-22 17:21:27','2015-05-22 17:21:27','',189,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Rachel-McAdams-as-Regina-George-rachel-mcadams-2377123-1600-900.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(201,1,'2015-05-25 00:07:03','2015-05-25 00:07:03','[vc_row full_width=\"\" parallax=\"\" parallax_image=\"\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2>Hollywood</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_basic_grid post_type=\"page\" max_items=\"1000\" style=\"all\" items_per_page=\"10\" show_filter=\"\" element_width=\"4\" gap=\"30\" orderby=\"date\" order=\"DESC\" filter_source=\"category\" filter_style=\"default\" filter_align=\"center\" filter_color=\"grey\" filter_size=\"md\" button_style=\"rounded\" button_color=\"blue\" button_size=\"md\" arrows_design=\"none\" arrows_position=\"inside\" arrows_color=\"blue\" paging_design=\"radio_dots\" paging_color=\"grey\" loop=\"\" autoplay=\"-1\" item=\"none\" grid_id=\"vc_gid:1434579750607-7e7cda87-2ab0-4\" taxonomies=\"22\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"\" parallax=\"\" parallax_image=\"\" el_id=\"\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2>Silver Lake &amp; Echo Park</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_basic_grid post_type=\"page\" max_items=\"1000\" style=\"all\" items_per_page=\"10\" show_filter=\"\" element_width=\"4\" gap=\"30\" orderby=\"date\" order=\"DESC\" filter_source=\"category\" filter_style=\"default\" filter_align=\"center\" filter_color=\"grey\" filter_size=\"md\" button_style=\"rounded\" button_color=\"blue\" button_size=\"md\" arrows_design=\"none\" arrows_position=\"inside\" arrows_color=\"blue\" paging_design=\"radio_dots\" paging_color=\"grey\" loop=\"\" autoplay=\"-1\" item=\"none\" grid_id=\"vc_gid:1434579917753-f044d9b3-e115-1\" taxonomies=\"40\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"\" parallax=\"\" parallax_image=\"\" el_id=\"\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2>Koreatown</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_basic_grid post_type=\"page\" max_items=\"1000\" style=\"all\" items_per_page=\"10\" show_filter=\"\" element_width=\"4\" gap=\"30\" orderby=\"date\" order=\"DESC\" filter_source=\"category\" filter_style=\"default\" filter_align=\"center\" filter_color=\"grey\" filter_size=\"md\" button_style=\"rounded\" button_color=\"blue\" button_size=\"md\" arrows_design=\"none\" arrows_position=\"inside\" arrows_color=\"blue\" paging_design=\"radio_dots\" paging_color=\"grey\" loop=\"\" autoplay=\"-1\" item=\"none\" grid_id=\"vc_gid:1434579986155-bba68bb7-d63b-10\" taxonomies=\"41\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"\" parallax=\"\" parallax_image=\"\" el_id=\"\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2>Arlington Heights</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_basic_grid post_type=\"page\" max_items=\"1000\" style=\"all\" items_per_page=\"10\" show_filter=\"\" element_width=\"4\" gap=\"30\" orderby=\"date\" order=\"DESC\" filter_source=\"category\" filter_style=\"default\" filter_align=\"center\" filter_color=\"grey\" filter_size=\"md\" button_style=\"rounded\" button_color=\"blue\" button_size=\"md\" arrows_design=\"none\" arrows_position=\"inside\" arrows_color=\"blue\" paging_design=\"radio_dots\" paging_color=\"grey\" loop=\"\" autoplay=\"-1\" item=\"none\" grid_id=\"vc_gid:1434580107568-4f8ee71f-68cc-7\" taxonomies=\"42\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"\" parallax=\"\" parallax_image=\"\" el_id=\"\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2>Chinatown</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_basic_grid post_type=\"page\" max_items=\"1000\" style=\"all\" items_per_page=\"10\" show_filter=\"\" element_width=\"4\" gap=\"30\" orderby=\"date\" order=\"DESC\" filter_source=\"category\" filter_style=\"default\" filter_align=\"center\" filter_color=\"grey\" filter_size=\"md\" button_style=\"rounded\" button_color=\"blue\" button_size=\"md\" arrows_design=\"none\" arrows_position=\"inside\" arrows_color=\"blue\" paging_design=\"radio_dots\" paging_color=\"grey\" loop=\"\" autoplay=\"-1\" item=\"none\" grid_id=\"vc_gid:1434580189478-212b0a96-cd01-5\" include=\"487\" taxonomies=\"43\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width=\"\" parallax=\"\" parallax_image=\"\" el_id=\"\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h2>Downtown</h2>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_basic_grid post_type=\"page\" max_items=\"1000\" style=\"all\" items_per_page=\"10\" show_filter=\"\" element_width=\"4\" gap=\"30\" orderby=\"date\" order=\"DESC\" filter_source=\"category\" filter_style=\"default\" filter_align=\"center\" filter_color=\"grey\" filter_size=\"md\" button_style=\"rounded\" button_color=\"blue\" button_size=\"md\" arrows_design=\"none\" arrows_position=\"inside\" arrows_color=\"blue\" paging_design=\"radio_dots\" paging_color=\"grey\" loop=\"\" autoplay=\"-1\" item=\"none\" grid_id=\"vc_gid:1434579767189-2d2261c7-6238-5\" taxonomies=\"39\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Venues','','publish','open','open','','venues','','','2015-06-17 22:29:56','2015-06-17 22:29:56','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?page_id=201',0,'page','',0),(206,1,'2015-06-01 21:04:33','2015-06-01 21:04:33','[vc_row full_width=\"\" parallax=\"\" parallax_image=\"\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]<b>Circus Disco</b>\r\n\r\nWant to twist the night away, then hit the Santa Monica boardwalk? Well, you kinda can  or at least you can get the essentials.\r\n\r\nHollywood nightclub Circus Disco pairs its lively dance club with a ferris wheel and other carnival festivities (though, luckily, no clowns). At night, the massive Hollywood warehouse transforms into a decadent playspace for clubgoers, offering an impressive three separate dance floors and a roomy patio  plus outdoor carnival rides.\r\n\r\nDcor is esoteric and appropriately carnivalesque, drawing from club culture and bright fair aesthetics, and featuring some less expected pieces like a rococo-inspired chandelier. Its no surprise that Circus Disco is particularly beloved by trance fans, and best suited for big, atmospheric parties with lots of bells, whistles and lasers. During the week, it tends to be a little emptier, though, so for the full experience, its best to go on a Friday or Saturday.\r\n\r\nResidencies and regular nights are diverse, offering everything from mainstream and hip hop to salsa, karaoke, and drag shows. Current residents include DJ Calahan and DJ Jorge, but the Disco is most known for bringing international acts. DJs tend to stray from playing tired disco classics, instead featuring rarer tracks and mixes  so dont ask for The Bee Gees or The Trammps.\r\n\r\nThough some parties charge a cover, weekly sets like DJ Barneys Friday residency are often free before 10pm, and the clubs site features deals where you can text or join an email list in exchange for entry. Saturdays are primarily trance/EDM with dark electronic sets, but theres also a room reserved for hip hop. (Word on the street is thats where to go if youre looking for a particularly strong drink).\r\n\r\nDrinks can run a little steep, though if youre willing to shell out, ask for Ernesto to make you The Grateful Dead or another one of the clubs popular specialty cocktails. Like most circuses, the Disco isnt at its most enjoyable when experienced in sobriety.\r\n\r\nThough Circus Disco might lack a little in ponies and elephants, with a diverse calendar of regular sets and DJs visiting from abroad, it certainly isnt clownin around  theres more than enough to fill three rings and overflow into the parking lot, where nearby food trucks are known to swarm, preying on disco-drunchies.\r\n\r\n<b>The Lowdown</b>\r\n\r\nCircus Disco is a large warehouse dance club in Hollywood, featuring resident hip hop and electronic nights. The club also holds pole dancing performances and drag shows. Highlights include bottle service, high tech visuals, a fake tiger and a very real ferris-wheel.\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text css_animation=\"\"][templatera id=\"349\"][/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Circus Disco','','publish','open','open','','clubcircus','','','2015-08-12 18:29:02','2015-08-13 01:29:02','',201,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?page_id=206',0,'page','',0),(210,1,'2015-05-25 16:08:35','2015-05-25 16:08:35','','Shop','','publish','closed','open','','shop','','','2015-05-25 16:08:35','2015-05-25 16:08:35','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/shop/',0,'page','',0),(213,1,'2015-05-25 16:08:35','2015-05-25 16:08:35','[woocommerce_my_account]','My Account','','publish','closed','open','','my-account','','','2015-05-25 16:08:35','2015-05-25 16:08:35','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/my-account/',0,'page','',0),(217,5,'2015-05-26 10:00:21','2015-05-26 10:00:21','This week, enjoy girl-groups &amp; fantastical burlesque, or go Russian viaimprovised Chekhovian drama.\r\n<h2><strong>Tuesday</strong></h2>\r\nSwing by Dragonfly for Women Rock Against Breast Cancer, a showcase of LAs best girl bands. Hosted by local indie rock event mavens <strong>Krystal Khali</strong> and <strong>John McCracken</strong>, proceeds from the nights <a href=\"http://www.eventbrite.com/e/women-rock-against-breast-cancer-tickets-16920880810\">festivities</a> will go towards Krystals high school friend Aleena Clavels treatment bills.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" alignnone\" src=\"https://cdn.evbuc.com/eventlogos/140067664/photo28229smaller.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"585\" height=\"891\" />\r\n<h2><strong>Wednesday</strong></h2>\r\nIf you\'re feeling spellbound by the power of film, cruise down Fairfax to the Cinefamily for<b>O is for Occult</b>, A Special Presentation by Skip Elsheimer of <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/avgeeks\">A/V Geeks</a>. Join <strong>The Sacred Order of the Lost &amp; Found Film Club</strong> for an <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1417674211875867/\">evening</a> of hysterical, anti-occult propaganda from the dark ages to the age of aquarius, and mercury retrogrades of today. The tour will hit San Francisco\'s First Church of Satan, meet with Grandmaster Warlocks, and enact Satanic rituals foreign to those whove yet to listen to Zeppelin records in reverse.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"380\"]<img src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xaf1/v/t1.0-9/10420255_908436692553748_6789962903849465069_n.jpg?oh=53759c48dc3d1fbea51d711d950d5f0c&amp;oe=55F34434\" alt=\"\" width=\"380\" height=\"289\" /> Courtesy of Facebook[/caption]\r\n\r\nAfterwards, we recommend swinging by <strong>Canters</strong> &amp; <strong>The Kibitz Room</strong> for pastrami or a cocktail at one ofLA\'s most iconic establishments. If you\'re in the neighborhood earlier in the evening, stopat <strong>Bark \'N Bitches</strong> to say hi to some adoptable rescue pups!\r\n<h2><strong>Thursday</strong></h2>\r\nMidweek blues? Embrace your inner witchy macabre,and head over to Bellflower to enjoy a taste of the dark <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1066989253317802/\">side</a> at <strong>Goth Night at The New Wave Bar</strong>, with darkwave karaoke and dancing.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"343\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://fc09.deviantart.net/fs71/f/2014/077/2/4/24e06e7abfda5cd87f6cbc19beafb0dd-d7apunp.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"343\" height=\"517\" /> courtesy of deviantart: kyawolfwritten[/caption]\r\n<h2><strong>Friday</strong></h2>\r\nWatch all your favorite aspiring burlesque dancers get put to the test at<b>BURLYPICKS California Regional Competition</b> live at <b>FAIS DO DO</b>. Snag your <a href=\"http://www.brownpapertickets.com/event/1587268\">tickets</a> to watch 23 performers face off for the gold, and the chance to move on to the final round to represent the Golden State in the <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1589071811329140/\">Burlypicks Finals 2015</a>!\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"720\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://static1.squarespace.com/static/50f6d8dfe4b0c4007db424a3/t/51b4b43ce4b027c2e3e5104c/1370797116518/newsprint.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"720\" height=\"480\" /> Courtesy of BollyBrit[/caption]\r\n\r\nOr, if farce is more your speed, head over to North Hollywood for a <a href=\"http://www.yelp.com/events/north-hollywood-the-idiot-box\">performance</a> of <strong>The Idiot Box</strong>. The sitcom play boastswar, betrayal, and the absurd, with collisions of reality, denial and illusion run amuck.\r\n<h2><strong>Saturday</strong></h2>\r\nIf Saturday nights got you feeling like a sexy unicorn (why not?), strap on your bustiers and corsets and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/934058183313320\">head</a> to <b>Charlies Unicorn Cabaret </b>for a night of seductive and <i>horny</i> delights and performance to sets by DJ Dan and Magical Guest DJs.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"2400\"]<img src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/82/DomenichinounicornPalFarnese.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2400\" height=\"1983\" /> courtesy of Wikipedia Commons[/caption]\r\n\r\nOr, if youre feeling some NBA playoffs FOMO, dribble your way to West LAs Equinox Sports Club for an epic celebrity <a href=\"http://www.timeout.com/los-angeles/sport-and-fitness/sports-spectacular-celebrity-basketball-game#tab_panel_2\">match</a> off that will leave even the least sporty subterranean saying ball! The game will be hosted by hip hip artist/prospective Kardashian Tyga, and benefit Cedars Sinai. You can purchase tickets <a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/celebrity-basketball-spectacular-benefiting-sports-spectacular-tickets-17074974709\">eventbrite</a> to support the hospital and watch your favorite famous faces fumble for a lay-up.\r\n\r\nOr, if youre feeling more kinky than sporty, swing by Night Visions LA Fashion &amp; Fetish Ball, as live performance, music, art and all things fetish <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/851771634888927/\">fill</a> the 333 Live Grand Ballroom.\r\n<h2><strong>Sunday</strong></h2>\r\nFirst, head over to <strong>LA WineFest</strong> to <a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/event/la-winefest-5606213\">sip</a> vinos from around Italy, Argentina, and Sonoma, and take samplings from vines close to home.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Then, catch someChekhovian </span><a style=\"line-height: 1.5;\" href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/event/impro-theatres-chekhov-unscripted-5502260\">improv</a><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">as</span><strong style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Impro Theatre\'s Chekhov UnScripted</strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">performs animprovised play inspired by the master Russian dramatist.</span>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"332\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e9/Chekhov_1898_by_Osip_Braz.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"332\" height=\"426\" /> Courtesy of Wikipedia Commons[/caption]\r\n<h2><strong>Monday</strong></h2>\r\nFeeling nostalgic, Angelinos? Join Zcalo and KCRW\'s Saul Gonzalez in conversation with<i>L.A. Weekly</i>s Dennis Romero, Libros Schmibros David Kipen, KCETs Lynell George, crime novelist Denise Hamilton and L.A. Office of Historic Resources manager Ken Bernstein, in a discussion on LA\'s architectural history. The talk, entitled \"<strong>Is L.A.s Past Worth Saving</strong>?\" is in conjunction with the launch of the Getty-sponsored preservation initiative, <strong>HistoricPlacesLA</strong>, a site chronicling the endangered, and ever changing city.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"5100\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/60/View_of_the_Angels_Flight_with_the_cars,_the_tower_and_surrounding_buildings,_Third_Street_and_Hill_Street,_Los_Angeles,_ca.1910_(CHS-5542).jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"5100\" height=\"4090\" /> Courtesy of Wikipedia Commons[/caption]\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend. Like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange  we scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest hanging fruit, and stick out after hours til the last last-call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Suicide Tuesdays 5/26','','publish','open','open','','suicide-tuesdays-526','','','2015-05-26 17:08:55','2015-05-26 17:08:55','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=217',0,'post','',0),(236,5,'2015-05-26 00:18:54','2015-05-26 00:18:54','','watts','courtesy of Nate Miller/Vice','inherit','open','open','','watts','','','2015-05-26 00:19:26','2015-05-26 00:19:26','',217,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/watts.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(239,5,'2015-05-26 00:41:04','2015-05-26 00:41:04','','IMG_9974','Courtesy of Nathaniel Miller','inherit','open','open','','img_9974','','','2015-05-26 00:42:06','2015-05-26 00:42:06','',217,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/IMG_9974.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(244,4,'2015-05-26 02:01:50','2015-05-26 02:01:50','[vc_row full_width=\"\" parallax=\"\" parallax_image=\"\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]Keffiyeh Truffaut skateboard meh. Deep v fashion axe tousled, Neutra keytar kogi Godard aesthetic single-origin coffee. Messenger bag twee Williamsburg fixie irony, shabby chic swag Echo Park tofu