=\"\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]Its hard not to enjoy Hollywoods Golden Box Theater  even if it can be a <i>little</i> difficult to find it. Tucked away behind the Supper Club, the Golden Box was first the bookish back room at LA mainstay Musso &amp; Frank Grill, and later went by the name The Writers Room  inspired by literati clientele ranging from Hemingway and Fitzgerald to Dorothy Parker. Though historic Hollywood is best known for the silver screen, its literary history is just as schmaltzy and impressive as its cinematic one  and just as fun to toast vodka sodas to.\r\n\r\nThe venues owners include NYC nightlife icon Nur Khan, comic Jason Segel, and actor Jack Huston, who is best known for playing Richard Harrow or the man with half a face on HBOs 20s mob drama <i>Boardwalk Empire.</i> Theres more to Golden Box than just jazz age nostalgia, though  the space has left behind some of its mid-century speakeasy dcor in favor of graffiti-style paintings and Bowie, which bring an 80s ethos and sense of performance to the small, sultrily lit bar.\r\n\r\nThe Golden Box is deceptively spacious, especially for its stealth location  the floor neatly sections off a booth where DJs spin house, disco, or R&amp;B, depending on the night. For more dedicated time-travelers and aspiring jazz cats, the club also hosts some burlesque performances accompanied by live music reminiscent of authentic 1920s Chicago-style jazz.\r\n\r\nSince the Golden Box is primarily a weekend after-hours joint, it can get a bit noisy, but its locale prevents it from falling victim to too many frenzied club-hopping tourists or belligerent Hollywood crowding. Theres only one bar, but drink lines are fairly manageable since the venues largest social spaces tend to be its lively dance floor and roomy patio.\r\n\r\nLike owner Nur Khans better-known New York haunts, Kenmare and Don Hills, the Golden Box has a distinctly rock n roll sensibility  more <i>Last Days of Disco</i> than Faulkner or Fitzgerald. Though its a popular spot for private parties, and certainly has an intimate, exclusive vibe, both the Golden Boxs interior and clientele skew towards more offbeat tastes than Tinseltowns usual VIP destinations  more secret entrance than A-List only. While its previous lives and monikers might remain a little shrouded in mystery, today the club is a unique hybrid of disco and bookish dive, and has something for dancing queens and boozy scribes alike  and encourages partygoers to embrace a little bit of both.\r\n\r\n<b>The Lowdown</b>\r\n\r\nThe Golden Box Theater is a speakeasy-turned-afterhours disco located behind Hollywoods famous Supper Club. Though its traded some of its vintage digs for dance floor space and a DJ setup, the club nods to literary history and retro Los Angeles.\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][templatera id=\"349\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Golden Box Theater','','publish','open','open','','goldenboxla','','','2015-08-12 18:40:47','2015-08-13 01:40:47','',201,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?page_id=305',0,'page','',0),(314,1,'2015-05-28 23:18:17','2015-05-28 23:18:17','','Order &ndash; May 28, 2015 @ 11:18 PM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_5567a22564569','order-may-28-2015-1117-pm','','','2015-05-28 23:18:17','2015-05-28 23:18:17','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=314',0,'shop_order','',3),(316,4,'2015-05-28 23:31:43','2015-05-28 23:31:43','','wtn-social-twitter','','inherit','open','open','','wtn-social-twitter','','','2015-05-28 23:31:43','2015-05-28 23:31:43','',5,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/wtn-social-twitter.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(325,1,'2015-05-29 03:02:41','2015-05-29 03:02:41','','Order &ndash; May 29, 2015 @ 03:02 AM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_5567d68f4f0fc','order-may-29-2015-0301-am','','','2015-05-29 03:02:41','2015-05-29 03:02:41','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p