hile also candidly rendering the authors experiences growing up as a gay man with cerebral palsy.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/538391767012212736/wjDmvTkw.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"424\" /> Courtesy of Twitter[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Wednesday</b></h2>\r\nHead to Beverly Hills for an <a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/event/spring-awakening-5558475\">awakening</a> like no other, as <b>Deaf West Theater</b> incorporates song, dance, &amp; sign-language into their acclaimed interpretation of <b><i>Spring Awakening</i></b>. The 2006 Musical playfully explores sexual repression in a German High school; expect to leave with inhibitions shed and expectations surpassed, basking in a celebration of sensuality, language, &amp; artistic expression.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1800\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://www.trbimg.com/img-5419e3cb/turbine/la-et-cm-deaf-west-theatres-spring-awakening-20140917\" alt=\"\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" /> Courtesy of The LA Times[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Thursday </b></h2>\r\nHead down to<strong> Vegas Meat Market</strong> in Echo Park to catch a <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/851962604895939/\">show</a> from one of our favorite local acts, <b>Harriet Brown</b>. Expect soulful synths &amp; sensual funk beats, plus sets from Pr0files, Cannons &amp; Valida. Get a taste of Harriet Browns signature Romantic Funk on Suzanne Krafts Stop Think mix, from Feel So Real.\r\n\r\nhttps://soundcloud.com/feelsoreal/stop-think-suzanne-kraft-remix\r\n<h2><b>Friday</b></h2>\r\nPick up your Pride and get your art on, subterraneans, for the opening evening of <b>Art AIDS America</b>, an exhibition in two parts. Showcasing a history of rich artistic production around the last or so thirty years since AIDS and HIV hit epidemic proportions, the exhibit promises more than a viral load of art with a distinctly &amp; insistently political and autobiographical voice. And this is <a href=\"http://one.usc.edu/art-aids-america/\">your chance to glimpse it</a> in good company.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"288\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://www.libertyhill.org/image/weho-art-aids-america-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"288\" height=\"234\" /> Courtesy of Liberty Hill[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Saturday</b></h2>\r\nStart your day off with the corgis (yes, those corgis) at the <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/qbsdr\"><b>Queen\'s Best Stumpy Dog Rescue</b></a> <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1584373095163765/\"><b>Yard Sale</b></a> in Torrance, hosted by Kimberly &amp; Jimmy Roberts. Youll get to mingle with lovable, stumpy rescue dogs as you bargain-hunt for clothing, shoes, housewares, accessories and more. All proceeds will go directly to vet care, food, supplies &amp; more for the low-riding pups.\r\n\r\nDone snagging cheap crap and oogling stumpy dogs at the corgi yard sale? Start your evening right with the opening of <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/462103427290382/\"><b>Living Home</b> by <b>Calista Lyon</b></a>, part of a group show at the <b>Luckman Gallery</b>. Expect your night to include the words of activist <b>Ron Finley</b>, and the collected talents of the <b>Gallery of Solutions</b>. The artist boasts a richness of internationalisms as well as local color to bring to the visual stage. Keep your sunglasses on, the future looks bright.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/11181236_10153376079466929_9183732008539182924_o.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-375\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/11181236_10153376079466929_9183732008539182924_o-214x300.jpg\" alt=\"11181236_10153376079466929_9183732008539182924_o\" width=\"214\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n\r\nPerhaps youre feeling like getting your book nerd on, but youre struggling to hold back your rocknroll soul. Theres no conflict at the library, with a Summer Reading session, starring <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/108752599456324/\">a screening of <b>The Runaways</b></a>, based on <b>Cherie Currie</b>s rockin rock n roll memoir, <b>Neon Angel</b>. If that wasnt enough to soothe the savage breast, Cherie joins special guest moderator <b>Susan Olsen</b> (thats right, from The Brady Bunch) to discuss her life in music, movies and her last 15 years as a renowned chain-saw artist. Shell even have books for the signing, if youre so inclined.\r\n<h2><b>Sunday</b></h2>\r\nFirst, get your pussy <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1607634816120374/\">wet</a> at the <b>Catnip Club Pool Party</b> at the <b>Standard Rooftop Bar</b>. Come in your fiestiest, feline swim get-up with, just enough cattitude to bask in the sun &amp; twist to disco seductions spun by LAs friskiest lady-DJs.\r\n\r\nThen, finish off your weekend right, with <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/378034182395210/\"><b>Girl Crush</b> improv</a> at the brand new <b>Womens Centre for Creative Work</b>. The brand new collaborative workspace isnt even officially launched, so youll be getting a sneak peek at what is yet to be for the creative future of womanhood in LA. Easing you into the space are the combined talents of Girl Crush, a self-defined girl gang of stone cold weirdos and cool kids who enjoy getting together and creating crush-worthy, story-focused, long-form improv.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://scontent-sjc2-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xpt1/v/t1.0-9/11165231_1593482717575627_6861516206841861025_n.jpg?oh=b1b4cd34c66b577a13b63a92ee649ff9&amp;oe=55FF61B7\" alt=\"\" width=\"851\" height=\"315\" />\r\n<h2><strong>Monday</strong></h2>\r\nInject a dose of soul into your week at <b>Club Nokia</b>, as <b>DAngelo &amp; The Vanguard</b>s R&amp;B stylings get you in the mood for whatever you have in store this June. Though <a href=\"http://www.axs.com/events/277812/d-angelo-and-the-vanguard-tickets\">tickets</a> run a pretty penny, weve heard its worth splurging for, rendering a strain of soul music reminiscent of Sly Stone in the 60s, George Clinton in the 70s or 1980s Prince according the Wall Street Journal, who also hailed the artist as a dynamo of the James Brown variety.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://www.billboard.com/files/styles/promo_650/public/media/d-angelo-billboard-650a.jpg?itok=oUKY8HUi\" alt=\"\" width=\"650\" height=\"430\" />\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend. Like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange  we scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest hanging fruit, and stick out after hours til the last last-call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Suicide Tuesdays 6/2','','publish','open','open','','suicide-tuesdays-62','','\nhttp://one.usc.edu/art-aids-america/','2015-06-02 23:23:51','2015-06-02 23:23:51','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=374',0,'post','',0),(375,5,'2015-06-02 02:21:49','2015-06-02 02:21:49','','11181236_10153376079466929_9183732008539182924_o','','inherit','open','open','','11181236_10153376079466929_9183732008539182924_o','','','2015-06-02 02:21:49','2015-06-02 02:21:49','',374,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/11181236_10153376079466929_9183732008539182924_o.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(376,1,'2015-06-02 02:31:28','2015-06-02 02:31:28','','Order &ndash; June 2, 2015 @ 02:31 AM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_556d153e8ec84','order-jun-02-2015-0230-am','','','2015-06-02 02:31:28','2015-06-02 02:31:28','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=376',0,'shop_order','',3),(378,5,'2015-06-02 02:36:51','2015-06-02 02:36:51','','The-runaways','','inherit','open','open','','the-runaways','','','2015-06-02 02:36:51','2015-06-02 02:36:51','',374,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/The-runaways.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(379,1,'2015-06-02 03:25:16','2015-06-02 03:25:16','','Order &ndash; June 2, 2015 @ 03:25 AM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_556d221a36266','order-jun-02-2015-0325-am','','','2015-06-02 03:25:16','2015-06-02 03:25:16','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=379',0,'shop_order','',3),(387,4,'2015-06-02 18:54:42','2015-06-02 18:54:42','[vc_row full_width=\"\" parallax=\"\" parallax_image=\"\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]If you want to dance in the moonlight while gazing upon Los Angeles beautiful (and frankly, grossly underrated) downtown skyline, look no further than the rooftop bar at The Standard Hotel.\r\n\r\nWith plenty of room to twist and writhe to chill house and disco or sip a Tom Collins by the pool, the Standards rooftop bar is the perfect place to spend a summer evening with friends or grab an atmospheric after-work drink. Cocktails are steep, and not the tastiest for the price tag  we recommend keeping it simple.\r\n\r\nLike most hotel bars, people can get friendly  in both positive and negative senses. Theres always someone eager chat or dance, though these gregarious roof-dwellers can be a little difficult to shake if youre actually seeking alone time. (Why are you on a hotel roof again?)\r\n\r\nThere is also a nearby pretzel vendor in the adjoining biergarten, if you feel the drunchies creeping up on you, or are in the mood for a brew or quick game of ping pong. Gamers can also take a quick detour to the hotels second floor SPiN lounge, a ping pong club with its own bar and more tables where you can do your best Williams sister or McEnroe impression, for more foul-mouthed subterraneans.\r\n\r\nOn weekdays, crowds pluck from the usual hotel bar suspects (tourists, sleazy businessmen, bros &amp; broettes) and a more high-fashion, young Hollywood crowd later in the night. We recommend dressing up a little, and going all-black if youre at a loss for what to wear.\r\n\r\nWith a spacious bar, dance floor, cozy booth seating and adorable hippo-shaped waste bins, you wont be at a loss for things to do and look at.\r\n\r\nWhile the roof hosts ticketed events like Fade To Mind, Dig Deeper, and The Catnip Club, there are also plenty of free sets and nights when the roof is open to all. Our favorite roof parties tend to be those held during the week and during the day on the weekend, when the hotels a little less crowded and there are plenty of spots to sit, dance, and take in the horizon of high rises.\r\n\r\n<b>The Lowdown</b>\r\n\r\nThough it might lack the retro appeal of The Ace, DTLAs skyline lends the downtown Standard Rooftop plenty of eye candy of its own. We recommend stopping by for a daytime or weekday party. If youre itching to break out your racket or fiendin for a craft brew, theres ping pong and a biergarten adjacent to the bar and nearby pool.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text css_animation=\"\"][templatera id=\"349\"][/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]','The Rooftop at The Standard, Downtown LA','','publish','open','open','','therooftopatthestandarddowntownla','','','2015-08-12 18:34:24','2015-08-13 01:34:24','',201,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?page_id=387',0,'page','',0),(395,1,'2015-06-03 01:18:05','2015-06-03 01:18:05','','Order &ndash; June 3, 2015 @ 01:18 AM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_556e55c6421a5','order-jun-03-2015-0117-am','','','2015-06-03 01:18:05','2015-06-03 01:18:05','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=395',0,'shop_order','',3),(396,1,'2015-06-03 16:06:58','2015-06-03 16:06:58','','Order &ndash; June 3, 2015 @ 04:06 PM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_556f261e07857','order-jun-03-2015-0406-pm','','','2015-06-03 16:06:58','2015-06-03 16:06:58','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=396',0,'shop_order','',3),(397,1,'2015-06-03 18:16:56','2015-06-03 18:16:56','','Order &ndash; June 3, 2015 @ 06:16 PM','','wc-processing