shop_order','',3),(567,1,'2015-06-07 22:26:44','2015-06-07 22:26:44','','Order &ndash; June 7, 2015 @ 10:26 PM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_5574c52132d41','order-jun-07-2015-1026-pm','','','2015-06-07 22:26:44','2015-06-07 22:26:44','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=567',0,'shop_order','',3),(568,1,'2015-06-07 23:06:43','2015-06-07 23:06:43','','Order &ndash; June 7, 2015 @ 11:06 PM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_5574ce4116fc7','order-jun-07-2015-1105-pm','','','2015-06-07 23:06:43','2015-06-07 23:06:43','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=568',0,'shop_order','',3),(569,1,'2015-06-08 00:13:33','2015-06-08 00:13:33','','Order &ndash; June 8, 2015 @ 12:13 AM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_5574ddbed747c','order-jun-08-2015-1211-am','','','2015-06-08 00:13:33','2015-06-08 00:13:33','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=569',0,'shop_order','',5),(570,5,'2015-06-09 10:10:21','2015-06-09 10:10:21','If thisweek\'s heat spell leaves you suffering from night fever, treat yourself to a Tom Collins and make a splash at this week\'s pride parties, performances, andreadings.\r\n<h2><b>Tuesday</b></h2>\r\nRevisit those precious childhood years via <b><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1596555537279331/\">An Evening with Judy Blume</a></b>, as the renowned author takes on a discussion that promises the answers to all your greatest childhood concerns, or perhaps even your current preoccupations. Watch <b>Alex Cohen</b>, co-host of KPCC\'s Take Two, ask Are you there God? and other more current questions about the authors work and life, and even In The Unlikely Event you can <a href=\"http://lfla.org/event/an-evening-with-judy-blume/\">get your latest copy of her work signed</a>.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"398\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/18/JudyBlume2009(cropped).jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"398\" height=\"444\" /> Courtesy of Wikipedia Commons[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Wednesday</b></h2>\r\nHead over to Little Armenias <strong>Bicycle Coffee</strong> and join <strong>Potluck Magazine</strong> for a reading from touring poet <strong>John Mortara</strong>. Mortara will be <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1680052018885557/\">reading</a> from his new collection <em>Some Planet</em>,with support from local bards including <strong>Melissa Broder</strong> (aka @sosadtoday on twitter), <strong>Joshua Jennifer Espinoza</strong>, and Walk the Nights own <strong>Lucy Tiven</strong>!\r\n\r\nAfter you get your literary fix in, hightail it to Hollywood for <strong>Cats Chorus</strong>, a karaoke <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/993112397379610/\">night</a> with <strong>The Catnip Club</strong>! Make sure you BYOB and come in ears, ready to caterwaul the night away with your Catnip friends.<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Screen-Shot-2015-06-08-at-4.44.48-PM.png\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-577 aligncenter\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Screen-Shot-2015-06-08-at-4.44.48-PM-298x300.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-06-08 at 4.44.48 PM\" width=\"298\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n<h2><b>Thursday</b></h2>\r\nIf youre ready for more than just a laugh, head over to <b>Hollywood Improv</b> to enjoy <a href=\"http://hollywood.improv.com/event.cfm?id=399210\">stand up comedy for a cause</a>. What cause, you ask? The future of all humankind! The nights entertainment is brought to you by the incredible non-profit <b>ImMEDIAte</b> Justice which supports<b></b>professional filmmakers tutoring underserved girls ages 14-18 by teaching them filmmaking with a social justice lens. <b>The Ladies of Comedy Association</b> <b>(LOCA)</b> has rallied to put on a benefit show featuring the likes of shining light comedians <b>Laura Kightlinger</b>,<b> Chelsea Peretti</b>, <b>Eliza Skinner</b>, <b>Janine Brito</b>, <b>Helen Hong</b>, <b>Jenny Yang</b>&amp; even more.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Screen-Shot-2015-06-05-at-3.18.47-PM.jpg\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-576 aligncenter\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Screen-Shot-2015-06-05-at-3.18.47-PM-300x165.jpg\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-06-05 at 3.18.47 PM\" width=\"300\" height=\"165\" /></a>\r\n<h2><b>Friday </b></h2>\r\nIf you\'re feeling like a literary bad boy or girl, join Meredith Ailing, Jerry Gabriel, Porochista Khakpour, Michal Lemberger, Kevin Maloney and host Jim Ruland for <b>Vermin on the Mount</b>, a <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1452766895036647/\">night</a> of irreverent readings sponsored by <b>Razorcake/Gorsky Press, Inc</b>.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"364\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://verminonthemount.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/VERMIN_LA_Web-580x750.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"364\" height=\"471\" /> Courtesy of Vermin on the Mount[/caption]\r\n\r\nAfter the reading, saunter over to <b>Echoplex</b>and hit the<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/879818375408105/\">dancefloor</a> to sets from <b>Blackbird Blackbird</b> + <b>Midnight Magic</b> + <b>Steed Lord</b> + <b>Anzano</b> + <b>Cooper Saver</b>.\r\n<h2><b>Saturday</b></h2>\r\nWant to ring in pride in style? Hit the Lash for <strong>YAS BITCH YASSSSSSSSSS</strong> <strong>(A PRIDE PARTY)</strong>, for sets by dirty &amp; dangerous DJs<strong> Daddy Rose</strong> + <strong>Dirty Rich Kidd</strong> + <strong>Guano</strong> + <strong>Killed By Synth</strong>. With no door charge, it\'s the perfect way to celebrate your weekend and dance the night away Subterranean style.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"397\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://www.justcircuit.com/Portals/0/images/news/lapride2012-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"397\" height=\"263\" /> Courtesy of Just Circuit[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Sunday</b></h2>\r\nSunday is a day to think about the hard questions  such as, how much do you enjoy fun? We thought so. Step into all the fun you could possibly need, while supporting LGBTQIA communities and allies on the culmination of <b>LA Pride week</b>, with <a href=\"http://lapride.org/pride/celebration.html\">the parade and festival</a> that you want to be at, in proud queer style with wigs, body paint, and outfits galore, and some of the best subterraneans around!\r\n\r\nPolish off your pride weekend with <b>Honey Soundsystem</b> at <b>Sound Nightclub</b>. The beloved Bay-area queer house/disco collective will be <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/995082180504691/\">premiering</a> their four-week LA residency for Pride, and will be joined by local sisters <strong>Jeniluv</strong>,<strong> Chris Bowen </strong>and<strong> Victor Rodriguez</strong>. Though tickets will be fifteen dollars at the door, you can snag a $5 presale and skip the line!\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"560\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://smartblogchicago.com/smartbar_new/wp/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/Honey-Soundsystem-Cropped-WEB-%C2%A9ShannaDoherty.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"560\" height=\"200\" /> Honey Soundsystem, Courtesy of Smart Blog Chicago[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Monday</b></h2>\r\nNeed to get your week off to a raunchy <a href=\"http://www.mondaynighttease.com/\">start</a>? Swing by the <strong>3 Clubs</strong> for <strong>Monday Night Tease</strong>, a weekly burlesque show with song, juggling, live bands and a rotating cast.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"311\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://s-media-cache-ak0.pinimg.com/736x/ec/a0/d6/eca0d6c0142b80fc802ec86228779a9d.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"311\" height=\"466\" /> Courtesy of For the Love of Lingerie[/caption]\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the </i>last<i> last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>','Suicide Tuesdays 6/9','','publish','open','open','','suicide-tuesdays-69','','','2015-06-09 01:38:52','2015-06-09 01:38:52','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=570',0,'post','',0),(573,1,'2015-06-08 20:31:26','2015-06-08 20:31:26','','Order &ndash; June 8, 2015 @ 08:31 PM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_5575fb9a1c645','order-jun-08-2015-0831-pm','','','2015-06-08 20:31:26','2015-06-08 20:31:26','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=573',0,'shop_order','',3),(575,5,'2015-06-09 00:01:28','2015-06-09 00:01:28','','Screen Shot 2015-06-05 at 3.18.47 PM (1)','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-06-05-at-3-18-47-pm-1','','','2015-06-09 00:01:28','2015-06-09 00:01:28','',570,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Screen-Shot-2015-06-05-at-3.18.47-PM-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(576,5,'2015-06-09 00:01:44','2015-06-09 00:01:44','','Screen Shot 2015-06-05 at 3.18.47 PM','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-06-05-at-3-18-47-pm','','','2015-06-09 00:01:44','2015-06-09 00:01:44','',570,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Screen-Shot-2015-06-05-at-3.18.47-PM.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(577,5,'2015-06-09 00:01:57','2015-06-09 00:01:57','','Screen Shot 2015-06-08 at 4.44.48 PM','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-06-08-at-4-44-48-pm','','','2015-06-09 00:01:57','2015-06-09 00:01:57','',570,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Screen-Shot-2015-06-08-at-4.44.48-PM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(578,5,'2015-06-09 00:17:49','2015-06-09 00:17:49','','100830944_419d067ce5_o','David Hockney via Flickr Commons','inherit','open','open','','100830944_419d067ce5_o','','','2015-06-09 00:19:13','2015-06-09 00:19:13','',570,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/100830944_419d067ce5_o.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(579,5,'2015-06-09 00:18:23','2015-06-09 00:18:23','','Gay Rights are Human Rights','2011 Capital Pride Parade - Dupont Circle - Washington, DC','inherit','open','open','','gay-rights-are-human-rights','','','2015-06-09 00:18:23','2015-06-09 00:18:23','',570,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/5823033786_5b4f7e39f5_o.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(584,5,'2015-06-09 21:49:01','2015-06-09 21:49:01','<i>I first met Techno Sam at Sunset Campout 2014, when he was kind enough to invite me and my friend to join his camp </i><i> </i><i>he also made us tacos and rallied strongly to get our car keys back from a friend who was passed out at the time.</i>\r\n\r\n<i>I moved to Los Angeles shortly after, and have been lucky enough to accompany him to many parties and undergrounds, including performances by Harriet Brown, an artist from his LA record label, Feel So Real, also featured on this mix.</i>\r\n\r\n[embed]https://soundcloud.com/heywalkthenight/sammy-goes-deep-vol-6-eternal-spring-la-nights-and-other-tales-of-the-balearic[/embed]\r\n\r\n<i>While we have also met each others cats, swapped countless nightlife war stories, and are planning a Koreatown potluck, I wanted to learn a little more about his mixes, label, and Los Angeles upbringing.</i>\r\n\r\n<b>Tell us more about this mix - Its called Sammy Goes Deep Vol. 6: Eternal Spring, LA Nights &amp; Other Tales of the </b><b>Balearic</b><b>.</b>\r\n\r\nThe idea for the mix was really simple and not too different from the general format of my other mixes: I chose tracks that I really love, tracks that I listen to ALL the time by myself or when Im DJing for friends, and I tried to sequence them in a way that creates a compelling journey.\r\n\r\n<b>How did you hope to channel the Balearic in this mix? What does the Balearic or Balearic beat mean to you?</b>\r\n\r\nFor me, Balearic has no restrictions in terms of vibe or tempo. Instead, its more about context and sharing songs that I have a strong personal connection to. I wanted to put a mix out that gets people into the headspace Ive been in regarding DJing lately.\r\n\r\n<b>Would you mind describing that [headspace] a little, or is it best to just let the mix speak for itself?</b>\r\n\r\nListen to the mix ;-)\r\n\r\n<b>This mix features a </b><b>Suzanne Kraft </b><b>mix of Harriet Browns Stop Think that I really love, and youve posted a lot of other great ones on social media and SoundCloud. Why did you choose this one specifically to include?</b>\r\n\r\nI love this remix. Its gorgeous, ultra chill, and brings the mix down a notch to gear up for the big ending. It just fit the vibe I was going for. I love all the other tracks on that release, which features remixes from the homies Cooper Saver, Sage Caswell, and Feel So Reals star producer Alex Talan aka Coolwater.\r\n\r\n<b>Seals Violet pops up on this mix, which I loved </b><b></b><b> I know youre a big fan. For those of our readers who might be less familiar with your mixes or the discography of Seal, wed love to hear you talk a little more! What do you like about this track specifically, and its placement in the mix? It feels very organic, yet also somewhat stark and unexpected.</b>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/06/11424468_10204057676591472_360266308_o-1.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-589 size-medium alignleft\" src=\"http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/06/11424468_10204057676591472_360266308_o-1-199x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"199\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n\r\nI LOVE this song. I hate to use this word, but theres something really epic about Violet. It takes you on a journey, and I love songs that build and have their moment. You have to listen to the whole song because it grabs you and never lets go. Not to mention immaculate production work by Trevor Horn aka The Man Who Invented the 80s. Also, I love to surprise people with my selections, which I think this does properly.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>We met at Sunset </b><b></b><b> because I am a </b><b><i>baby</i></b><b> and deeply beholden to getting at least 6hrs of sleep a night, you caught a lot more of those sets than I did. Which was your favorite? </b>\r\n\r\nOn Sunday morning, while all the suckers were watching Soul Clap, there was an impromptu b2b set between Traxx and Mick Wills. Both are serious selectors that push their audiences with rare and obscure but still very danceable music. I only recognized a few tracks they played the whole morning.\r\n\r\n<b>Will you be attending Sunset this year? If so, what are you looking forward to?</b>\r\n\r\nIm hoping to attend this year. Sunset Campout is my favorite California party, hands down. I havent checked the lineup, but Im stoked just to catch the Sunset residents play. Solar is one of my top favorite DJs and Galens Sunday morning set last year was one of the most fun moments of the party for me.\r\n\r\n<b>At that campout, I believe I passed out in our tent for ~7 hours after consuming some combination of pop tarts and Xanax. In the grand scheme of party fouls, not</b><b><i> too </i></b><b>terrible. Whats the worst thing youve seen recently? </b>\r\n\r\nAt that campout, there was a group of people that were camped next to the communal porta-potties. It literally smelled like shit everywhere, and we began to refer to their camp as Shit City for the rest of the party.\r\n\r\n<b>Wed love to hear a little more about working with Aaron (Harriet Brown) and other Feel So Real projects like Rare Times. What are you guys most excited about doing here in LA? </b>\r\n\r\nWorking with Aaron has been excellent. I absolutely love his music and his unique style, and Im proud that Feel So Real got to formally release his first EP. Mark my words, its only a matter of time before this kid blows up. Everything on the label is closely curated, and Alex (Talan) and I argue for days before we come to agreements on what we can and cant put out. If that means we have a more relaxed release schedule (there are only 6 FSR releases to date), then so be it. We strongly stand behind everything weve put out so far. Its this dynamic that lends itself to a sort-of signature FSR sound that were building towards. Also, Alexs production style is really important as its arguably the largest influence in what shapes the current FSR sound - he produces and mixes virtually everything that comes out on our label. Aside from that, were excited to start doing some FSR branded events soon, and are currently planning our next releases.\r\n\r\n<b>Oooh. What kind of events do yall have in the works?</b>\r\n\r\nIm not ready to share any details yet, but you can keep up with FSR news <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/feelsoreal\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n<b>When I moved here from the Bay Area, I found LA parties and nightlife culture quite different from those of the Bay. How would you describe throwing and attending parties and undergrounds here, compared to other places youve lived like SF or Berlin?</b>\r\n\r\nLAs party scene has a really young and exceptionally diverse energy to it. We party with people of all ages and backgrounds, and all our best parties happen in warehouses instead of clubs. I cant remember the last time I went to an actual venue to see music, which is great, because I hate clubs in America. Too many rules and restrictions.\r\n\r\n<b>Tell us about the last great party or show you attended.</b>\r\n\r\nI caught Floating Points play all night in a warehouse for a Far Away party. Ive been a fan of his since he first started releasing music, so naturally I was excited to finally get to see him play, let alone all night long.\r\n\r\n<b>That show was awesome. When you arent going out, what are your favorite things to do in LA?</b>\r\n\r\nI love cooking and going out to meals with friends. All my closest friends are really into food and we enjoy getting together for drinks and delicious meals. Other than that, LA has some great hikes. I also love playing with cats.\r\n\r\n<b>Were known to play with a cat or two ourselves. Lastly, what LA DJs, labels and collectives most excite you right now?</b>\r\n\r\nI go to pretty much all of the Far Away parties, and my friends at Fine Time are putting together some really well curated and unexpected lineups. Ive also been a big fan of the Droid Behavior parties since I first started partying here almost 10 years ago; they threw the first proper underground I ever went to. Other than that, watch out for the Redline parties which have recently started to gear up, thrown by my good friends Mike Gushansky, who is a DJ for FSR, as well as As You Like It in the Bay, and by Carlos Morales, who is closely involved with the Beat Electric website. Also, two of my favorite ladies, Alison Swing and Masha Mar, are gaining traction and booking some great artists with their Dig Deeper parties. Shoutout!\r\n\r\n<em>Special thanks to photographers Neha Talreja &amp; Jason Klass. </em>\r\n\r\n<em>Follow Walk the Night on <a href=\"https://soundcloud.com/heywalkthenight\">Soundcloud</a> for more exclusive mixes &amp; tracks.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</em>','Shit City: An Interview with Feel So Reals Techno Sam','','publish','open','open','','shit-city-an-interview-with-feel-so-reals-techno-sam','','','2015-09-10 12:01:44','2015-09-10 19:01:44','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=584',0,'post','',0),(585,5,'2015-06-09 20:43:01','2015-06-09 20:43:01','','11424468_10204057676591472_360266308_o','photographed by neha talreja','inherit','open','open','','11424468_10204057676591472_360266308_o','','','2015-06-09 20:52:41','2015-06-09 20:52:41','',584,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/11424468_10204057676591472_360266308_o.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(586,5,'2015-06-09 20:44:08','2015-06-09 20:44:08','','img_0592tinycolorcor','Photographed by  Jason Klass','inherit','open','open','','img_0592tinycolorcor','','','2015-06-09 20:44:44','2015-06-09 20:44:44','',584,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/img_0592tinycolorcor.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(588,5,'2015-06-09 20:56:26','2015-06-09 20:56:26','','11424468_10204057676591472_360266308_o','','inherit','open','open','','11424468_10204057676591472_360266308_o-2','','','2015-06-09 20:56:26','2015-06-09 20:56:26','',584,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/11424468_10204057676591472_360266308_o1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(589,5,'2015-06-09 20:58:15','2015-06-09 20:58:15','','11424468_10204057676591472_360266308_o (1)','','inherit','open','open','','11424468_10204057676591472_360266308_o-1','','','2015-06-09 20:58:15','2015-06-09 20:58:15','',584,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/11424468_10204057676591472_360266308_o-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(609,3,'2015-06-10 20:22:29','2015-06-10 20:22:29','[vc_row full_width=\"\" parallax=\"\" parallax_image=\"\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]<b>The Frolic Room</b>\r\n\r\nOwned in its early days by Howard Hughes, The Frolic Room was attached to Hollywoods Pantages Theater and was a favorite of vaudeville actors. Since its prohibition heyday, the bar has gained a door (the previous entrance being through the Pantages) and a period neon sign, which adds to its jazz-age kitsch.\r\n\r\nNow, the converted speakeasy is beloved by locals for its retro digs, quiet neighborhood ambiance and history of legendary patrons. Most nefariously, the Frolic Room was the last place Elizabeth Short, aka Black Dahlia, was seen alive, but its also hosted its share of local actors, industry legends a la John Belushi, and Oscars pre-show parties in the days when the ceremony was held at the Pantages.\r\n\r\nThe Hollywood joint is also rumored to have been one of poet Charles Bukowskis haunts, keeping Hank Chinaski alive with a portrait over the register Yelpers occasionally mistake for a poorly drawn Jesus, and by stocking lots of Cutty Sark whisky behind the bar  which also features 70s red walls and a mural by <i>New York Times </i>caricaturist Al Hirschfield.\r\n\r\nWidely considered Hollywood Boulevards last true dive, The Frolic Room is a must-see destination for cinema and LA history buffs as well as locals looking for a quaint, tourist-free spot to imbibe. A vintage cigarette machine completes the rooms old school Los Angeles look, while its television plays atmospheric movies on mute as a jukebox blasts an esoteric mix of classics from Fleetwood Mac to Bowie to Birdman.\r\n\r\nFancied as a drinkers bar, the Frolic Room comes most alive at night, but is also a great place to grab an after-work drink, mingle, or even read a book during the day. The small, historic dive has been hailed as one of the last true cross-sections of Hollywood, where entertainment CEOs can be caught sipping martinis and breaking bread (or Jiffy Pop, the house favorite snack) with the young and broke crowd.\r\n\r\nThe Frolic Room lies conveniently across from the Vine/Hollywood Red Line metro station entrance, right by the Gary Cooper star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame. Despite its central location, the venue is typically quiet and has a reputation for keeping out particularly sauced or belligerent street traffic.\r\n\r\nBartenders don suits, adding to the noir, old-world quality, and walls feature caricatures of Einstein and Groucho Marx. Regulars are fond of the stiff drinks, particularly the Scooby Snack, though you might also do well to follow Bukowskis advice:\r\n\r\nstay with the beer.\r\n\r\nbeer is continuous blood.\r\n\r\na continuous lover.\r\n\r\n<b>The Lowdown</b>\r\n\r\nThe Frolic Room is a converted speakeasy-turned-dive, well-known by locals as one of Hollywoods last real dive bars. Highlights include cheap drinks, freshly popped Jiffy Pop, and the chance to make a toast with Charles Bukowskis ghost.\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text css_animation=\"\"][templatera id=\"349\"][/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Frolic Room','','publish','open','open','','frolic-room','','','2015-08-12 18:30:00','2015-08-13 01:30:00','',201,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?page_id=609',0,'page','',0),(611,7,'2015-06-10 20:26:55','2015-06-10 20:26:55','[vc_row full_width=\"\" parallax=\"\" parallax_image=\"\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]<b>Playhouse Nightclub</b>\r\n\r\nComplete with acrobats, go-go dancing and LED-lit checkholders, Playhouse Nightclub brings a little Vegas to Hollywood, but not too much.\r\n\r\nBehind the vintage theater facade lies a dizzyingly modern dance hall venue, complete with VIP lounges, Funktion 1 Sound and retractable skylight.\r\n\r\nThe club was named as one of <a href=\"http://uk.reuters.com/article/2010/06/04/us-travel-picks-nightclubs-idUKTRE6531ZX20100604\">Reuters Top Ten Nightclubs in the World</a> and boasts a world-class sound system designed by Dane Agne from Sound Investments. Theyve hosted a wide range of world-class acts, from Jermaine Dupri to Nick Cannon to Tisto, though weve heard there are also quieter nights when a resident DJ spins bass and electro house.\r\n\r\nHelmed by Music Lifestyle Group partners Rob Vinokur and Mikayel Israelyan since 2009, the showy Hollywood Club has drawn the likes of Justin Timberlake, Gerard Butler and Rhianna  so getting in can be a little tricky if you arent a celebrity or friend of the promoter, and non-VIP sections arent for the crowd-weary. If youre lucky enough to make it in, you might even brush shoulders with the Hollywood elite at the bar or, more likely, while dodging the occasional blast of dry ice that douses the downstairs dance floor.\r\n\r\nDespite its myriad amenities, party tricks and glam clientele, The Playhouse is best known for top-shelf service. Each VIP table is allotted an individual host, as well as a personal VIP bottle hostess  though, if youve got your sights set on one of these, we recommend making a reservation and RSVPing early.\r\n\r\nEach room is lit with colorful lights and lasers, and burlesque and go-go dancers are tucked into the clubs many enclaves. If you look up, you might catch your server suspended from one of the Playhouses high ceilings  many bartenders double as trapeze artists, though we arent sure exactly what staff training entails, or where they source such versatile talent.\r\n\r\nIf youre looking for a hip, sexy circus and arent afraid to wait in line for the bathroom, look no further than the Playhouse.\r\n\r\n<b>The Lowdown</b>\r\n\r\nRanked the #4 nightclub in the world, Playhouse Nightclub is open Thursday through Sunday, offering bustling parties sometimes even attended by big name celebrities. The 13,000-square-foot nightclub was formerly The Fox Theatre, and maintains some classic theater architecture  even if its now adorned with intelligent disco lights and used to suspend caged-in burlesque dancers over its rowdy crowds of A-listers and socialites.\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text css_animation=\"\"][templatera id=\"349\"][/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Playhouse Nightclub','','publish','open','open','','playhousehollywood','','','2015-10-15 11:52:55','2015-10-15 18:52:55','',201,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?page_id=611',0,'page','',0),(615,1,'2015-06-10 21:51:42','2015-06-10 21:51:42','','Order &ndash; June 10, 2015 @ 09:51 PM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_5578b169ddf97','order-jun-10-2015-0951-pm','','','2015-06-10 21:51:42','2015-06-10 21:51:42','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=615',0,'shop_order','',3),(620,1,'2015-06-10 23:01:56','2015-06-10 23:01:56','','Order &ndash; June 10, 2015 @ 11:01 PM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_5578c1a083330','order-jun-10-2015-1100-pm','','','2015-06-10 23:01:56','2015-06-10 23:01:56','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=620',0,'shop_order','',3),(624,4,'2015-06-11 00:11:07','2015-06-11 00:11:07','[vc_row full_width=\"\" parallax=\"\" parallax_image=\"\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]Burlesque acts, tightrope walkers, and snappily dressed bar staff make the inside of No Vacancy as unique as the venues Victorian exterior.\r\n\r\nDreamed up by the Houston brothers, the club abides by the usual Hollywood speakeasy rules: <i>Shiny Shirts, Shorts, Sports Gear, Logos, Flip Flops, Most Hats and Loud Colors are Highly Discouraged.</i>\r\n\r\nHouse DJ sets and the late-night house band mostly observe the Prohibition theme, playing jazz, blues, and bluegrass as well as more traditional dance-fare, while Wednesday night Porch Sessions showcase particularly exciting new and local talent.\r\n\r\nGin is the drink of choice  the bar features subtle, pared-down classic cocktails and modern updates curated by iconic mixologists like Adrian Biggs, Dave Fernie, Francois Vera, and Jim Meehan. Beer drinkers are just as welcome, and can enjoy Magic Hat #9 and other American draft brews for a bargain $5, or choose from No Vacancys modest bottled selection. Wine and champagne are also available, but run $10-15 a glass and are mostly West Coast varietals.\r\n\r\nA fiver can also snag you a grilled cheese from the pop-up grill, if you feel the drunchies setting in from too many Gin and Jamesons (Jameson, Beefeater, lime, grapefruit, orgeat syrup and honey)  or a kitschy trinket from the gift shop.\r\n\r\nLike other Houston spots, No Vacancy lies a little off the map, featuring a red-carpet-lined back entrance and clever three-door entry (tip: ask when the house was built).\r\n\r\nThe venue has all the nooks and crannies, classic moldings, and fireplaces that the mark the best historic Victorian homes, and fully commits to period with antique torches and lush detailing in red velour and tufted leather. Guests are encouraged to sip gin and bitters from an antique glass, or snap a selfie in the retro phone-turned-photo booth.\r\n\r\nFlappers and jazz cats seeking a more intimate experience can reserve a private room upstairs with bottle service and a private bar, while those whose pockets are feeling a bit more recession-era are advised to get a little dressed up to get through the door.\r\n\r\nWith a vibrant dance floor, modern amenities, and swanky (or hotsy-totsy, in 20s vernacular) vintage trinkets strewn about, No Vacancy is a great spot to swap war stories or Charleston the night away between stock market crashes.\r\n\r\n<b>The Lowdown</b>\r\n\r\nNo Vacancy is a 20s-style speakeasy with a diverse roster of live performances and nightly DJ sets. Housed in a restored Victorian home, the club is most known for its eye candy, boasting multiple fireplaces, classy retro furnishings and vintage glassware. The bar features signature gin drinks created by big name mixologists and decadent liquor punches for big groups.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text css_animation=\"\"][templatera id=\"349\"][/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]','No Vacancy','','publish','open','open','','novacancyla','','','2015-08-12 18:42:07','2015-08-13 01:42:07','',201,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?page_id=624',0,'page','',0),(628,4,'2015-06-11 00:35:12','2015-06-11 00:35:12','[vc_row full_width=\"\" parallax=\"\" parallax_image=\"\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\n[templatera id=\"362\"]\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\n[templatera id=\"361\"]\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Module - Series Page Sidebar','','publish','closed','closed','','template-series-page','','','2015-10-15 12:31:46','2015-10-15 19:31:46','',0,'ht