 Alison Swing, The Black Madonna and Masha, Photographed by Erin Keefe\" width=\"462\" height=\"309\" /></a> DJs Alison Swing, The Black Madonna and Masha, Photographed by Erin Keefe[/caption]\r\n\r\nLast Saturdays Dig Deeper party brought a powerhouse of female DJs, with awesome sets from Masha, Alison Swing, and the Black Madonna.\r\n<h2>Tech Noir / Health Goth</h2>\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1008\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://www.mixmag.net/assets/uploads/images/_full/drapehouse.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1008\" height=\"672\" /> Courtesy of Mix Mag[/caption]\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://www.wweek.com/portland/imgs/media.images/20996/lede_faq.widea.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"622\" height=\"455\" />\r\n\r\nWe cant exactly make out your faces, but you cloaked drape housers &amp; health goths<a href=\"http://mixmag.net/read/drape-house-is-the-new-fashion-trend-in-las-underground-scene-fashion\">look</a> pretty cool from here.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Going-Down-Barometer.png\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-646 aligncenter\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Going-Down-Barometer-300x258.png\" alt=\"Going Down (Barometer)\" width=\"300\" height=\"258\" /></a>\r\n<h2>Bromance</h2>\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"500\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://c4.staticflickr.com/4/3401/3269109274_a4b4f4b41e.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"335\" /> Courtesy of Flickr Commons[/caption]\r\n\r\nLet the <em>Entourage Movie</em> box office numbers speak for themselves.\r\n<h2>Shia Lebouf</h2>\r\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nuHfVn_cfHU[/embed]\r\n\r\nDo what? Refill your adderall prescription?\r\n<h2>Crust Punk</h2>\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"720\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://squattheplanet.com/attachments/167109_652689348179_2807762_36762388_7252286_n-jpg.21578/\" alt=\"\" width=\"720\" height=\"478\" /> Courtesy of Squat The Planet[/caption]\r\n\r\nNo, I will not yield to your tall bike.\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the </i>last<i> last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>','Barometer 6/11','','publish','open','open','','barometer-611','','','2015-06-11 21:16:22','2015-06-11 21:16:22','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=634',0,'post','',0),(635,5,'2015-06-11 17:47:59','2015-06-11 17:47:59','','barometer','','inherit','open','open','','barometer','','','2015-06-11 17:47:59','2015-06-11 17:47:59','',634,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/barometer.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(637,5,'2015-06-11 18:02:51','2015-06-11 18:02:51','','barometer-small-09','','inherit','open','open','','barometer-small-09','','','2015-06-11 18:02:51','2015-06-11 18:02:51','',634,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/barometer-small-09.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(642,5,'2015-06-11 18:39:32','2015-06-11 18:39:32','','Screen Shot 2015-06-11 at 11.38.26 AM','DJs Alison Swing, The Black Madonna and Masha, Photographed by Erin Keefe','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-06-11-at-11-38-26-am','','','2015-06-11 18:40:17','2015-06-11 18:40:17','',634,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Screen-Shot-2015-06-11-at-11.38.26-AM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(645,5,'2015-06-11 20:18:56','2015-06-11 20:18:56','','Going Up (Barometer)','','inherit','open','open','','going-up-barometer','','','2015-06-11 20:18:56','2015-06-11 20:18:56','',634,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Going-Up-Barometer.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(646,5,'2015-06-11 20:19:00','2015-06-11 20:19:00','','Going Down (Barometer)','','inherit','open','open','','going-down-barometer','','','2015-06-11 20:19:00','2015-06-11 20:19:00','',634,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Going-Down-Barometer.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(650,5,'2015-06-11 20:48:58','2015-06-11 20:48:58','','barometer-small-09','','inherit','open','open','','barometer-small-09-2','','','2015-06-11 20:48:58','2015-06-11 20:48:58','',634,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/barometer-small-09.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(652,5,'2015-06-11 21:06:54','2015-06-11 21:06:54','','barometer-small-09-08','','inherit','open','open','','barometer-small-09-08','','','2015-06-11 21:06:54','2015-06-11 21:06:54','',634,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/barometer-small-09-08.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(653,5,'2015-06-11 21:14:44','2015-06-11 21:14:44','','barometer-small-09-08','','inherit','open','open','','barometer-small-09-08-2','','','2015-06-11 21:14:44','2015-06-11 21:14:44','',634,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/barometer-small-09-081.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(654,1,'2015-06-12 05:38:11','2015-06-12 05:38:11','','Order &ndash; June 12, 2015 @ 05:38 AM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_557a703fccd2c','order-jun-12-2015-0538-am','','','2015-06-12 05:38:11','2015-06-12 05:38:11','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=654',0,'shop_order','',3),(655,1,'2015-06-12 14:58:16','2015-06-12 14:58:16','','Order &ndash; June 12, 2015 @ 02:58 PM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_557af383b5d35','order-jun-12-2015-0258-pm','','','2015-06-12 14:58:16','2015-06-12 14:58:16','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=655',0,'shop_order','',3),(656,5,'2015-06-13 03:36:32','2015-06-13 03:36:32','This week, civil rights activist <strong>Rachel Dolezal</strong> <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/jun/12/civil-rights-activist-rachel-dolezal-misrepresented-herself-as-black-claim-parents\">was</a> outed for misrepresenting her race.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Slate</strong> </em>reminded us of the feminist issue of the diva <a href=\"http://www.slate.com/articles/double_x/doublex/2015/06/menstrual_cups_are_a_feminist_issue_they_re_healthy_eco_friendly_and_good.html?wpsrc=fol_fb\">cup</a>, while <strong>Thinx</strong> <a href=\"http://www.artinfactmag.com/culture-dish/thinx-underwear-period-panties/\">launched</a> a line of menstrual-specific underwear. Our technology is completely new to market, and its patent-pending, says marketing director Veronica del Rosario. Its really game-changing for women in terms of it being <a href=\"http://www.shethinx.com/technology/\"><strong>four layers of awesome</strong></a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Elizabeth Ellen</strong> <a href=\"http://www.hobartpulp.com/web_features/6-poems--9\">shared</a> poems about Drake and Frida Kahlo on <em><strong>Hobart</strong></em>.\r\n\r\nOver at <em>Electric Literature</em>, Ursula Leguin <a href=\"http://electricliterature.com/ursula-k-le-guin-i-keep-asking-you-not-to-buy-books-from-amazon/\">told</a> us not us to buy books from Amazon, saying:\r\n\r\n<em>The profit motive often is in conflict with the aims of art. We live in capitalism. Its power seems inescapable. So did the divine right of kings. Any human power can be resisted and changed by human beings. Resistance and change often begin in art, and very often in our artthe art of words.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>I have had a long career and a good one. In good company. Now here, at the end of it, I really dont want to watch American literature get sold down the river. We who live by writing and publishing wantand should demandour fair share of the proceeds. But the name of our beautiful reward is not profit. Its na</em><em>me is freedom.</em>\r\n\r\nWith the third season of <strong><em>Orange is the New Black</em></strong> live on <strong>Netflix</strong>, <em>After Ellen</em> sat down with <strong>Laverne Cox</strong> and <strong>Selenis Leyva</strong> to discuss the new <a href=\"http://www.afterellen.com/tv/436239-laverne-cox-selenis-leyva-season-3-surprises-orange-new-black\">episodes</a>.\r\n\r\nActress <strong>Zoe Saldana</strong>\'s husband <a href=\"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/06/08/zoe-saldana-husband-last-name-_n_7536974.html\">took</a> her name, while <em>Dazed</em> had us oogling <strong>Denmark</strong>s cushy rehab <a href=\"http://www.dazeddigital.com/artsandculture/article/25022/1/denmark-is-sending-young-drug-addicts-on-caribbean-cruises\">cruises</a>.\r\n\r\n<em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</em>','Thank Fuck It\'s Friday 6/12','','publish','open','open','','thank-fuck-its-friday-612','','\nhttp://www.artinfactmag.com/culture-dish/thinx-underwear-period-panties/','2015-06-13 03:39:19','2015-06-13 03:39:19','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=656',0,'post','',0),(658,5,'2015-06-13 03:35:57','2015-06-13 03:35:57','','Laverne_Cox_at_Paley_Fest_Orange_Is_The_New_Black','Courtesy of Wikipedia Commons ','inherit','open','open','','laverne_cox_at_paley_fest_orange_is_the_new_black','','','2015-06-13 03:36:19','2015-06-13 03:36:19','',656,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Laverne_Cox_at_Paley_Fest_Orange_Is_The_New_Black.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(660,5,'2015-06-13 03:38:56','2015-06-13 03:38:56','','article-2611631-1D4D335C00000578-367_634x453','via Thinx','inherit','open','open','','article-2611631-1d4d335c00000578-367_634x453','','','2015-06-13 03:39:07','2015-06-13 03:39:07','',656,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/article-2611631-1D4D335C00000578-367_634x453.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(662,1,'2015-06-14 07:52:22','2015-06-14 07:52:22','','Order &ndash; June 14, 2015 @ 07:52 AM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_557d32aed5787','order-jun-14-2015-0752-am','','','2015-06-14 07:52:22','2015-06-14 07:52:22','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=662',0,'shop_order','',3),(663,1,'2015-06-16 01:04:14','2015-06-16 01:04:14','','Order &ndash; June 16, 2015 @ 01:04 AM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_557f760ac4564','order-jun-16-2015-0104-am','','','2015-06-16 01:04:14','2015-06-16 01:04:14','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=663',0,'shop_order','',3),(664,5,'2015-06-16 10:40:54','2015-06-16 10:40:54','Already polished off OITNB? No problem,subterraneans. Distract yourselfat this week\'s best parties &amp; performances.\r\n\r\n<strong>Tuesday</strong>\r\n\r\nIf Junes got you talkin about <strong>Harry Nilsson</strong>, who can blame ya? Hit Silver Lake <a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/event/a-tribute-to-harry-nilsson-5603398\">tonight</a> for a tribute to the iconic songwriter &amp; recording artist, with covers from <strong>Henry Wolfe</strong> to <strong>Leslie Stevens</strong>, to Nilsson\'s son <strong>Kief</strong>. If youre new to Nilsson, we recommend pregaming the nights entertainment with the documentary <strong><em>Who Is Harry Nilsson (And Why Is Everybody Talkin\' About Him)?</em></strong> streaming on Netflix.\r\n\r\n[embed]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2AzEY6ZqkuE[/embed]\r\n\r\n<strong>Wednesday </strong>\r\n\r\nHightail it <a href=\"http://la.racked.com/2015/6/4/8726197/joie-equipment-current-elliott-warehouse-sale-june-2015\">over</a> to <strong>Siren Studios</strong> with your wallet in hand (but not your bag! these must be checked at the door) for a sample sale from fashion mavens <strong>Equipment, Joie and Current/Elliott</strong>. You might wanna get there a little early if you want first pick of the lines, and to wear something you can quickly and easily slip off and on, to cut down fitting room time.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"620\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://www.redcarpet-fashionawards.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Sophia-Bushs-CurrentElliott-Star-Stiletto-Jeans.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"620\" height=\"478\" /> Sophia Bush in Current/Elliot, Courtesy of Red Carpet Fashion Awards[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>Thursday</strong> 6/18\r\n\r\nCruise down Sunset to the <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/766631996787578/\"><strong>Iam8bit Anniversary Show</strong></a>. Its their 10th anniversary as a creative collective and gallery space, which means theyve had a lot of time to curate this show! The opening reception promises a huge spectrum of artists (over 100 we hear) from all over the globe, who reinvent our gaming memories of yesteryear. Anticipate plenty of divers images of consoles, Gameboys, hand-held devices and the fascinating revivification of long-forgotten pixelated memories from your younger days, accompanied by tunes by <strong>DJ R-Rated</strong>.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"970\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://nerdist.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/72dpi-Mark_Harrison-Keep_On_Workin-970x545.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"970\" height=\"545\" /> Courtesy of Nerdist[/caption]\r\n\r\nOnce your undead daydreams of childhood games (or your present enthusiasms) have been satiated, you might want to indulge in a little more witchery. <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/383300898545505/\"><strong>H/O/M/O/C/C/U/L/T</strong></a> brings the Bruja booty bass and queer dark shades of the rainbow, as delivered by the undisputed empress of Australian queer parties, <strong>DJ Romy.</strong> Be dark, be glittery, bring your best moves and take out your toil and trouble on the dance floor!\r\n\r\n<strong>Friday</strong>\r\n\r\nSpend your Friday right with an evening of deep discussion at a <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/430775830427375/\"><strong>BigQueerConvo</strong></a>, for the kick-off of <strong>Trans Pride LA</strong>. With past guests including the delights of such trans glitterati as <strong>Laverne Cox</strong> and <strong>Buck Angel</strong>, anticipate some brilliant lights and impressive voices to hear and see, including Sandy Stone, one of the originators of transgender studies, as well as Kate Bornstein.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://thenextfamily.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/11140760_859061444161392_9010857197338137802_o.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"2048\" height=\"757\" />\r\n\r\nThen, <a href=\"http://learningcurvela.org/bigqueerconvo\">grab a drink with them</a> to get pumped for <strong>Trans Pride LA</strong> <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/430775830427375/\">festival</a>: a day of community outreach, music and dancing, with performances in the evening and maybe a spot of self-defense for queers who want to emerge fore-armed for life in a straight world. Highlights include a Name and Gender Change Clinic, with legal assistance on hand.\r\n\r\nIf youre looking to boogie, head <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/817774624968215/\">over</a> to Moony Habits to catch sets from DJ Dez Andrs &amp; Mark de Clive-Lowe &amp; his full band CHURCH. With trumpets blaring and an opening set by residents JoJo Armani (Moony Habits) &amp; Leja Hazer (Hesperian Sound Division), this party should get all you subterraneans in the weekend groove.\r\n\r\nKeep your night going at <strong>Restless Nights</strong><strong> Transit</strong> afterhours party, with sets from Vancouvers mysterious <strong>Hashman Deejay</strong>, <strong>Masha</strong>, <strong>Marshall Lake &amp; Simonowsky</strong>. Make sure to snag your presale &amp; <a href=\"http://www.restlessnites.com/transit/\">RSVP</a> on Restless Nights for the secret location.\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHead over to <strong>The Lyric</strong> to catch sets from <strong>Breakfast, Benedek, Harriet Brown</strong> and more, plus a DJ set from our pal <strong>Techno Sam</strong>! After all, who doesnt love breakfast after dinner?\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"293\"]<img src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xpa1/v/t1.0-9/10959434_736884916424840_8876063227715183893_n.jpg?oh=fc77842c8a75034616777c264fdb3589&amp;oe=55F269DF\" alt=\"\" width=\"293\" height=\"293\" /> Harriet Brown Photographed by J Barbagelott[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>Sunday</strong>\r\n\r\nNeed to infuse the ecstasy of movement into the coming week? Head down down Westwood for Alyssa Aparicios<strong> Sacred Dance of Sensuality</strong> <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/833610546747111/\">workshop</a>.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xaf1/v/t1.0-9/11393083_10152838307770248_6412219054658367993_n.jpg?oh=e4a0e1616a11c23e73b62eee3bd10181&amp;oe=55EA01A8\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"637\" />\r\n\r\nAfter youve gotten in touch with your sensual side and moved a bit, stick around for <strong>Amore One/DJ Ecstatic Dance</strong>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Monday</strong>\r\n\r\nDrop in to <strong>Book Soup</strong> to ring your Monday in like a <a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/event/stephen-witt-5673594\">pirate</a>  a data pirate, that is. Author <strong>Stephen Witt</strong> will discuss his new title <em>How Music Got Free: The End of an Industry, the Turn of the Century, and the Patient Zero of Piracy</em>, which brags that it goes beyond Napster and flushes out the full history of leakage, the mp3, and more.\r\n\r\n<em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Suicide Tuesdays 6/16','','publish','open','open','','suicide-tuesdays-616','','','2015-06-16 17:20:24','2015-06-16 17:20:24','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=664',0,'post','',0),(665,1,'2015-06-16 04:02:55','2015-06-16 04:02:55','','Order &ndash; June 16, 2015 @ 04:02 AM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_557f9feaf2d97','order-jun-16-2015-0402-am','','','2015-06-16 04:02:55','2015-06-16 04:02:55','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=665',0,'shop_order','',3),(666,5,'2015-06-16 04:08:38','2015-06-16 04:08:38','','Harry_Nilsson_(1974)','','inherit','open','open','','harry_nilsson_1974','','','2015-06-16 04:08:38','2015-06-16 04:08:38','',664,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Harry_Nilsson_1974.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(672,5,'2015-06-18 00:45:25','2015-06-18 00:45:25','Did you make it to LAs inaugural <strong>Redline</strong> party?\r\n\r\nWe swooned to an ethereal set from Benedek featuring live instrumentals and grooved to eclectic beats by <strong>Hunee</strong>, while Cosmic <strong>Champagne</strong> &amp; <strong>Conor</strong> kept us dancing til sunrise.\r\n\r\nIf you didn\'t make it out, dont get too wrapped up in party envy  though details are still top secret (<em>shhhh!</em>), weve heard theyre launching a series of underground parties in LA.\r\n\r\nDreamed up by some of our favorite local talents, <strong>Carlos Morales</strong> (DJ <strong>Cosmic Champagne</strong>)&amp; <strong>Mike Gushansky</strong>, you can expect sultry disco beats &amp; heady subterranean vibes.\r\n\r\nIn the meantime, we recommend grabbing your passport and heading a bitsouth of the border to catch Sessions this weekend. With <strong>Honey Soundsystem</strong>s <strong>Jason Kendig</strong> headlining, you might have to get back on duolingo for this one. Or, if you want it quick &amp;dirty, try <em>Me pones una caa por favor?</em>,which were almost positive means \"a beer, please!\"\r\n\r\n<em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</em>','Redline & Sessions','','publish','open','open','','redline-sessions','','','2015-06-18 00:47:45','2015-06-18 00:47:45','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=672',0,'post','',0),(673,5,'2015-06-18 00:29:43','2015-06-18 00:29:43','','GUSH','','inherit','open','open','','gush','','','2015-06-18 00:29:43','2015-06-18 00:29:43','',672,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/GUSH.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(684,4,'2015-06-18 01:08:34','2015-06-18 01:08:34','','loading','','inherit','open','open','','loading','','','2015-06-18 01:08:34','2015-06-18 01:08:34','',5,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/loading.gif',0,'attachment','image/gif',0),(685,1,'2015-06-18 04:46:17','2015-06-18 04:46:17','','Order &ndash; June 18, 2015 @ 04:46 AM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_55824d15d9e32','order-jun-18-2015-0446-am','','','2015-06-18 04:46:17','2015-06-18 04:46:17','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=685',0,'shop_order','',3),(687,1,'2015-06-19 19:10:04','2015-06-19 19:10:04','','Order &ndash; June 19, 2015 @ 07:10 PM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_558469092fa24','order-jun-19-2015-0710-pm','','','2015-06-19 19:10:04','2015-06-19 19:10:04','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=687',0,'shop_order','',3),(690,5,'2015-06-19 20:17:01','2015-06-19 20:17:01','<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Going-Up-Barometer.png\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-645 aligncenter\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Going-Up-Barometer-300x258.png\" alt=\"Going Up (Barometer)\" width=\"300\" height=\"258\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThis week, <strong>Japan</strong> went footloose, amending its no-dancing laws. The <strong><a href=\"http://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2015/06/17/national/japan-eases-late-night-restrictions-dance-clubs/#.VYFQ9lVVhHy\">Japan Times</a></strong> reports that venues open for long periods of time will be monitored by local police who will measure illumination in the clubs\' seating areas and permit dimmer light in dance areas, given that light settings can vary on the dancefloor.\"\r\n\r\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ltrMfT4Qz5Y[/embed]\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, <strong>China</strong><a href=\"http://www.mixmag.net/read/theres-about-to-be-a-rave-at-the-great-wall-of-china-news\">announced</a> its second YinYang festival, a rave held by the eponymous <strong>Great Wall</strong>.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"467\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6f/The_Great_Wall_of_China_at_Jinshanling.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"467\" height=\"310\" /> Courtesy of Wikipedia Commons[/caption]\r\n\r\nA little closer to home, <strong>Burner Air</strong> is offering pricey private flights to <strong>Burning Man</strong> - if you have an extra grand lying around and dont wanna suffer another rideshare with someone keying bumps of ketamine across the Nevada border.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" aligncenter\" src=\"http://static1.squarespace.com/static/53bd60c3e4b026326f83a899/t/55555481e4b0d953929376f1/1431655561405/Burner_Air_Flights_to_Burning_Man_2015.png?format=1500w\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"938\" />\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Going-Down-Barometer.png\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-646 aligncenter\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Going-Down-Barometer-300x258.png\" alt=\"Going Down (Barometer)\" width=\"300\" height=\"258\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<img class=\" alignright\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/03/Soundcloud_Shiny_Icon.svg/2000px-Soundcloud_Shiny_Icon.svg.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"143\" height=\"143\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Soundcloud </strong><a href=\"http://www.mixmag.net/read/soundcloud-makes-more-controversial-changes-to-service-news\">announced</a> a daily play limit on tracks hosted externally. As reported by <strong>Mixmag</strong>, the idea is part of the company\'s move to crack down on \"abuse\" of creator content, and to introduce their ads in a less invasive fashion but may scare off some of the sites customer base.\r\n\r\nAn <strong>NPR</strong> guest spot by <strong>Kim Kardashian</strong> left some public radio listeners more than a little peeved. <strong>The Chicago Tribune</strong> <a href=\"http://www.chicagotribune.com/business/ct-kim-kardashian-npr-backlash-0620-biz-20150619-story.html\">reports</a>:\r\n\r\n<em>Listeners apparently were not impressed, and hundreds of complaints flooded NPR\'s email inbox this week, including people who threatened to pull their donations to the nonprofit radio network. That prompted Elizabeth Jensen, NPR\'s ombudsman, to post a <a href=\"http://www.npr.org/sections/ombudsman/2015/06/17/415203751/what-s-all-the-kommotion-about-kim-kardashian-west-on-wait-wait\">response </a>on the organization\'s website Wednesday about the \"kommotion\" caused by Kardashian\'s guest spot.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>\"I\'m still not sure what to make of this week\'s outrage over Kardashian, who was indeed a surprising guest, given how often the show has pilloried her and her clan in the past,\" Jensen said. \"She wasn\'t a great guest  she had a couple funny lines  but she was gracious.\"</em>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://www.famefacts.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/kim-kardashian-crying-face-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"394\" /> Courtesy of Fame Facts[/caption]\r\n\r\nAfter <a href=\"http://www.avclub.com/article/brian-williams-apologizes-gets-banished-msnbc-221066\">apologizing</a> for his tall-tales,<strong>Brian Williams</strong>was relegated to an outpost at <strong>MSNBC</strong>. Ouch.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"374\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://c1.staticflickr.com/9/8058/8250502754_03da52f67d_b.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"374\" height=\"561\" /> Courtesy of Flickr Commons[/caption]\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>','Barometer 6/19','','publish','open','open','','barometer-619','','','2015-06-19 20:17:01','2015-06-19 20:17:01','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=690',0,'post','',0),(692,5,'2015-06-19 20:09:49','2015-06-19 20:09:49','','kevin-bacon-footloose','Courtesy of Social News Daily ','inherit','open','open','','kevin-bacon-footloose','','','2015-06-19 20:10:28','2015-06-19 20:10:28','',690,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/kevin-bacon-footloose.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(694,5,'2015-06-19 21:12:28','2015-06-19 21:12:28','Dancing in the moonlight is the perfect way to beat the LA heat.\r\n\r\nHead downtown to <strong>Moony Habits</strong> to groove to sets formDJ Dez Andrs &amp; Mark de Clive-Lowe &amp; his full band CHURCH.\r\n\r\nResidentsJoJo Armani (Moony Habits) &amp; Leja Hazer (Hesperian Sound Division) will bemixing beats to keep you dancing \'til you drop. <a href=\"http://www.residentadvisor.net/event.aspx?719083\">Snag</a> your tickets on <strong>Resident Advisor</strong>!\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Moony Habits : DJ Dez Andrs & Mark de Clive-Lowe & CHURCH.','','publish','open','open','','moony-habits-dj-dez-andres-mark-de-clive-lowe-church','','','2015-06-19 21:24:41','2015-06-19 21:24:41','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=694',0,'post','',0),(695,5,'2015-06-19 21:08:32','20