uit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>','Barometer 6/25','','publish','open','open','','barometer-625','','','2015-06-25 21:42:47','2015-06-25 21:42:47','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=713',0,'post','',0),(714,5,'2015-06-25 21:05:55','2015-06-25 21:05:55','','9562569088_948acea9ed_o','Courtesy of Flickr Commons','inherit','open','open','','9562569088_948acea9ed_o','','','2015-06-25 21:06:23','2015-06-25 21:06:23','',713,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/9562569088_948acea9ed_o.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(715,5,'2015-06-25 21:24:11','2015-06-25 21:24:11','','17029800149_017e072099_z','Courtesy of Flickr Commons','inherit','open','open','','17029800149_017e072099_z','','','2015-06-25 21:25:42','2015-06-25 21:25:42','',713,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/17029800149_017e072099_z.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(717,5,'2015-06-25 21:41:53','2015-06-25 21:41:53','','8566730507_56eee6f789_z','Photographed by Gage Skidmore via Flickr Commons','inherit','open','open','','8566730507_56eee6f789_z','','','2015-06-25 21:42:30','2015-06-25 21:42:30','',713,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/8566730507_56eee6f789_z.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(719,5,'2015-06-26 23:40:57','2015-06-26 23:40:57','This morning, <b>The Supreme Court</b> <a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2015/06/27/us/supreme-court-same-sex-marriage.html\">voted</a> to legalize gay marriage in all 50 states!\r\n\r\n<b>Justice Kennedy</b> <a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2015/us/2014-term-supreme-court-decision-same-sex-marriage.html?ref=liveblog\">wrote</a> in favor of the decision:\r\n\r\n\"No union is more profound than marriage, for it embodies the highest ideals of love, fidelity, devotion, sacrifice, and family. In forming a marital union, two people become something greater than once they were. As some of the petitioners in these cases demonstrate, marriage embodies a love that may endure even past death. It would misunderstand these men and women to say they disrespect the idea of marriage. Their plea is that they do respect it, respect it so deeply that they seek to find its fulfillment for themselves. Their hope is not to be condemned to live in loneliness, excluded from one of civilizations oldest institutions. They ask for equal dignity in the eyes of the law. The Constitution grants them that right.\"\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, <b>Chief Justice Thomas</b> remained firm in his dissenting position, asserting:\r\n\r\nThe majoritys decision is an act of will, not legal judgment. The right it announces has no basis in the Constitution or this Courts precedent. The majority expressly disclaims judicial caution and omits even a pretense of humility, openly relying on its desire to remake society according to its own new insight into the nature of injustice. Ante, at 11, 23. As a result, the Court invalidates the marriage laws of more than half the States and orders the transformation of a social institution that has formed the basis of human society for millennia, for the Kalahari Bushmen and the Han Chinese, the Carthaginians and the Aztecs. Just who do we think we are?\r\n\r\n<b>The White House</b> wasted no time before celebrating with a new <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/WhiteHouse/photos/a.437372744237.233573.63811549237/10153564889214238/?type=1\">logo</a>, while on <b>The New York Times</b> <b>Opinion</b>, <b>Timothy-Stewart Winter</b> <a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2015/06/28/opinion/sunday/the-price-of-gay-marriage.html?_r=0\">reminded</a> us the fight for equal rights isnt over yet, writing: <b></b>\r\n\r\nIt is no accident that the one civil rights law that would likely apply to the greatest numbers of gays  a ban on discrimination in employment and housing on the basis of sexual orientation or gender identity  continues to elude us. An anti-discrimination law creates substantial costs not only for the government, which must enforce it, but also for corporations, which must comply with it; letting gays into military service and into the institution of marriage does not. Indeed, 379 employers, including many of the nations largest airlines, banks, health insurers and manufacturers, filed a brief in support of same-sex marriage, arguing that inconsistency in marriage laws created an onerous regulatory and financial burden and hurt their efforts to recruit talent.\r\n\r\n<i>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</i>','TFIF 6/26','','publish','open','open','','tfif-626','','','2015-06-26 23:40:57','2015-06-26 23:40:57','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=719',0,'post','',0),(720,5,'2015-06-26 23:38:14','2015-06-26 23:38:14','','whitehousegay','','inherit','open','open','','whitehousegay','','','2015-06-26 23:38:14','2015-06-26 23:38:14','',719,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/whitehousegay.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(724,5,'2015-06-26 23:59:40','2015-06-26 23:59:40','Tonight, youll find us at the <b>ESG</b> show at the <b>The Regent</b>!\r\n\r\nWe cant wait to get moody and groove to those funky South Bronx bass lines.\r\n\r\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SgS1_-oWkzY[/embed]\r\n\r\n<b>Trouser Press</b> hails the group as \"one of the most dynamic bands that New York could offer at the top of the 80s\".\r\n\r\n<b>ESG</b>s story is just as inspiring and original as their groovy proto-house sound. The Scroggins sisters came of age in a South Bronx eviscerated by Robert Moses\' Cross Bronx Expressway  a neighborhood carved up by projects and abandoned by government. writes <b>Pitchfork</b>s <b>Joe Tangari</b>. <b></b>Their mother bought them instruments in the hope that her girls might devote themselves to music and stay out of trouble. And they did . . . . The band developed a sound unlike any other and quite by accident became a major influence on hip-hop, dance music, and dance-punk, fitting right in with New York City\'s arty downtown scene and the UK\'s vibrant post-punk explosion.\r\n\r\nWill you come <a href=\"http://www.theregenttheater.com/event/874869-esg-los-angeles/\">away</a> with us?\r\n\r\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GkZ1bC1FQBk[/embed]\r\n\r\n<em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</em>','The Sweat Spot : ESG','','publish','open','open','','the-sweat-spot-esg','','','2015-06-27 00:00:50','2015-06-27 00:00:50','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=724',0,'post','',0),(726,5,'2015-06-27 00:00:19','2015-06-27 00:00:19','','ESG-band','Courtesy of Wikipedia Commons','inherit','open','open','','esg-band','','','2015-06-27 00:00:34','2015-06-27 00:00:34','',724,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/ESG-band.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(728,4,'2015-06-27 02:06:09','2015-06-27 02:06:09','<strong>Join our pride and get exclusive access to all Catnip Club events and products.</strong>\r\n\r\nMembers get:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Free entry to select events</li>\r\n	<li>Reduced entry to supper clubs, pool parties and The Catnip Club Nocturne events</li>\r\n	<li>Exclusive Catnip Club ears</li>\r\n	<li>Exclusive Catnip Club membership card</li>\r\n	<li>Exclusive Catnip Club pin, so you can locate your fellow pussy lovers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMemberships can be bought for 6 months, 1 year or two years. Lifetime memberships can be procured on request.\r\n\r\nPart of the proceeds for The Catnip Club memberships go to<a href=\"http://www.kittybungalow.org/\">Kitty Bungalow</a>, the LA based non profit dedicated to improving the lives of stray cats.\r\n\r\nMemberships are non refundable and non transferable.','Catnip Club Membership - 6 months','Memberships can be bought for 6 months, 1 year or two years. Lifetime memberships can be procured on request.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','publish','closed','closed','','catnip-club-membership-6-months-mm','','','2015-06-27 02:12:43','2015-06-27 02:12:43','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/product/catnip-club-membership-6-months-mm/',0,'product','',0),(730,5,'2015-07-01 20:22:04','2015-07-01 20:22:04','[embed]https://soundcloud.com/heywalkthenight/walk-the-night-summer-grooves[/embed]\r\n\r\n<strong>How did <em>Thats Deck</em> get started? Wed love to know more about your background in radio and electronic music.</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>Thats Deck</em> got started back in 2008 when I decided to start a blog dedicated to music, art, and street-style fashions. Throughout my five years of college, the radio show became an outlet to share new music and invite artists for in-studio sessions and guest spots.\r\n\r\nSince then, it has become completely music-centric, focusing on discovering and exploring sounds from artists around the globe pushing the envelope in their field &amp; giving them the exposure they deserve.\r\n\r\nMy background in electronic music dates back to when I got a foundational introduction to the genre from my older cousins who had great taste. It just blossomed from there as I would spend hours searching online for unheard-of music, new and older. After college, I joined this independent electronic music station called EMS Radio in the Inland Empire and have been running a two-hour show since the Summer of last year.\r\n\r\n<strong>How would you describe the curatorial process for your show? Do you start with a track, DJ you want to feature, a mood or subgenre, or something else entirely?</strong>\r\n\r\nAs far as my radio show goes, it really depends on how much new music has been sent over or I have come across within a weeks time. I have existing relationships with many labels and artists that strictly send me new material for radio play or blog review. Soundcloud and email submissions are very much apart of my curatorial process for the radio show. Also, if there are any good shows occurring in Los Angeles that week I try to highlight the headliners. The genres and moods vary, as I like to keep it deep, eclectic, and otherworldly.\r\n\r\n<strong>Who are your favorite artists youve featured or worked with recently?</strong>\r\n\r\nWe feature a lot of artists on a weekly basis, but some artists I have been really into lately have been J.Albert, Jupiter Jax, SLOPE114, Mbongwana Star, and Nebraska, to name a few.\r\n\r\n<strong>As a relative newcomer, Ive found LA nightlife very different from the parties and undergrounds that introduced me to electronic music when I lived in the Bay Area. Here, things seem more sprawling, but also suffused with a distinctly Los Angeles energy. Im not sure if this has to do with the kinds of jobs and lifestyles people have here, which tend to be kind of intense and spread out across the city, or something totally different. How would you describe the community and scene here?</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"316\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xpf1/v/t1.0-9/6273_10152953850454924_1829597952323404266_n.jpg?oh=3078ca22cdaa200c1c7480470902b065&amp;oe=5619FFD1\" alt=\"\" width=\"316\" height=\"217\" /> Collage by Saish Kotecha[/caption]\r\n\r\nYoure definitely spot on with that; LA indeed has a distinct energy about it, as does any other major city really. I think the community and scene is definitely growing and becoming more diverse here in LA Those that are attracted to a particular sound naturally gravitate towards what they are aligned with culturally and musically: we all seek an environment in which we can express ourselves freely.\r\n\r\nThanks to the dedicated LA underground party organizers who continue to book out-of-state and foreign acts, more and more like-minded music heads are able to catch their favorite DJ or producer almost any day of the week. Everyone at these parties shares one universal commonality  the music  no matter what walk of life they have trekked.\r\n\r\nI feel as though these days the underground parties in LA are just as unique and exhilarating as they are in Europe or anywhere else in the world. After experiencing many proper parties in Berlin, Amsterdam, Barcelona, Stockholm, Vienna, and London during this time last year, I immediately compared it to the community and scene we have here in LA. While Europes community and scene behind their parties are a lot more set in place, I feel that Los Angeles is rapidly gaining momentum and getting to that point, at a West coast pace. Its exciting to see the people and the music flourishing.\r\n\r\n<strong>For those who may have not gotten the chance to make it out, how would you sum up the first <em>Thats Deck</em> party at Complex? Feel free to talk about the sets, visuals, crowd, general vibe, or anything else.</strong>\r\n\r\nIt was fantastic, great turnout for our first party at the well-respected Complex venue. All the sets flowed nicely into each other, carrying a solid garage, house, and techno stream. Very memorable sets from Stefan Ringer, Cromie, and An Expresso. The people on the dancefloor were moving and grooving, creating a nice atmosphere all in all. The visuals definitely took the music to a new level, thanks to my talented friend Garett Gioia who kept the crowd hypnotized with his trippy 3D renders. All in all, the artists and the crowd were satisfied and so was I.\r\n\r\n<strong>Were most attendees fans of the show, people you knew, or folks you were meeting for the first time?</strong>\r\n\r\nA little bit of all the above. Many were fans and friends that I have known for quite sometime, while others were just music heads interested in experiencing something new.\r\n\r\n<strong>What are you listening to these days? Have you heard any particularly great sets?</strong>\r\n\r\nI have been relistening to a lot of older Nite Jewel, John Maus, and Arthur Russells material lately. Theres something about their song structures and the emotion carried along with their instrumentation that is really aligned with me at the moment. These artists are legends in their own right. A recent memorable set that I witnessed would have to be Jeremy Underground, who killed it at the last States of Being party. Such proper vibes  his track selections had everyone grooving the fuck out into the morning light.\r\n\r\n<strong>What makes a great disco party?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe music. The people. The vibe.\r\n\r\n<strong>What soundscapes do you plan to explore next? Wed love to know about any future parties, shows, deckcasts or special projects fans can look forward to.</strong>\r\n\r\nA lot of new projects are in the works that I cant say much about yet, but we are planning our next show in July sometime, which is exciting. You can stay up to date with all future parties, radio shows, and podcasts via <a href=\"http://www.thatsdeck.com\">www.thatsdeck.com</a> and the blogs social networks.\r\n\r\nCatch both <em>Thats Deck</em> radio shows worldwide here:\r\n\r\nw/ SoirJi  Mondays 9PM-11PM PST  <a href=\"http://emsradio.la/\">emsradio.la/</a>\r\n\r\nw/ Hollabec  Every second Tuesday of the month 7PM-8PM AEDT  <a href=\"http://trnsmt.tv/\">trnsmt.tv/</a>\r\n\r\n<em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Such Proper Vibes - An Interview with Thats Decks Saish Kotecha','','publish','open','open','','such-proper-vibes-an-interview-with-thats-decks-saish-kotecha','','','2015-07-01 20:22:04','2015-07-01 20:22:04','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=730',0,'post','',0),(732,5,'2015-06-29 22:06:25','2015-06-29 22:06:25','','thatsdeckwtn','','inherit','open','open','','thatsdeckwtn','','','2015-06-29 22:06:25','2015-06-29 22:06:25','',730,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/thatsdeckwtn.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(734,5,'2015-06-30 10:00:35','2015-06-30 10:00:35','Whether you\'re eagerly stocking up on sparklers or ready to batten down the hatches for the Fourth, there\'s plenty of subterranean intrigue for every taste in this week\'s LA nightlife offerings.\r\n<h2><b>Tuesday</b></h2>\r\nVisionaries and forward thinkers, the future is here! Or perhaps its just back  <a href=\"http://www.hollywoodbowl.com/tickets/back-future-concert-30th-anniversary/2015-06-30\"><b>Back to the Future</b></a>, that is. Its just about time for an anniversary edition screening of the epic adventure series from childhood\'s past, and none is likely to take you adventuring further and more melodically than Lala-Lands summer concert focus,<b> The Hollywood Bowl</b>. Anticipate a production with the added delights of live scoring and extra music from local classical luminaries, the<b> LA Phil</b>.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/back-to-the-future-part-ii-original-1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-735\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/back-to-the-future-part-ii-original-1-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"back-to-the-future-part-ii-original (1)\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a>\r\n<h2><b>Wednesday</b></h2>\r\nHas July gotten you subterraneans feeling Semitic? Stop kvetching and head over to <b>The Geffen Playhouse </b>for a performance of <b>Bad Jews</b>, Joshua Harmons play on contemporary Judaism. Whether you are tapping into your roots or simply have watched a few too many <b>Woody Allen</b> flicks, its the perfect <a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/event/bad-jews-5570880\">way</a> to get your J-fix in.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"3000\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://images1.laweekly.com/imager/u/original/5570879/badjews.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"3000\" height=\"2400\" /> Courtesy of LA Weekly[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Thursday</b></h2>\r\nHead over to <b>Pasadena </b>for a delightful <a href=\"http://www.timeout.com/los-angeles/things-to-do/playhouse-district-block-party#tab_panel_2\">evening</a> of food and music in the<b> Playhouse District</b>! First, grab vino at <b>Monopole Wine</b> or caff up at <b>Zona Rosa</b>. The block party will feature some of LAs best food trucks, as well as hefty servings of <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/583504121785812/\">live music</a>!\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"441\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c4/Red_wine_closeup_in_glass.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"441\" height=\"294\" /> Courtesy of Wikipedia Commons[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Friday</b></h2>\r\nOn the hunt for adventure? Make your way over to the<b> Hollywood Forever Cemetary</b> for<b> Cinespia</b>s <a href=\"http://www.timeout.com/los-angeles/film/cinespia-cemetery-screenings-1\">showing</a> of <b>The Goonies.</b>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://static.underthegunreview.net/uploads/2014/04/goonies.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"415\" height=\"352\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOr, if youre feeling post-punk, swing by the Telegram Ballroom to <a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/event/television-5565428\">catch</a> the <b>Television </b>show.\r\n<h2><b>Saturday </b></h2>\r\nFirst, go red, white and blue at the <a href=\"http://www.timeout.com/los-angeles/major-venues/rose-bowl-stadium\">Rose Bowl</a>s <b>Americafest</b>. Enjoy classic greasy food, motorcycle stunts, and of course fireworks. With tickets at $13, itll have even you expat subterraneans saying America  fuck yeah!\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1280\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/02/4th_July_2006_Pacific_Palisades_HS_Fireworks.jpg/1280px-4th_July_2006_Pacific_Palisades_HS_Fireworks.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1280\" height=\"979\" /> Courtesy of Wikipedia Commons[/caption]\r\n\r\nAfter youve gotten your fill of classic Fourth fare, make your way over to <b>Lot 13</b> for <b>Prototype</b>.<b> Scuba </b>will be headlining, with support from <b>Radio Slave</b> and LAs <b>Plastic Love</b>. As is the case with all <b>Lot 13</b> parties, security will be tight  perhaps even tighter than usual since its the fourth, so imbibe with caution.\r\n<h2><b>Sunday</b></h2>\r\nKick your Saturday back into the 90s, subterraneans  with the return of Riot Grrrl, in all its glorious punk chaos and then some!<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1609838012608769/\"> <b>The Riot Grrrl Carnival</b></a> promises girls to the front and so much more, with a lineup showcasing the artivist and the gender diverse. Look forward to <a href=\"https://atrakopunx.bandcamp.com/\"><b>Atrako</b></a>, who joins <b>Trap Girl</b>, <b>Las Sangronas y El Cabron</b> and the epic <b>Pardon Me Sir. </b>Anticipate local art on display, and live art performances by <b>Belly Belt</b>. Whats more, your entry donates to LA nonprofits <a href=\"http://thesmell.tunestub.com/event.cfm?id=211035&amp;cart\">with the price of admission</a>!\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_737\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/8599432411_e375356e46_o.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-737 size-medium\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/8599432411_e375356e46_o-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"Riot Grrl Legends Bratmobile via Wikipedia Commons\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a> Riot Grrrl Legends Bratmobile via Wikipedia Commons[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Monday</b></h2>\r\nHit <b>Golden Road Brewing</b> and fill your pint glasses, as well as your plates, with an all-you-can-eat bonanza experience in support of the future of sport  roller sport, that is. <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/602796229823931/\"><b>The Angel City Junior Roller Derby fundraiser</b></a> is the perfect way to cheers the future stars of roller derby and meet the community behind the female-fueled athletic hothouse.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Roller_Derby_1950-1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-736\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Roller_Derby_1950-1-300x234.jpg\" alt=\"Roller_Derby_1950 (1)\" width=\"300\" height=\"234\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</em>','Suicide Tuesdays 6/29','','publish','open','open','','suicide-tuesdays-629','','','2015-06-29 22:32:57','2015-06-29 22:32:57','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=734',0,'post','',0),(735,5,'2015-06-29 22:19:24','2015-06-29 22:19:24','','back-to-the-future-part-ii-original (1)','','inherit','open','open','','back-to-the-future-part-ii-original-1','','','2015-06-29 22:19:24','2015-06-29 22:19:24','',734,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/back-to-the-future-part-ii-original-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(736,5,'2015-06-29 22:19:30','2015-06-29 22:19:30','','Roller_Derby_1950 (1)','','inherit','open','open','','roller_derby_1950-1','','','2015-06-29 22:19:30','2015-06-29 22:19:30','',734,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Roller_Derby_1950-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(737,5,'2015-06-29 22:26:30','2015-06-29 22:26:30','','8599432411_e375356e46_o','Riot Grrl Legends Bratmobile via Wikipedia Commons','inherit','open','open','','8599432411_e375356e46_o','','','2015-06-29 22:26:52','2015-06-29 22:26:52','',734,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/8599432411_e375356e46_o.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(743,5,'2015-07-01 20:07:38','2015-07-01 20:07:38','','11259081_10153552304599924_494656698_o','','inherit','open','open','','11259081_10153552304599924_494656698_o','','','2015-07-01 20:07:38','2015-07-01 20:07:38','',730,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/11259081_10153552304599924_494656698_o.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(747,1,'2015-07-01 20:54:06','2015-07-01 20:54:06','','Order &ndash; July 1, 2015 @ 08:54 PM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_5594536b57c99','order-jul-01-2015-0854-pm','','','2015-07-01 20:54:06','2015-07-01 20:54:06','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=747',0,'shop_order','',3),(749,5,'2015-07-02 23:13:11','2015-07-02 23:13:11','<h2><a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Going-Up-Barometer.png\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-645 aligncenter\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Going-Up-Barometer-300x258.png\" alt=\"Going Up (Barometer)\" width=\"300\" height=\"258\" /></a></h2>\r\n<h2><b>Ibiza Real Estate </b></h2>\r\nProperty developers shilled out 25 million for three miles of the iconic Ibiza beachfront, reports the <a href=\"http://www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/sto/business/Companies/article1574226.ece\"><i>Sunday Times</i></a>. No clubs will be closed, but many wonder about the impact of luxury apartments on the island paradise.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"3648\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e4/Ibiza_rock_volcano_(747230830).jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"3648\" height=\"2496\" /> Courtesy of Wikipedia Commons[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Blood Orange</b></h2>\r\nThe artist released a beautiful, ten-minute track inspired by the Charleston shootings. <strong>Do You See My Skin Through the Flames?\"</strong> samples a story about police harassment in France while also reflecting on <strong>Haynes</strong> origins and experience as a black man.\r\n\r\n[embed]https://soundcloud.com/bloodorange/do-you-see-my-skin-through-the-flames[/embed]\r\n<h2><strong>InsaneJim Carrey</strong></h2>\r\nMeanwhile, in a more irritating corner of the universe (sorry, Canadians), <strong>Jim Carrey</strong>s <strong>anti-vaxx</strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/jimcarrey/status/616049450243338240\">tirade</a> left many wondering where Ace Venturas spay/neuter policies lie.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://media.aintitcool.com/media/uploads/2013/aceventurafistpump_large.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"680\" height=\"382\" />\r\n<h2><b><a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Going-Down-Barometer.png\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-646 aligncenter\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Going-Down-Barometer-300x258.png\" alt=\"Going Down (Barometer)\" width=\"300\" height=\"258\" /></a></b></h2>\r\n<h2><b>Rick Ross </b></h2>\r\nNaturally, <strong>Ricky Ros</strong> paid his $500,000 bond in cash plus $1 million in equity from his mansion. Before you start popping the pink champagne, its worth mentioning that <strong>Ross</strong> was charged with pistol-whipping the groundskeeper of his property, breaking his employees jaw and injuring his neck  not great.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"323\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c8/Rick_Ross_mug_shot.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"323\" height=\"425\" /> Courtesy of Wikipedia Commons[/caption]\r\n<h1>Peas</h1>\r\nAn unconventional addition to a guacamole recipe left <strong><i>New York Times </i></strong>readers up in arms this Wednesday. In what was likely the most exciting moment of one food writers career, <strong>President Obama</strong> chimed in on Twitter, echoing the anti-pea sentiments.<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Screen-Shot-2015-07-02-at-3.49.48-PM.png\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-750 size-full\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Screen-Shot-2015-07-02-at-3.49.48-PM.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-07-02 at 3.49.48 PM\" width=\"585\" height=\"238\" /></a>\r\n<h2>The Rolling Stones</h2>\r\nWhile touring museum exhibit is perhaps the perfect name for a 2015 <strong>Rolling Stones</strong> show, the group has announced that they will, in fact, be opening an actual traveling reliquary of some kind. Stay tuned, lest you miss any rock history.\\m/\\m/\\m/\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"928\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/93/Keith_Richards_Mick_Jagger_Rolling_Stones_2012-12-13.jpg/928px-Keith_Richards_Mick_Jagger_Rolling_Stones_2012-12-13.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"928\" height=\"1024\" /> Courtesy of Wikipedia Commons[/caption]\r\n\r\n<em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</em>','Barometer 7/2','','publish','open','open','','barometer-72','','','2015-07-02 23:13:11','2015-07-02 23:13:11','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=749',0,'post','',0),(750,5,'2015-07-02 22:50:54','2015-07-02 22:50:54','','Screen Shot 2015-07-02 at 3.49.48 PM','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-07-02-at-3-49-48-pm','','','2015-07-02 22:50:54','2015-07-02 22:50:54','',749,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Screen-Shot-2015-07-02-at-3.49.48-PM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(751,5,'2015-07-02 23:12:43','2015-07-02 23:12:43','','nytnowguac-articleLarge','Dominic Perri for The New York Times','inherit','open','open','','nytnowguac-articlelarge','','','2015-07-02 23:13:05','2015-07-02 23:13:05','',749,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/nytnowguac-articleLarge.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(754,5,'2015-07-07 21:34:59','2015-07-07 21:34:59','<h2><b>Tuesday</b></h2>\r\nTuesdays are such a drag  by which we mean, the perfect night to catch a comedy <a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/event/jackie-beat-all-you-can-eat-5731206\">show</a> from drag queen extraordinaire Jackie Beat! Held at the <b>Cavern Club, </b>the monthly show promises a smorgasbord of parodic raunch &amp; revelry to boot, with upcoming themes such as Ladies of the 80s and Racist, Homophobic, Woman-Hater.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"503\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://ourcommunityroots.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/jackiebeat.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"503\" height=\"648\" /> Our Community Roots[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Wednesday</b></h2>\r\n1960s Los Angeles came to embody both the greatest hopes and intensified fears of African Americans. Join <b>Josh Sides</b> for <a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/event/the-promises-and-perils-of-postwar-black-los-angeles-5725452\"><b>The Promises and Perils of Postwar Black Los Angeles</b></a>, a <a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/event/the-promises-and-perils-of-postwar-black-los-angeles-5725452\">discussion</a> in conversation with the Hammers current exhibit <b><i>Mark Bradford: Scorched Earth</i></b>, which includes the LA-based artists twelve paintings and a sound installation inspired by such early-90s issues as the AIDS epidemic and the 1992 LA riots.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"914\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d2/Wattsriots-burningbuildings-loc.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"914\" height=\"657\" /> Wikimedia[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Thursday</b></h2>\r\nWarm up your Thursday night with affection and fall for the city all over again with the company of the artists who made <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/374716916046873/\"><b><i>Love, Los Angeles</i></b></a>, a letter in progress. Two native Angelenas have assembled an intoxicating set of notes, fragments, reflections &amp; odes that will draw you in and keep you wanting more. Their negotiations of the city and its rapidly shifting landscapes comes with its own DJd soundtrack  a sight rarely seen in the hallowed halls of the Central Library. Witness the city in its best and worst ever-changing faces, with a soundscape to suit, for a night to remember.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/11205008_1106046319411323_7739524503128948459_n.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-755\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/11205008_1106046319411323_7739524503128948459_n-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"11205008_1106046319411323_7739524503128948459_n\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a>\r\n<h2><b>Friday</b></h2>\r\nDive on in to the weather-beaten world of <a href=\"http://www.thenewbev.com/midnightssource/2015/6/5/july-3-10-17-24-amp-31-django-unchained\"><b><i>Django Unchained</i></b></a>. Although LAs <b>New Beverly Cinemas </b>is no newcomer to the midnight movie buff, this particular film may leave you in directorial company  Tarantino himself doubles as both films director and the owner of the cinema itself.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://d12vb6dvkz909q.cloudfront.net/uploads/galleries/26648/django-unchained-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1082\" />\r\n<h2><b>Saturday</b></h2>\r\nFeeling overheated? Why not quench your thirst with a tasty splash of the written word. The Last Bookstores Hot July <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1454012438231621/\">reading</a>s lineup promises a feminist literary powerhouse with bad feminist Roxane Gay, LAs very own Wendy Ortiz and poet xTx.\r\n\r\nAfter the reading, get ready to dance the night away! Join <b>Fine Time</b> for The Bunker Showcase, featuring <b>Mike Servito, Derek Plaslaiko</b>, and LA native <b>Tahl K</b>. Post comments for RSVP (location) and presale password on <a href=\"http://www.restlessnites.com/finetime\">Restless Nights</a>.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"640\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2013/5778901295_04b29d6af0_z.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" /> Flickr[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Sunday</b></h2>\r\nIf the heats got you feelin trippy, simply spend your summer Sunday at <strong>Acid Camp</strong>. The show features of lineup of Chicago talents <strong>Olin</strong> &amp; <strong>Studio Casual</strong> plus LA faves <strong>Jeniluv, Alison Swing</strong>, and<strong> Techno Sam.</strong> Whats more, the party, running from 3 - 10 pm, will feature sounds from a Funktion-One as well as a pop-up record shop! Check out the <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/857456217674947/\">listing</a> or call the party line at 347-218-0963 for more details and to snag your ticket!\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xtp1/v/t1.0-9/10403253_905880042807963_9208212234728844137_n.jpg?oh=7c3dba05cd3e3c66e414a680b7c0951c&amp;oe=56580D1F\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"358\" />\r\n<h2><b>Monday</b></h2>\r\nHead back in time and meet your best friend Madge on her Blonde Ambition tour. <b><i>Madonna: Truth or Dare</i></b> is just one of the incredible offerings at<b> Outfest </b>this year. Every good subterranean deserves a long week in darkened rooms to make the most of the film festivals grab bag of goodies. The celebrated documentary juxtaposes color and monochromes to bring you back to both the gritty reality and glitzy celebrity of the era.<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Madonna_truth_or_dare_poster.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-757\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Madonna_truth_or_dare_poster-199x300.jpg\" alt=\"Madonna_truth_or_dare_poster\" width=\"199\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</em>','Suicide Tuesdays 7/7','','publish','open','open','','suicide-tuesdays-77','','','2015-07-07 21:36:36','2015-07-07 21:36:36','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=754',0,'post','',0),(755,5,'2015-07-07 21:17:42','2015-07-07 21:17:42','','11205008_1106046319411323_7739524503128948459_n','','inherit','open','open','','11205008_1106046319411323_7739524503128948459_n','','','2015-07-07 21:17:42','2015-07-07 21:17:42','',754,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/11205008_1106046319411323_7739524503128948459_n.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(756,5,'2015-07-07 21:19:20','2015-07-07 21:19:20','','django-unchained-jamie-foxx','','inherit','open','open','','django-unchained-jamie-foxx','','','2015-07-07 21:19:20','2015-07-07 21:19:20','',754,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/django-unchained-jamie-foxx.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(757,5,'2015-07-07 21:22:03','2015-07-07 21:22:03','','Madonna_truth_or_dare_poster','','inherit','open','open','','madonna_truth_or_dare_poster','','','2015-07-07 21:22:03','2015-07-07 21:22:03','',754,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Madonna_truth_or_dare_poster.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(758,5,'2015-07-07 21:22:09','2015-07-07 21:22:09','','django-unchained-jamie-foxx','','inherit','open','open','','django-unchained-jamie-foxx-2','','','2015-07-07 21:22:09','2015-07-07 21:22:09','',754,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/django-unchained-jamie-foxx1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(759,5,'2015-07-07 21:25:11','2015-07-07 21:25:11','','django-unchained-jamie-foxx','','inherit','open','open','','django-unchained-jamie-foxx-3','','','2015-07-07 21:25:11','2015-07-07 21:25:11','',754,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/django-unchained-jamie-foxx2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(763,5,'2015-07-11 00:51:19','2015-07-11 00:51:19','<b></b>There are so many great parties this weekend that its hard to choose  but well leave that part up to you. For now, heres the lowdown to get you through your last few minutes on the clock:\r\n\r\nOn Saturday afternoon, head downtown to the Standard Rooftop to catch Dutch duo <b>Detroit Swindle </b>with supporting sets from <b>Soul of Hex</b>, <b>Cromie </b>and <b>Dig Deeper </b>residents <b>Alison Swing</b> &amp; <b>Masha</b>! RSVP now on <a href=\"http://www.restlessnites.com/finetime\"><b>Restless Nights</b></a><b>.</b>\r\n\r\nAfter youve danced a little and gazed upon the DTLA skyscape, its time to take things underground at<b> Fine Time</b>s all night party, <b>Club Time</b>. Well catch sets from<b> Mike Servito</b> and <b>Derek Plaslaiko </b>of <b>The Bunker</b>, with LAs <b>Tahl K </b>supporting the NYC house and techno legends. Post in comments for RSVP (location) / presale password on <a href=\"http://www.restlessnites.com/finetime\"><b>Restless Nights</b></a>!\r\n\r\nMake sure you get a few hours of shuteye post-afterhours, though! Pop an Advil &amp; a little 5-HTP and head over to <b>Mystery Box</b> for <b>Acid Camp</b>! The party features Chicagos <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/olintechno\">Olin</a> (<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/smartbarchicago\">Smart Bar Chicago</a> / <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/ArgotTasteful-Nudes/363895576977012\">Argot / Tasteful Nudes</a>), <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/StudioCasual\">Studio Casual</a> (<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/strippedchewed\">Stripped &amp; Chewed</a>) with support from LA talents <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/jeniluvLA\">Jeniluv</a> (<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/making.shapes.events\">Making Shapes</a>), <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/mynameisalisonandiliketodancealot\">Alison Swing</a> (<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/DigDeeperLA\">Dig Deeper LA</a>) and Techno Sam (<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/feelsoreal\">Feel So Real</a>).\r\n\r\nSee you on the dance floor!\r\n\r\n<em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</em>','The Sweat Spot: Dig Deeper / Club Time / Acid Camp','','publish','open','open','','the-sweat-spot-dig-deeper-club-time-acid-camp','','','2015-07-11 00:55:44','2015-07-11 00:55:44','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=763',0,'post','',0),(764,5,'2015-07-11 00:46:00','2015-07-11 00:46:00','','cover_photo_mike_and_derek_-_credit_will_calcutt','','inherit','open','open','','cover_photo_mike_and_derek_-_credit_will_calcutt','','','2015-07-11 00:46:00','2015-07-11 00:46:00','',763,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/cover_photo_mike_and_derek_-_credit_will_calcutt.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(765,5,'2015-07-11 00:46:38','2015-07-11 00:46:38','','cover_photo_mike_and_derek_-_credit_will_calcutt','','inherit','open','open','','cover_photo_mike_and_derek_-_credit_will_calcutt-2','','','2015-07-11 00:46:38','2015-07-11 00:46:38','',763,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/cover_photo_mike_and_derek_-_credit_will_calcutt1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(766,5,'2015-07-11 00:48:56','2015-07-11 00:48:56','','maxresdefault','','inherit','open','open','','maxresdefault','','','2015-07-11 00:48:56','2015-07-11 00:48:56','',763,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/maxresdefault.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(768,5,'2015-07-14 19:16:44','2015-07-14 19:16:44','<h2><b>Tuesday</b></h2>\r\nCelebrate Bastille Day in style by <a href=\"http://californianewswire.com/2015/06/09/le-french-festival-2015-a-10-day-bastille-day-celebration-in-los-angeles-of-french-artisans-and-culture-CNW28566_161107.php/\">hitting</a> <b>Le French Festival</b>, swinging by one of LAs best French <a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/restaurants/three-delicious-ways-to-celebrate-bastille-day-in-los-angeles-5788280\">restaurants</a>, or simply spending the night in with your favorite Francophone film! We recommend <b><i>Girlhood</i></b><b>, </b>a poignant coming-of-age story about a group of girlsgrowing up in a poor Paris suburb.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1920\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://d236bkdxj385sg.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/GIRLHOOD_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1920\" height=\"800\" /> Girlhood[/caption]\r\n<h2><b> </b><b>Wednesday </b></h2>\r\nLet the birds tweet! Head over to Los Felizs Skylight Books to catch a <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1606523769608067/\">reading</a> from Mira Gonzalez and Tao Lin. The duo will be celebrating the release of their <i>Selected Tweets </i>compilation. Expect to brush shoulders with edgy LA literati and hear tales of substance abuse and anxiety recounted with dry wit in no more than 140 characters.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"436\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xpa1/v/t1.0-9/11692578_10153622656912481_718761093328724685_n.jpg?oh=2bef178236537f872f8911574ba809c6&amp;oe=56244EF6\" alt=\"\" width=\"436\" height=\"513\" /> Mira Gonzalez[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Thursday </b></h2>\r\nMake your way west to the Santa Monica pier for a free show from Real Estate! While there arent many <a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/event/real-estate-5596496\">reasons</a> to brave the 10 or spend your evening on the crowded Santa Monica pier, the bands beachy indie rock sound <i>does</i> seem perfectly suited for the shore.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"4256\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/79/DaysPressShot.JPG\" alt=\"\" width=\"4256\" height=\"2832\" /> Wikipedia Commons[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Friday </b></h2>\r\nIf Wednesdays tweets left you craving more digital literary fare, dont fret! Simply saunter over the <b>The Pop-Hop</b> for <b>\"Selfie Performativity and the Digital Attention Economy\"</b>, a panel on the poetic selfie moderated by LA poet &amp; performance artist <b>Kate Durbin</b>. Panelists<b> manuel arturo abreu, Die Dragonetti, Jos Charles, Joshua Jennifer Espinoza,</b> &amp;<b> Sara June Woods</b> all hail from the TRANS PLANET poetry tour, and will have their works featured in the <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/814437691988481/\">talk</a>.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xfa1/t31.0-8/s960x960/10003838_10207378597807385_2916088380749577193_o.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"421\" height=\"667\" />\r\n<h2><b>Saturday </b></h2>\r\nIf you didnt make it to last weeks <b>Club Time</b> party, you missed out on some killer sets. No need to mourn too long, though: this weekend promises another lively late night affair, with DJs from around the world, or at least the Western Hemisphere:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/Linkwood/224044183539\">Linkwood</a> (Firecracker Recordings, Prime Numbers, UK)\r\n\r\nGalcher Lustwerk (White Material, Tsuba, Lustwerk - NY)\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/Nautiluss\">Nautiluss</a> (Turbo Recordings, The Nite Owl Diner, Hemlock, CAN)\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/TahlkLA\">Tahl K</a> on the warmup (Fine Time)\r\n\r\nPost in comments for RSVP (location) / presale password on <a href=\"http://www.restlessnites.com/clubtime/\"><b>Restless Nights</b></a>. What are you waiting for? Join us on the dance floor!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xpf1/v/t1.0-9/10419531_575642762574131_703010212543462651_n.png?oh=c6614b3d4f3b83ae5df7978228219160&amp;oe=56532D13\" alt=\"\" width=\"785\" height=\"296\" />\r\n<h2><b>Sunday </b></h2>\r\nNot ready for the weekend to end? Head over to the <b>Sound Nightclub</b> to catch <b>Honey Soundsystem</b> <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1627308977487166/\">debut</a> their LA residency. Therell be plenty of groove to go around, and you can <a href=\"http://soundnightclub.com/event.cfm?cart&amp;id=149466\">snag</a> your presale for a mere $5!There will also be shrimp rolls.<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Screen-Shot-2015-07-14-at-11.38.42-AM.png\"><img class=\"  wp-image-769 alignright\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Screen-Shot-2015-07-14-at-11.38.42-AM.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-07-14 at 11.38.42 AM\" width=\"14\" height=\"126\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xtp1/v/t1.0-9/10414838_869964489705238_5975521948137879346_n.jpg?oh=fee538b0b0d3e55a97d1edee8469901a&amp;oe=561BCFC3\" alt=\"\" width=\"784\" height=\"295\" />\r\n<h2><b>Monday </b></h2>\r\nLike your nostalgia a little lighthearted? Swing by The Groundlings Theater for the troupes <b>Decade Night. </b>The <a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/event/decade-nights-5786369\">show</a> will include a star-studded lineup of Groundling grads, while proceeds will go towards a new 5,000sqft improv &amp; sketch comedy school! The show will kick off at 7pm sharp with alumni from the 70s, and proceed through another decade each hour.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" alignnone\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/ac/Groundlings01.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"463\" height=\"385\" />\r\n\r\n<em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Suicide Tuesday 7/14','','publish','open','open','','suicide-tuesday-714','','','2015-07-14 19:16:44','2015-07-14 19:16:44','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=768',0,'post','',0),(769,5,'2015-07-14 18:39:34','2015-07-14 18:39:34','','Screen Shot 2015-07-14 at 11.38.42 AM','','inherit','open','open','','screen-shot-2015-07-14-at-11-38-42-am','','','2015-07-14 18:39:34','2015-07-14 18:39:34','',768,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Screen-Shot-2015-07-14-at-11.38.42-AM.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(770,5,'2015-07-14 18:46:17','2015-07-14 18:46:17','','1024px-Storming_the_bastille_4_-_2','Creative Commons','inherit','open','open','','1024px-storming_the_bastille_4_-_2','','','2015-07-14 18:46:31','2015-07-14 18:46:31','',768,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/1024px-Storming_the_bastille_4_-_2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(773,1,'2015-07-15 06:08:06','2015-07-15 06:08:06','','Order &ndash; July 15, 2015 @ 06:08 AM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_55a5f8c0a101a','order-jul-15-2015-0608-am','','','2015-07-15 06:08:06','2015-07-15 06:08:06','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=773',0,'shop_order','',3),(777,5,'2015-07-16 15:19:51','2015-07-16 22:19:51','<h2></h2>\r\n<h2><b><a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Going-Up-Barometer.png\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-645 aligncenter\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Going-Up-Barometer-300x258.png\" alt=\"Going Up (Barometer)\" width=\"300\" height=\"258\" /></a>Ganja Girls </b></h2>\r\n<b>Vice</b>s <b>Gabby Bess</b> <a href=\"http://www.vice.com/read/pussy-money-weed-678\">told</a> us how marketers are appealing to the burgeoning stoner-chic demographic.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"500\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://stonerthings.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/stoner-girl.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"324\" /> Stoner Things[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>MTV: Ibiza Shore?</b></h2>\r\nThe shore franchise plans to take on the nightlife capital <a href=\"http://www.factmag.com/2015/07/16/mtv-has-commissioned-ibiza-shore/\">next</a>.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"480\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://news.mtv.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/jersey-5-years.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"480\" height=\"320\" /> MTV News[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Free Drug Testing </b></h2>\r\nNova Scotias Evolve festival last weekend <a href=\"http://www.mixmag.net/read/canadian-festival-will-carry-out-free-drug-testing-this-weekend-new\">offered</a> purity tests for MDMA &amp; LSD.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1600\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://farm3.staticflickr.com/2923/14364091179_6439069f3f_h.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1201\" /> Flickr Commons[/caption]\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Going-Down-Barometer.png\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-646 aligncenter\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Going-Down-Barometer-300x258.png\" alt=\"Going Down (Barometer)\" width=\"300\" height=\"258\" /></a>\r\n<h2><b>Chaka Khan </b></h2>\r\nSam Smith and I are really good friends, the singer <a href=\"https://slack-redir.net/link?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mirror.co.uk%2F3am%2Fcelebrity-news%2Fsam-smith-chaka-khan-plan-6037460\">told</a> The Mirror. :(\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"3456\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f0/Chaka_Khan_in_Chris_March_01.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"3456\" height=\"5184\" /> Wikipedia Commons[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Horsing around </b></h2>\r\n<b>David Guetta</b>s plans to bring in an equine friend to DJ with him were <a href=\"http://pagesix.com/2015/07/15/david-guetta-blasted-for-wanting-to-bring-a-horse-to-a-nightclub/?_ga=1.61527084.1093464932.1437002063\">halted</a> by an online petition claiming, The horse has to enter the big Pacha hall at 4 a.m. [with] a huge crowd of people, drunken and drugged, screaming and sweating ... [its] irresponsible to put a horse in the middle of the night under so much stress. The petition has gathered more than 7,000 signatures.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"750\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/b6/Rapa_das_bestas_sabucedo_2_jpereira.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"500\" /> Wikipedia[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Neil Young</b></h2>\r\nStreaming has ended for me, <a href=\"http://www.avclub.com/article/streaming-services-cannot-capture-glory-neil-young-222364\">proclaims</a> Young. I dont need my music to be devalued by the worst quality in the history of broadcasting or any other form of distribution. More like Neil Old, amirite?\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"600\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/bb/Neil_Young_-_Per_Ole_Hagen.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"421\" /> Wikipedia Commons[/caption]\r\n\r\n<em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</em>','Barometer 7/16','','publish','open','open','','barometer-716','','\nhttps://slack-redir.net/link?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mirror.co.uk%2F3am%2Fcelebrity-news%2Fsam-smith-chaka-khan-plan-6037460','2015-07-16 15:20:55','2015-07-16 22:20:55','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=777',0,'post','',0),(779,5,'2015-07-16 15:20:41','2015-07-16 22:20:41','','Evolve','Mixmag','inherit','open','open','','evolve','','','2015-07-16 15:20:52','2015-07-16 22:20:52','',777,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Evolve.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(780,5,'2015-07-21 10:00:29','2015-07-21 17:00:29','This week, enjoy mariachi music and weeknight improvwith your Saturday subterranean fare.\r\n<h2><b>Tuesday</b></h2>\r\nHeel and toe your way to Human Resources for brazen &amp; darkperformances from <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/479499285552961/\"><b>Ros Hernandez, Boychild </b>and<b> Divinity Fudge</b></a>. If you missed them only days ago at <b>Step and Repeat</b> at MOCA, youll be relieved to find theyre continuing the artistry. Plod into an evening of solos, experimentations, works-in-progress, featuring a group finale Walking Meditation with Sage Charles on percussion. The night swims with talent, so keep the office-inappropriate banter up after the performance with drinks and a rare chance to mingle with the artists themselves.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xap1/v/t1.0-9/11207321_1118977488116775_6588819709709098602_n.jpg?oh=167424fb538124ea9e11b77393394c7f&amp;oe=56485AB4\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"960\" />\r\n<h2><b>Wednesday</b></h2>\r\nSwing by the Copper Still to <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/794335954018002/\">lighten</a> up your Wednesday at <b>A New Stand-Up Show</b>! Hosted by Josh Fadem &amp; Johnny Pemberton, youll toast pupusas &amp; spicy margs to sets by <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/tobythecomic\">Toby Muresianu</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/joe.kardon\">Joe Kardon</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/goalkeeper290\">Michael Magid</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/lori.weiss.184\">Lori Weiss</a>, <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/brentjamessullivan\">Brent Sullivan</a> &amp; <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/lizzy.cooperman\">Lizzy Cooperman</a>.Entry is free!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xft1/v/t1.0-9/11174931_437119856472286_8430232171270763315_n.jpg?oh=08731dfdf0ec0991b9b2a03f4fc391b8&amp;oe=561E9003\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"960\" />\r\n<h2><b>Thursday</b></h2>\r\nTake a turn in the stacks and head downtown for books that hold <a href=\"http://lfla.org/event/unspeakable-empathy/\"><b>Unspeakable Empathy</b></a>. ALOUD, the Central Librarys literary talk, catches up with the authors behind these emotional tomes. This evening focuses on the words of Leslie Jamisons <i>The Empathy Exams</i>, as she discusses the urgency to feel, while Meghan Daum fires back against false sentimentality across our culture. Feeling language will abound  ready your mind for the delicious connection between emotion and the written word.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\" http://i.guim.co.uk/img/static/sys-images/Books/Pix/pictures/2014/5/27/1401191849214/Leslie-Jamieson-014.jpg?w=620&amp;q=85&amp;auto=format&amp;sharp=10&amp;s=49b220a84d7cd81fb136cf28fce30b69\" alt=\"\" width=\"620\" height=\"372\" />\r\n<h2><b>Friday</b></h2>\r\nSashay your way into a world of classic mariachi music at <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1046979655317464/\"><b>Viva la Mujer! </b>Celebrating Women in Mariach</a>i. Well journey away from the machismo at the forefront, instead diving into the life of the underrepresented female Mariachi, highlighting the trailblazing female force behind the best of the musical genre. Guided by <b>Dr. Leonor X. Perez</b>, founder of the <b>Mariachi Womens Foundation,</b> the evening will feature a performance by local group <b>Mariachi Reyna de Los Angeles</b> in a rare film screening of <b><i>Que Caramba es la Vida</i></b>.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xtp1/v/t1.0-9/11227967_996654857012273_495371951732509587_n.jpg?oh=d85cf04effafcfb595d3f959dc690bca&amp;oe=565862F4\" alt=\"\" width=\"641\" height=\"960\" />\r\n<h2><b>Saturday</b></h2>\r\nSubsume yourself in grime, slime and musical fantasy at<b> Sanctuary One</b>! The party returns with <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/GolfChannelRecordings\">Golf Channel Recordings</a>\' <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/justinvandervolgen\">Justin Van Der Volgen</a>. The party is hosted by Courtney Fruit Fly Nichols, with resident support from <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/TresDubois\">Tres Dubois</a> &amp; <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/ray.barragan.3\">Ray Barragan</a>. See you subterraneans on the dance floor!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xaf1/v/t1.0-9/425334_587139961331240_1623101403_n.jpg?oh=5f99747048ff4aaa81418a7b0fe67751&amp;oe=56139B68\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"339\" />\r\n<h2><b>Sunday</b></h2>\r\nSummon your inner Julia Roberts and <a href=\"http://press.fourseasons.com/beverlywilshire/hotel-news/2015/pretty-woman-necklace/\">escort</a> yourself to theBeverly Wilshire for <b>The Pretty Woman Experience</b>. In celebration of the iconic films 25th birthday, Angelenas &amp; Angelenos are invited to gaze at relics &amp; recreations from the set, as well as the treasured film script. If youre lucky, you might even land your very own silver fox.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://cdn.skim.gs/images/y0jbuhcaozf3gma0ugpx/11-iconic-90s-movie-outfits-you-ll-never-forget-pretty-woman-6\" alt=\"\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" />\r\n<h2><b>Monday</b></h2>\r\nThese days, who isnt a little bit of a Chris Pratt fangirl? Head over to iO West for <i>T</i><i>he Hopefully Chris Pratt and Shane Hartline Show 2</i>. The premise of the show plays off an obsessed fan-cum-Pratt-lookalike, and aspires to attract the man himself. Stop by and (at the very least) <a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/event/the-hopefully-chris-pratt-and-shane-hartline-show-2-5805653\">see</a> Pratts likeness for yourself!\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"2718\"]<img src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/89/Chris_Pratt_by_Gage_Skidmore.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2718\" height=\"3168\" /> Wikipedia Commons[/caption]\r\n\r\n<em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</em>','Suicide Tuesdays 4/21','','publish','open','open','','suicide-tuesdays-421','','','2015-07-20 19:00:18','2015-07-21 02:00:18','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=780',0,'post','',0),(781,5,'2015-07-20 18:57:37','2015-07-21 01:57:37','','prettywoman__140312185350','','inherit','open','open','','prettywoman__140312185350','','','2015-07-20 18:57:37','2015-07-21 01:57:37','',780,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/prettywoman__140312185350.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(784,1,'2015-07-27 16:33:14','2015-07-27 23:33:14','','Order &ndash; July 27, 2015 @ 04:33 PM','Please print this name on membership card \' aung soe \'','wc-processing','open','closed','order_55b6bfb661727','order-jul-27-2015-1133-pm','','','2015-07-27 16:33:14','2015-07-27 23:33:14','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=784',0,'shop_order','',3),(785,1,'2015-07-27 18:10:57','2015-07-28 01:10:57','','Order &ndash; July 27, 2015 @ 06:10 PM','','wc-processing','open','closed','order_55b6d69de1038','order-jul-28-2015-0110-am','','','2015-07-27 18:10:57','2015-07-28 01:10:57','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=shop_order&#038;p=785',0,'shop_order','',3),(786,5,'2015-07-28 19:57:45','2015-07-29 02:57:45','<h2><b>Tuesday </b></h2>\r\nTonight, make your way to <b>The Echo</b> for <b>FYF Presents Jamie xx with Young Marco</b>.\r\n\r\nThe iconic London indie producer <a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/event/jamie-xx-young-marco-5706210\">conjures</a> U.K. garage, dubstep &amp; funky sounds in a unique sonic hybrid of indie electronic and EDM. You wont want to miss it  provided youre lucky enough to snag a ticket.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xpt1/v/t1.0-9/10641231_10155677378490099_5221086488621175721_n.jpg?oh=569d4f5c8dc3fed017820da9ea5e8e6f&amp;oe=565A246C\" alt=\"\" width=\"416\" height=\"461\" />\r\n<h2><b>Wednesday</b></h2>\r\nThink you know the full Amy Winehouse story? Head over to <b>The Landmark</b> for a <a href=\"http://www.themirrorcube.com/event/amy-the-landmark-la\">screening</a> of <b><i>Amy</i></b>, the much anticipated Amy Winehouse documentary. The film notably lacks the usual talking head interviews, instead plucking existing footage from Winehouses friends and lovers. After catching wind of the controversies and objections from the late singers family surrounding the release, we cant wait to see the contested documentary for ourselves.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/52/Amy_Winehouse_f5048439.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"368\" height=\"270\" />\r\n<h2><b>Thursday</b></h2>\r\nHeat got you down? Dont disrobe quite yet. Hightail it to <b>Sunday Gallery</b> for <b>Hot in Here</b>, an art <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/670061796457883/\">show</a> from an amazing all-girl collective featuring the likes of:\r\n\r\nSigne Pierce*Molly Matalon*Adi Rajkovic*Eleanor Bleier*Carly Jean Andrews*Brittney Scott*Erika Braukis*Caroline Goldfarb*Teryn Brown*Sarah Bowser*Ariana Papademetropoulos*Caroline David*Cat Roif*Anja Salonen*Rebecca Rose*Taralyn Thomas*Kaya Yusi*Hanan Sharifa*Sofia Arreguin*Courtney Melahn*Molly Soda*Sinziana Vlicescu*Kaylan George*Grace Miceli*Brie Moreno*Kelsey Reckling*Liza Mandelup*Meghan Tryon*Abby Banks*Claire Sullivan*Faye Orlove*Solita Montoya*Logan White*Francesca Allen*Fath Silva*Mayan Toledano*Nina Ljeti*Vivian Fu*Margaret Haines*Zoe Zag*Valerie Shusterov*Keely Murphy*Andrea Sonnenberg*Devon Leigh*Keely Murphy*Kiera McNally*Arvida Bystrom*Delaney Lee*Patty*\r\n\r\nWith DJ sets from <b>Honey Power</b> plus Claras Cakes and complimentary drinks, this show is shaping up to be a perfect thirsty Thursday.\r\n\r\nOr, If youre feeling fit to journey into the Orient, swing by <b>Cinefamily</b> as bands play scores for two classic Japanese films live.\r\n\r\nCo-presented by <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/weopen.arthouses\">We Open Art Houses</a> &amp; <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/tigerbeat6\">Tigerbeat6, </a>the <b>Videosonics</b> lineup features live score performances from:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/Pod-Blotz/191657147558605\"><b>Pod Blotz</b></a>  \'Funeral Parade Of Roses\' (Matsumoto, 1969)\r\n\r\nRemixed! Feat. an original score by Pod Blotz.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/xiuxiuforlife\"><b>Xiu Xiu</b></a> \'Under Blossoming Cherry Trees\' (Shinoda, 1975)\r\n\r\nRemixed! Feat. an original score by Xiu Xiu\r\n\r\nLive For Each Moon VS Crocodile (Ki Duk Kim, 1996)\r\n\r\nRemixed! Feat. an original score by <b>Live For Each Moon </b>\r\n\r\nAfter the show, stick around for a patio party and special sneak-peek of <b>Mila Zuo </b>and <b>Angela Seo</b>s new <a href=\"http://kck.st/1gy77vm\">short</a> exploring the dark undercurrents of Asian fetish, <b>\'Carnal Orient,\'</b> featuring. a score by <b>Xiu Xiu</b>\'s <b>Angela Seo.</b>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://thefanzine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/under-the-blossoming-cherry-trees.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"376\" />\r\n<h2><b>Friday </b></h2>\r\nHitting the dance floor is the best <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1596758913910010/\">way</a> to kick your work week stress, dont you think? This Friday, head for 4th Street to hear your all of your favorite DJs at <b>Risky Vision</b>!\r\n\r\nThe lineup features:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/Octo-Octa/311612715552997\">Octo Octa</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/MASHA/1637544393158808\">MASHA</a> b2b <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/mynameisalisonandiliketodancealot\">Alison Swing</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/ChannelOne.LA\">Channel One</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/TahlkLA\">Tahl K</a>\r\n\r\nSnag your $10 <a href=\"http://www.restlessnites.com/finetime/\">Presales / RSVP on Restless Nights</a> for $10 entry before 11pm! This party is going to be ragin!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xft1/v/t1.0-9/11665594_803830306398149_325373224049210721_n.jpg?oh=6c5ce6eb9b6a7330dee033971db41acc&amp;oe=5642107F\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"349\" />\r\n<h2><b>Saturday </b></h2>\r\nSet your GPS to the Inland Empire for Pomonas <b>Hard Summer</b> festival to to catch a <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1611929405715513/\">performance</a> from <b>The Chemical Brothers</b>. This years festival lineup is split between hip hop &amp; EDM and boasts a few crossover DJs. While its a bit of a shlep, the promise of seeing The Chemical Brothers might be enough for us to brave the drive (and the crowds).\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d7/Chemical_Brothers_Live.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"492\" height=\"402\" />\r\n<h2><b>Sunday </b></h2>\r\nIf things are starting to seem a bit <a href=\"http://www.laweekly.com/event/the-13th-annual-los-angeles-improv-comedy-festival-5830350\">sketchy</a>, its high time to head to <b>Hollywoods iO West Theaters 13th Annual Los Angeles Improv Comedy Festival</b>. The sketch &amp; improv showcase features over 200 performances, including a competition to set a Guinness World Record for Longest Continuous Improv Show. Also included in the festival itinerary are workshops with seasoned funny men: iO West hails instructors with credits from the Emmys, <i>Saturday Night Live</i>, and <i>MADtv</i>, to <i>Conan</i> and <i>Jimmy Kimmel Live</i>. Part of the proceeds benefit the Chris Farley House, a sober facility in Madison, Wisconsin.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://ioimprov.com/west/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2014/12/iowest-pic.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"469\" />\r\n\r\n<b>Monday</b>\r\n\r\nFighting off the Blue Mondays? Go literal and head to the <b>Susanne Vielmetter Projects </b>to ditch the blues and immerse yourself in <b>Bart Exposito</b>s muted desert palate. The exhibition, entitled Strange Alphabet, looks to the New Mexico landscape for its inspiration, while the artists atmospheric tan &amp; peach tones and stark minimalist <a href=\"http://www.themirrorcube.com/event/bart-exposito-strange-alphabet-susanne-vielmetter-projects-la\">graphics</a> will cure your Monday slump before you even think to reach for that expired bottle of 5-HTP.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://www.vielmetter.com/public/images/artworks/42/bart-exposito_1437523171_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"543\" height=\"396\" />\r\n<div id=\"msg_1435363124_000003\" class=\" message  show_user  avatar  unread   divider\" data-ts=\"1435363124.000003\"><em><span class=\"message_content\">Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</span></em>\r\n<div class=\"rxn_panel rxns_key_message-1435363124_000003-C06TD3BUJ no_rxns\" data-rxn-key=\"message-1435363124.000003-C06TD3BUJ\"></div>\r\n</div>','Suicide Tuesdays 7/28','','publish','open','open','','suicide-tuesdays-728','','','2015-07-28 20:00:01','2015-07-29 03:00:01','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=786',0,'post','',0),(787,5,'2015-07-28 19:36:22','2015-07-29 02:36:22','','bart-exposito_1437158821_2 (1)','','inherit','open','open','','bart-exposito_1437158821_2-1','','','2015-07-28 19:36:22','2015-07-29 02:36:22','',786,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/bart-exposito_1437158821_2-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(789,5,'2015-07-28 19:47:09','2015-07-29 02:47:09','','Bartthing','','inherit','open','open','','bartthing','','','2015-07-28 19:47:09','2015-07-29 02:47:09','',786,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Bartthing.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(790,5,'2015-07-28 19:49:15','2015-07-29 02:49:15','','barts','','inherit','open','open','','barts','','','2015-07-28 19:49:15','2015-07-29 02:49:15','',786,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/barts.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(791,5,'2015-07-28 19:55:51','2015-07-29 02:55:51','','funeralparadeofroses','','inherit','open','open','','funeralparadeofroses','','','2015-07-28 19:55:51','2015-07-29 02:55:51','',786,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/funeralparadeofroses.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(794,5,'2015-07-29 14:33:44','2015-07-29 21:33:44','<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Give-us-the-Night.png\"><img class=\"  wp-image-799 aligncenter\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Give-us-the-Night-300x78.png\" alt=\"Give us the Night\" width=\"333\" height=\"131\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThis week, wecaught up with one of our favoriteLA DJs,<strong>Alison Swing</strong> about LA nightlife, LA day jobs, <strong>Dig Deeper </strong>and her killer mix, <strong>SWINGSET OO2:: THE FORCE</strong>.\r\n\r\n[embed]https://soundcloud.com/alisonswing/swingset-002-the-force[/embed]\r\n\r\n<b>Wed love to learn more about your upbringing. Are you an LA transplant, or did you grow up here?</b>\r\n\r\nI was born in Torrance but my parents moved us early on to the suburbs. I grew up in Moorpark (about an hours drive north of LA) but spent a lot of time in LA. I moved back to the city in 2010.\r\n\r\n<b>How did you first get involved in the Los Angeles music scene? </b>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/11392958_10153401649354516_3192674521407538647_n.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-795  alignleft\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/11392958_10153401649354516_3192674521407538647_n-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"411\" height=\"272\" /></a>I\'ve always been nerdy about music. My Dad is a guitar teacher so I grew up playing trombone, bass and piano. I used to play in a couple garage bands and a contemporary church band for a while (ha!). I used to go on message boards and go to tons of concerts with my internet friends, so it all progressed very naturally.\r\n\r\nThe first party I ever went to was a 24-hour DROID party. I had to use my friend\'s ID to get in because I was underage and I remember being kind of terrified but completely fascinated by all of it. I haven\'t stopped going to warehouse parties since then.\r\n\r\n<b>You and Masha are really killing it right now. Did you guys meet through the scene, or some other way?</b>\r\n\r\nMasha and I met through mutual friends at the first Detroit Swindle party here. We both had flown to see them in San Francisco and here in LA on our own accord. I feel really lucky that we met, because we\'re both female DJs, almost exactly the same age and share a whole lot of love &amp; energy for the scene and, most importantly, the music.\r\n\r\n<b>Tell us a little more about your residency. When and how did you get involved with Dig Deeper? How would you describe the music and vibe to someone who hasnt been to your events? </b>\r\n\r\nMasha and I <i>are</i> Dig Deeper! We started Dig Deeper together in September 2014 because we wanted an outlet to bring in our favorite acts that weren\'t getting the attention they deserved. We put love into every aspect of our parties, from the bookings to the decor, to what food we\'re taking the DJs out to. It\'s hard to describe  come party with us and you\'ll see what the hype is about!\r\n\r\n<b>Whats your day job?</b>\r\n\r\nI\'m a graphic designer for the super kawaii brand, tokidoki. I\'ve been there for five years now. I design mostly t-shirts and hats, as well as doing some pretty fun collaboration work with brands like Barbie and Hello Kitty. I love it there! Having a creative full-time job outside of music presents its own challenges, but it\'s very rewarding.\r\n\r\n<b>How does your work in graphic design translate into your DJ life? </b>\r\n\r\nI got more involved with the \"scene\" when I started designing party flyers and album covers. It was a creative outlet and a way for me to tie the two things I love most together. It got to be a little too much to balance for a while though. Right now, I only design for Dig Deeper and a few other exciting projects, but I used to design about three flyers a week. One of the projects I have coming up is a poster for TBD Fest, for their artist series that I also participated in last year.\r\n\r\nOne of my life goals is to further integrate my love for music and design. I really feel so at home in both fields, and have been extremely lucky to be able to do both as my careers.\r\n\r\n<b>As a female DJ, do you feel like promoters or fans treat you differently than your male colleagues?</b>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/11174854_10206924115329333_7889844221977630733_n.jpg\"><img class=\"  wp-image-797  alignright\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/11174854_10206924115329333_7889844221977630733_n-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"416\" height=\"277\" /></a>\r\n\r\nIn general, I feel people have been really supportive and eager to help me, which has been really motivating and heartwarming. But on the other side it\'s always weird to me to be referred to as a \"female DJ\"; no one would ever called me a \"female graphic designer\". Something I really want to push with my own image and events is that it should just be the norm now. We\'re just DJs.\r\n\r\nOf course, as with most professions in nightlife, there are other elements men don\'t really have to deal with. I\'ve been drugged twice now, so I have to always watch my drinks. Some fans and other promoters have made remarks blaming being a female on any sign of success or making up disgusting reasons for us getting bookings. It really bothers me. It\'s total bullshit, but it just motivates me to dig deeper for records and work harder on becoming a badass mixer!\r\n\r\n<b>Tell us more about this mix, </b><b><i>Swingset 002</i></b><i>  </i><b><i>The Force</i></b><b>. What were you inspired by or hoping to channel?</b>\r\n\r\nLast year when I was designing too much and had a complete creative breakdown, I decided to go on a three-week solo trip around Europe. It was my first time leaving the country. I spent a lot of time record shopping in Berlin and Amsterdam so I used a lot of those records in this mix. I always want to base mixes on very specific memories. This mix was inspired by a super-long 7am bike ride with a guy I met in Amsterdam after seeing Eddie C play. It kind of felt like a diary entry for me.\r\n\r\n<b>Where can our readers catch Alison Swing playing next?</b>\r\n\r\nThe next Dig Deeper is August 14th with Eamon Harkin &amp; Justin Carter (Mister Saturday Night)! You can also follow my <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/mynameisalisonandiliketodancealot?fref=ts\">Facebook fan page</a> for other various dates before then.\r\n\r\n<em>Featured image courtesy of Photographer Erin Keefe.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</em>','\"We\'re Just DJ\'s\": Digging Deeper with Alison Swing','','publish','open','open','','were-just-djs-digging-deeper-with-alison-swing','','','2015-07-29 14:33:44','2015-07-29 21:33:44','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=794',0,'post','',0),(795,5,'2015-07-29 13:28:24','2015-07-29 20:28:24','','11392958_10153401649354516_3192674521407538647_n','','inherit','open','open','','11392958_10153401649354516_31926745214