0:39','2015-10-16 19:10:39','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=templatera&#038;p=819',0,'templatera','',0),(820,4,'2015-07-30 18:38:32','2015-07-31 01:38:32','[vc_row full_width=\"\" parallax=\"\" parallax_image=\"\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\n{Buy button}\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Module - Tickets','','publish','closed','closed','','module-tickets','','','2015-10-14 13:00:23','2015-10-14 20:00:23','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?post_type=templatera&#038;p=820',0,'templatera','',0),(825,5,'2015-08-04 21:47:43','2015-08-05 04:47:43','Stave off your weekday woes with flicks, skate chicks and just a touch of Earl Sweatshirt.\r\n<h2><b>Wednesday </b></h2>\r\nIf you missed any of Outfest, head towards Weho for<b>BEST OF FEST SHORTS, </b>a compilation of must-seeshort <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/453058874871602/\">films</a>from this year\'s festival.\r\n\r\nLGBTQIA filmhits &amp; highlights include<em>Queer Habits</em>,<em> Day Drunk Gays</em>, and<em>Tomgirl</em>, adding up to one hell ofagay ol\' time.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xtf1/v/t1.0-9/11817173_10153549064104031_1818673170483198434_n.png?oh=948cddfcdd2bc4fc9234422151aba58a&amp;oe=56423466\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"355\" />\r\n<h2><b>Thursday</b></h2>\r\nCan\'t wait for the weekend? Anafternoon drive should be enough to tide you over. This Thursday, skipthe Gosling and head towards <b>Library West Hollywood</b> for a matinee<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/673475122753579/\">screening</a> of <b><em>Rear Window</em>! </b>Ifclassic film isn\'t quite enough to lure you, we\'ve heard there will bepopcorn and lemonade to accompany the iconic Hitchcock black &amp; white.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://www.leninimports.com/hitchcock_rear_window_gallery_photo_4_new.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"770\" height=\"559\" />\r\n\r\nIf Hitchcock leaves you cravingsomething a little more upbeat  or simply higher in altitude, hit the downtown<b> Standard</b> for <b>RESTLESS ON THE ROOF</b>, a killer new firstThursday party from our friends at <b><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/RestlessNites\">Restless Nites</a>!</b>\r\n\r\nThis weeks party features a SECRET GUEST (from <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/CUTTERSRECORDS\">Cutters Records</a>, Australia),plus the five-fingered cast of the <strong>Restless Nites</strong> DJs:\r\n\r\n<strong>Eli Glad</strong>, <strong>Luke Mele</strong>, <strong>Brian Tarney</strong>, <strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/remytherestless\">Remy Marc</a> </strong>(of <strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/thebodyisavessel\">VSSL</a>/<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/Dublab/108443909176099\">Dublab</a></strong>) and <strong>Kat Matutina</strong> (aka <strong>Pickpocket</strong> of <strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/donutsparty\">Donuts Party</a></strong>)\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://restlessnites.com/ontheroof\">RSVP</a> for FREE Entry all night long! See you on the roof.\r\n<h2><b>Friday </b></h2>\r\nIn need of a cruise? Dont head for Long Beach just yet. High-tail it over to<strong>Out of Body</strong>\'s<strong>Psychic Summertime Cruise</strong>, a tour of all things deep house &amp; sonic underground.\r\n\r\nThe party lineup features:\r\n\r\n<strong>The 1080p All-Stars</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>KHOTIN</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>D.TIFFANY</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>JOURNEYMANN TRAX aka Bobby Draino</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>OPEN HEIR</strong> b2b<strong> HOLD MC</strong>\r\n\r\nWith sound by <strong>TRUECHORD</strong> and visuals by <strong>DIANA MORA</strong>, this is a trippy musical voyage you wont want to miss. Snag your tickets and RSVP on RN to <a href=\"http://www.restlessnites.com/outofbody/\">attend</a>!\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xtp1/v/t1.0-9/11705285_574453436031006_7872774262287741340_n.jpg?oh=b6628f567506ce503f584158d7b806aa&amp;oe=5648F699\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"622\" />\r\n<h2><b>Saturday </b></h2>\r\nFeeling low? Go with it! Head down Jefferson for the<b>Low End Theory </b><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1439088113062112/?ref=2&amp;ref_dashboard_filter=upcoming&amp;action_history=null\">festival</a>. With alineupfeaturing<b>Flying Lotus, Earl Sweatshirt </b>and some of our favorite<strong>Low End Theory</strong>resident DJs, you\'re bound to leave in high spirits.<img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/fc/Earl_Sweatshirt_March_15,_2013_-_02.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"509\" height=\"376\" />\r\n\r\nOr, if youre less than game forfestival crowds, head to the pier for a free show from <b>Matt &amp; Kim</b>. While it may not include <strong>Earl Sweatshirt</strong> yelling kill people burn shit fuck school, you <em>can</em> expect <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/650197115111765/?ref=2&amp;ref_dashboard_filter=upcoming&amp;action_history=null\">some</a> drumming and clapping from the indie duo.\r\n<h2><b>Sunday </b></h2>\r\nJoin <strong>Kora Colasuonno</strong>,<strong> Jenn Witt</strong> and X-Games gold medalists <strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/lacey.baker.fanpage\">Lacey Baker</a> </strong>and<strong> <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/vanessa.torres.fanpage\">Vanessa Torres</a></strong> for a <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1000957409937757/\">breakdown</a> of the basics of boarding. This awesome skate clinic boasts a fun and inclusive safe space for women/trans/femme-identified folk to take a fall or three in a no-judgement zone! Skaters are advised to arrive in sneaks and BYOBoard if they have one, though there will also be some spares available forvirgin shredders.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"432\"]<img class=\"\" src=\"http://cdn.coresites.factorymedia.com/cooler_new/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/On-Baker-Street-Lacey-Baker-Interview-5.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"432\" height=\"632\" /> Pro Skater Lacey Baker via Factory Media[/caption]\r\n<h2><b>Monday </b></h2>\r\nWhy so serious, subterraneans? Make your way to <strong>El Cid</strong> for<strong> EL SHOW</strong>!, a FREE monthly comedy <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1448241108837033/\">night</a> featuring stand-up, characters, sketch, music and nonsense, hosted by <strong>Sam Brown</strong> (Whitest Kids U Know), <strong>Josh Fadem</strong> (Eagleheart, 30 Rock) &amp; <strong>Eric Moneypenny</strong> (FOX ADHD, The Midnight Show @ UCB).\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This months lineup features <strong>Ashley Barnhill</strong> (FoD\'s Oddball Comedy Fest, HBO\'s Project Greenlight), <strong>Jon Rudnitsky</strong> (Montreal Comedy Festival), <strong>Hormoz Rashidi</strong> (The Comedy Store), <strong>Kim Congdon</strong> (The Comedy Store), and a TOP SECRET CELEBRITY GUEST . . . Arriba, arriba! Andale, andale!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"https://scontent-lax1-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xfa1/t31.0-8/s960x960/11780029_852064168196074_3580706559997580830_o.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"459\" height=\"632\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</em></p>','Suicide Tuesdays 8/4','','publish','open','open','','suicide-tuesdays-84','','','2015-08-07 12:57:57','2015-08-07 19:57:57','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=825',0,'post','',0),(826,5,'2015-08-04 21:00:41','2015-08-05 04:00:41','','James Stewart, Grace Kelly, and Alfred Hitchcock on the set of REAR WINDOW, 1954','','inherit','open','open','','james-stewart-grace-kelly-and-alfred-hitchcock-on-the-set-of-rear-window-1954','','','2015-08-04 21:01:03','2015-08-05 04:01:03','',825,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/013-rear-window-theredlist.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(848,7,'2015-08-11 13:06:32','2015-08-11 20:06:32','&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Scratch, rattle, and howl your way to the weekend.</h2>\r\n<h2><b style=\"line-height: 1\">Tuesday</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Head over to the </span><b>Echoplex</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> to get in the surf </span><a href=\"http://www.themirrorcube.com/event/la-luz-echoplex-la\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">groove</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">! Seattle surf-rockers </span><b>La Luz</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> will captain weeknight subterraneans on a pleasure trip to the depths of distortion as the group celebrates their sophomore album, </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Weirdo Shrine</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, produced by </span><b>Ty Segall</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, who deems the release</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> a world  burning with colors [hed] never seen, like mauve that is living.</span>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_854\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"800\"]<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/La-Luz.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-854 size-large\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/La-Luz-1024x554.jpg\" alt=\"Third Monk\" width=\"800\" height=\"433\" /></a> Third Monk[/caption]\r\n<h2>Wednesday</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">If you never got a chance to see DFW in the flesh, why not take a break from the </span><b><i>Jest</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and head over to </span><b>The Landmark</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> for something a bit more </span><a href=\"http://www.landmarktheatres.com/los-angeles/the-landmark/Film-Info/the-end-of-the-tour%20-10850%20West%20Pico,%20at%20Westwood%20Boulevard,%20Los%20Angeles,%20CA,%2090064\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">finite</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">  a showing of the biopic</span> <b><i>The End of the Tour</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">,</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400\">based on the life of beloved author </span><b>David Foster Wallace</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/DFW.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-852 size-full\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/DFW.jpg\" alt=\"DFW\" width=\"640\" height=\"420\" /></a>\r\n<h2>Thursday</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Has Thursday got you howling at the moon? Dont hold it in too long. Head for the </span><b>Egyptian Theater</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> for a </span><a href=\"http://www.americancinemathequecalendar.com/content/the-howling-0\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">screening</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> of the classic 80s film </span><b><i>The Howling</i></b><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span></i>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/The-Howling.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-857 size-full\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/The-Howling.jpg\" alt=\"The-Howling\" width=\"780\" height=\"500\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Or, if youre more in need of a good rattle, make your way to Echo Parks </span><b>Stories Bookstore</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> for the </span><b><i>Rattling Wall</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> Issue 5 reading &amp; release </span><a href=\"http://storiesla.com/blogs/events\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">party</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">.</span>\r\n<h2>Friday</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Shimmy your way downtown for</span><b> Dig Deeper LA</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, as </span><b>Eamon Harkin</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> &amp; </span><b>Justin Carter</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> mix deep house with classic 90s drum and bass. Spearheaded by vinyl junkie residents </span><b>Alison Swing</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> &amp; </span><b>Masha</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, you can expect steamy, subterranean environs pulsing with techno, electro &amp; house. Dig Deepers intimate parties pair impressive headliners with the best of the LA underground. RSVP on </span><b>Restless Nights</b> <a href=\"http://www.restlessnites.com/digdeeper/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">to snag a ticket</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and receive the secret location! </span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/Mister-Saturday-Night.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-855 size-full\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/Mister-Saturday-Night.jpg\" alt=\"Mister Saturday Night\" width=\"960\" height=\"355\" /></a>\r\n<h2>Saturday</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Hung out to dry from the LA heat? </span><b>Cold War Kids</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> save the day with the raw intensity of upbeat, throbbing, and bluesy indie rock. Part of KCRWs </span><b><i>Sound in Focus</i></b><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Saturday promises a vigorous live concert experience, replete with plenty of raucous stomping. </span><a href=\"http://www.annenbergphotospace.org/events/sound-focus-concerts-cold-war-kids-other-lives/2015-08-15\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">RSVP</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> to attend and arrive early to snag your spot.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/Cold_War_Kids.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-851 size-large\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/Cold_War_Kids-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"Cold_War_Kids\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" /></a>\r\n<h2>Friday, Saturday &amp; Sunday</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Cashed out and tired of hefty festival lines?</span> <a href=\"http://epr.la/\"><b>Echo Park Rising</b></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> is a three-day free event loaded with buzzworthy local acts and popular local food trucks. Spread out along Sunset Blvd, Glendale Blvd, and Echo Park Ave, the festival allows anyone to check out the scenesters amidst a diverse selection of up-and-coming artists. Dance, headbang, or mosh</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400\">to the sounds of tomorrow. Who knows? You may stumble upon a new audio obsession or catch the next big thing before it hits Pitchfork.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/echo-park-rising-2015.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-853 size-large\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/echo-park-rising-2015-695x1024.jpg\" alt=\"echo-park-rising-2015\" width=\"695\" height=\"1024\" /></a>\r\n<h2>Monday</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Got a case of the Manic Mondays? Scratch it out at </span><b>The Cinefamily</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">s </span><a href=\"http://www.themirrorcube.com/event/free-screening-of-scratch-the-cinefamily-la\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">screening</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> of </span><b><i>Scratch</i></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, a documentary tracing the history of spinning from the heyday of vinyl to the collectors &amp; record junkies of today.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/scratch.jpg..jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-856 size-large\" src=\"http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/scratch.jpg.-1024x688.jpg\" alt=\"scratch.jpg.\" width=\"800\" height=\"538\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</em>','Suicide Tuesdays 8/11','','publish','open','open','','suicide-tuesdays-811','','','2015-08-11 14:15:25','2015-08-11 21:15:25','',0,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/?p=848',0,'post','',0),(849,7,'2015-08-11 13:05:20','2015-08-11 20:05:20','','6439602217_8a49cf1be8_b','','inherit','open','open','','6439602217_8a49cf1be8_b','','','2015-08-11 13:05:20','2015-08-11 20:05:20','',848,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/6439602217_8a49cf1be8_b.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(851,7,'2015-08-11 14:05:55','2015-08-11 21:05:55','','Cold_War_Kids','','inherit','open','open','','cold_war_kids','','','2015-08-11 14:09:02','2015-08-11 21:09:02','',848,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/Cold_War_Kids.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(852,7,'2015-08-11 14:05:59','2015-08-11 21:05:59','','DFW','','inherit','open','open','','dfw','','','2015-08-11 14:08:12','2015-08-11 21:08:12','',848,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/DFW.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(853,7,'2015-08-11 14:06:01','2015-08-11 21:06:01','','echo-park-rising-2015','','inherit','open','open','','echo-park-rising-2015','','','2015-08-11 14:09:15','2015-08-11 21:09:15','',848,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/echo-park-rising-2015.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(854,7,'2015-08-11 14:06:04','2015-08-11 21:06:04','','La-Luz','Third Monk','inherit','open','open','','la-luz','','','2015-08-11 14:07:37','2015-08-11 21:07:37','',848,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/La-Luz.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(855,7,'2015-08-11 14:06:05','2015-08-11 21:06:05','','Mister Saturday Night','','inherit','open','open','','mister-saturday-night','','','2015-08-11 14:08:47','2015-08-11 21:08:47','',848,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/Mister-Saturday-Night.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(856,7,'2015-08-11 14:06:08','2015-08-11 21:06:08','','scratch.jpg.','','inherit','open','open','','scratch-jpg','','','2015-08-11 14:09:36','2015-08-11 21:09:36','',848,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/scratch.jpg..jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(857,7,'2015-08-11 14:06:10','2015-08-11 21:06:10','','The-Howling','','inherit','open','open','','the-howling','','','2015-08-11 14:08:30','2015-08-11 21:08:30','',848,'http://walkthenight.wpengine.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/The-Howling.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(863,6,'2015-08-14 12:06:44','2015-08-14 19:06:44','<i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Hey, Baby</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">. Ready to break out those jellies, chokers and punky plaids?</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Club 90s</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> has built a reputation on throwing massive LA ragers celebrating all things GenX, with residents </span><b>Bipjeffington</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, </span><b>Bruce Perdew</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and </span><b>Jason Lavitt</b> <b></b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">spinning pop classics b2b, accompanied by all your favorite 90s music videos via projector.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Past party themes include Blink 182 and</span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> Clueless</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, while this weekends festivities look to the ska-pop stylings of </span><b>No Doubt</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">, so its bound to be HELLA GOOD.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Expect crop tees, mohawks, stripes, baggy faded jeans, bindis and maybe some bleached hair. But underneath it all are just some Angelenos &amp; Angelenas looking to vibe out to some 90s tunage &amp; toast to a pre-Harajuku Gwen. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Bring your favorite dance partner and keep your eyes peeled for loads of Gwenabees.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">To attend, RSVP on </span><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1159874724029370/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Facebook</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400\"> and head to The Regent before 10pm for $5 entry, as ticket prices rise to $10 later in the evening.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Perks include a Gwen Stefani photo booth, free pins for the first 400 attendees, and an on-site T-shirt printing press!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">90s outfits are highly encouraged, and the best-dressed Gwenabee will receive a free limited edition T-shirt.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/gwennnn.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-865 size-large\" src=\"http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/gwennnn-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Get a little loose, lipsync to your favorite hits, and unearth some deep cuts from 90s ska revivalists.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400\">See you on the dancefloor  we imagine it wont be a tragic kingdom at all.</span>\r\n\r\n<em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the bodily fluid exchange. We scour the web, pluck from pop cultures best and lowest-hanging fruit, and stick out afterhours til the last last call. We walk the night hard  so you dont have to.</em>','The Sweat Spot : Club 90s No Doubt Night','','publish','open','open','','the-sweat-spot-club-90s-no-doubt-night','','','2015-08-14 12:06:44','2015-08-14 19:06:44','',0,'http://walkthenight.com/la/?p=863',0,'post','',0),(864,6,'2015-08-14 12:00:52','2015-08-14 19:00:52','','tumblr_mcf3rmAdOV1rorii7o1_1280','','inherit','open','open','','tumblr_mcf3rmadov1rorii7o1_1280','','','2015-08-14 12:00:52','2015-08-14 19:00:52','',863,'http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/tumblr_mcf3rmAdOV1rorii7o1_1280.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(865,6,'2015-08-14 12:02:34','2015-08-14 19:02:34','','Stefani At Benefit','Popular American singer Gwen Stefani of the band No Doubt, dressed in an orange and silver patterened sarong and a black, midriff-baring tank top, attends the Race to Erase MS benefit, Century City, California, November 15, 1997. (Photo by Albert Ortega/Online USA, Inc./Getty Images)','inherit','open','open','','stefani-at-benefit','','','2015-08-14 12:02:34','2015-08-14 19:02:34','',863,'http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/gwennnn.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(871,6,'2015-08-25 18:16:07','2015-08-26 01:16:07','Stretch out the last few days of summer with psych-rock, rowdy retro grooves, and a little help from Jessica Rabbit.\r\n<h2><b style=\"line-height: 1;\">Tuesday</b></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">After headlining FYF this last weekend, controversial and innovative rap group</span><b> DEATH GRIPS </b><a href=\"http://www.mirrorcube.com/event/death-grips-glass-house-la\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">cause</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> an intimate ruckus in LA.<strong>Death Grips</strong> unsuspectingly embodies the ideals of a modern punk band in the 21st century, mixing intense neo-techno hip hop withaninsatiable urgeto stick it to the man (Zuckerberg? Draper? Trump?). Heres your chance to get all of your pent-up aggression out in one show! Just discreetly pretend youre punching your boss in the face. </span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/2012_10_17_NPRLPR_192-1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-878 size-medium\" src=\"http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/2012_10_17_NPRLPR_192-1-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a>\r\n<h2>Wednesday</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fancy a psych-rock tongue twister? Hit The Echo for </span><b>King Gizzard and the Lizzard Wizard</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">! The seven-piece Aussie psych-rock band (boasting two drummers)is known forloads of twelve-minute progressive/krautrock songs that build. Get ready for a </span><a href=\"http://www.theecho.com/event/901327-king-gizzard-lizard-wizard-los-angeles/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">night</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> of headbanging, ethereal pop jams, &amp;bliss. Openers <strong>Mild High Club</strong> channel 60s popedelia with swirling hints of dazed confusion. Zone out, chill out, and keep on rockin in the free world.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/king-gizz.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-876 size-medium\" src=\"http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/king-gizz-300x296.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"296\" /></a>\r\n<h2>Thursday</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Enjoy your evening </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Thriller</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> with a side of</span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Bad</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">? Like to live your life on a roll? Lace up your skates and break out that solo sequined glove for a </span><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1469292853386495/\"><b>Michael Jackson skate night </b></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">to remember. </span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/thriller-2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-874 size-medium\" src=\"http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/thriller-2-300x163.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"163\" /></a>\r\n<h2>Friday</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Tired of whitewashed comedy nights? </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Step into to a world without a Raymond in sight at </span><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1599412936975594/\"><b>Hurt White Feelings</b></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, a diverse comedy night boasting queers, women, people of color, and plenty of laughs. Grab a drink and catch the next rising comedy star amidst the nights revelry, you may forget white guilt altogether!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Or, if youre</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">feeling nostalgic, head to the </span><b>El Rey</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, as</span><b> Chicano Batman</b> <a href=\"http://www.theelrey.com/events/detail/278873\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">bring</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">back the sounds of yesteryear, creating spot-on renditions of 70s funk, soul, and latin in one neat &amp; original package. Boogie down to the perfect music forcruising beautiful Southern California beachside highways.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/chicano_batman_article.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-877 size-medium\" src=\"http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/chicano_batman_article-300x171.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"171\" /></a></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Saturday</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Feeling a little off-kilter? Go full on STRANGE! </span><b>Way Strange Fest</b> <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/100655316936888/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">promises</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> loads of Cali-bleached reverb rock, bringing big headliners as well as up-and-coming Pomona acts. San Diego slacker rockers <strong>Tomorrows Tulips</strong> headline the fest, along with several other notable SoCal-drenched summer-vibers. Come out &amp;enjoy a day of bottomless tuneage with the first annual <strong>Way Strange Fest</strong>. Who knows? This might be the next FYF.</span>\r\n<h2>Sunday</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Where better to watch the queen of Soul then at the <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"http://www.hollywoodbowl.com/tickets/erykah-badu-st-vincent/2015-08-30\">Bowl</a></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">? Catch </span><b>Erykah Badu</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">s unique neosoul tunes live while the beautiful LA sky slowly descends to midnight. Dont forget to come early and catch upbeat experimental pop melodies from</span><b> St. Vincent</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, while </span><b>Moses Sumney</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">s R&amp;B experimentation will open the show</span>.</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/Erykah_badu-02-mika.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-875 size-medium\" src=\"http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/Erykah_badu-02-mika-297x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"297\" height=\"300\" /></a>\r\n<h2>Monday</h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This Monday, skip the drive-in and plunge into the citys aquatic alternative,<strong> The Dive In Theater</strong>. Your typical chill Monday evening will take on a new water-clad form with a splash of the bikini-ready curves of Jessica Rabbit, as we </span><a href=\"http://www.timeout.com/los-angeles/things-to-do/dive-in-theatre-skybar-september-7-2015\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">blast</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> back to the Summer of 88 with the classic </span><b><i>Who Framed Roger Rabbit?</i></b>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/maxresdefault-1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-872 size-medium\" src=\"http://walkthenight.com/la/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/08/maxresdefault-1-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"169\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<em>Walk the Night is your new best friend  like Tinder without the